Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.63,0:00:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,通过电影《2001太空漫游》\NAnd with that movie 2001,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.99,0:00:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你为我们展现了21世纪的样貌\Nyou're projecting us into the 21st century.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.65,0:00:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我把儿子乔纳森带来了\NI brought along my son Jonathan...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.58,0:00:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,到2001年他就跟我现在的岁数一样大\NWho in the year 2001 will be the same age as I am now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.35,0:00:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,也许他更能适应\NMaybe he will be better adjusted
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.15,0:00:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你所描绘的那个世界\Nto this kind of world that you're trying to portray.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.45,0:00:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,最大的区别在于  等他长大的时候\NThe big difference, when he grows up...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.25,0:00:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,假如我们愿意等到2001年...\NIn fact, if we wanted to wait till the year 2001...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.65,0:00:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他就能在自己的家里\NHe will have in his own house
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.51,0:00:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,拥有一个控制台\Nnot a computer as big as this,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.64,0:00:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是这么巨大的电脑\Nbut at least a console
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.98,0:00:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(242.25,227)}亚瑟·C·克拉克
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.98,0:00:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}英国科幻作家
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.60,0:00:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他可以通过控制台来访问本地电脑\Nthrough which he can talk to his friendly local computer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.49,0:00:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,从而得到日常所需的一切信息\Nand get all the information he needs for his everyday life,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,比如银行账单  剧院预订记录\Nlike his bank statements, his theater reservations,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.49,0:01:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,一切生活在\Nall the information you need
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.21,0:01:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,复杂的现代社会中  所需要的信息\Nin the course of living in a complex modern society.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.04,0:01:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,一切尽在家中的小小装置里\NThis will be in a compact form in his own house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.16,0:01:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,由像这样的电视屏幕和键盘组成\NHe'll have a television screen, like these here, and a keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.68,0:01:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他可以访问电脑获取信息\NAnd he'll talk to the computer and get information from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.55,0:01:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,看待它就像我们看待电话那样认为理所当然\NAnd he'll take it as much for granted as we take the telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.56,0:01:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我很好奇\NI wonder, though, what sort
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.33,0:01:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,那时的社交生活会变成什么样\Nof a life would it be like in social terms?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.81,0:01:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们的全部生活都围绕电脑展开\NI mean, if our whole life is built around the computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.44,0:01:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,那会是一个电脑依赖型社会吗\Ndo we become a computer-dependent society?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.57,0:01:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,某些方面是  但它们也会丰富我们的生活\NIn some ways, but they will also enrich our society
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.75,0:01:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,因为它让我们\Nbecause it will make it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.91,0:01:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,去任何自己喜欢的地方居住成为可能\Npossible for us to live, really, anywhere we like.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.55,0:01:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,商人和主管可以住在地球上几乎任何地方\NAny businessman and executive could live almost anywhere on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.50,0:01:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,而仍能通过这样的设备来管理企业\Nand still do his business through a device like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.21,0:01:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这多棒啊\NAnd this is a wonderful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.29,0:01:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,意味着我们将不必被城市所束缚\NIt means we won't have to be stuck in cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.53,0:01:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以住在偏远乡村或者任何宜人之处\NWe'll be able to live out in the country or wherever we please.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.05,0:01:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,屏幕提示这是个未执行问题\NScreen says it's an unimplemented trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.17,0:01:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,但是错误代码不对  是系统错误\NBut the error code is wrong. It's a system error.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.38,0:01:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(195,48)}库比蒂诺\N加利福尼亚州
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.72,0:01:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,-所以呢  -它不会跟大家问好\N- So what's the upshot? - It's not gonna say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.67,0:02:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,它肯定会跟大家问好\NIt absolutely is gonna say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.89,0:02:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(195,47)}麦金塔发布会
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.98,0:02:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,不能怪谁  这是系统错误\NIt's nobody's fault. It's a system error.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.05,0:02:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,是你开发的语音演示\NYou built the voice demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.30,0:02:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,语音演示不稳定  我一直跟你说...\NThe voice demo is flaky. I've been telling you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.98,0:02:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你声音小点\NKeep your voices down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.81,0:02:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,演示样本做得太大了\Nthat for... This thing is overbuilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.49,0:02:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,昨晚还能用  前晚也是\NIt worked last night. It worked the night before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.14,0:02:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,三个小时前还能用\NIt worked three hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.32,0:02:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,现在不能用了\NIt's not working now,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.16,0:02:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,-跳过语音演示吧  -去你妈的\N- so just skip over the voice demo. - Fuck you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.10,0:02:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,其他的都没问题\NEverything else is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.86,0:02:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,跳过语音演示吧\NSkip over the voice demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.33,0:02:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要它来问好\NWe need it to say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.31,0:02:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,你根本没听我说什么\NYou're not hearing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.11,0:02:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,-不会有问好的  -修复就行了\N- It's not going to say hello. - Just fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.77,0:02:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,-修复  -没错\N- Fix it? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.63,0:02:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-在40分钟内  -修复它\N- In 40 minutes? - Fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.78,0:02:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-我办不到  -那谁能办到\N- I can't. - Who's the person who can?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.46,0:02:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是能办到的人  但我也不行\NI'm the person who can, and I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.19,0:02:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,-到底有多糟糕  -非常糟糕\N- How bad are you saying? - It's pretty bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.81,0:02:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我不懂你的意思\NI don't know what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.02,0:02:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,意思是演示样本很有可能会崩溃\NIt means the demo is more than likely gonna crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.22,0:02:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你们得小点声\NYou have to keep your voices down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.43,0:02:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,乔尔·普福尔茨海姆就坐在厅里看着\NJoel Pforzheimer is sitting out in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.63,0:02:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我才不管...  乔尔·普福尔茨海姆是谁\NI don't care if... Who's Joel Pforzheimer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.57,0:02:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,《绅士季刊》记者\N《GQ》.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.98,0:02:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他已经跟了你一周了  你没发现吗\NHe's been shadowing you for a week. Did you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.58,0:02:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,装作一切正常\NJust look like everything's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.36,0:02:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他就在厅里看着呢\NHe's sitting out in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.76,0:02:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,你们怎么看\NWhat are you guys saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.15,0:03:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,某种竞态条件\NSome kind of race condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.38,0:03:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们还没能追溯到\Nbut we haven't been able to track it down yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.67,0:03:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,合成器取样够快吗\NIs the synthesizer sampling fast enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.49,0:03:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(156.75,211)}抱歉  发生错误
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.25,0:03:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,不够  速度下来了  而且一直崩溃\NNo, so the rates are off and it keeps crashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.07,0:03:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,不过就是两小时发布会中的二十秒\NIt's 20 seconds out of a two-hour launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.93,0:03:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么不能去掉呢\NWhy not just cut it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.92,0:03:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,-不能去掉  -能  你就去掉吧\N- We can't cut it. - Yeah, you just cut it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.53,0:03:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,两天前  我们在超级碗上\NTwo days ago, we ran a Super Bowl
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.98,0:03:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,放了条本来能拿奥斯卡最佳短片的广告\Nad that could've won the Oscar for Best Short Film.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.71,0:03:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,记住那条广告的人\NThere are more people who can tell
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.57,0:03:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,比记得比赛冠军的人还多\Nyou about the ad than can tell you who won the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.50,0:03:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我明白  但是广告只说\NI understand, but the ad said
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.20,0:03:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,麦金塔电脑将拯救世界\Nthe Mac was gonna save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.59,0:03:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,没说它会问好啊\NIt didn't say it was gonna say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.18,0:03:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,五分钟后开门入场\NWe open the house in five.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.42,0:03:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,别开门\NDon't open the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.23,0:03:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,短暂休息一下\NWe're taking a quick break.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.71,0:03:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,-部分问题在于...  -什么\N- Part of the problem is... - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.21,0:03:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以重新编译\NWe can recompile, but if it's
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.94,0:03:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果是硬件问题\Na hardware problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.92,0:03:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我们没法打开机器后面\Nwe can't get into the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.38,0:03:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么不能\NWhy not?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.03,0:03:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,-你来说还是我来说  -别惹我\N- Do you wanna tell her or should I? - Don't start with me, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.73,0:03:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么他没法打开机器后面\NWhy can't he get into the machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.50,0:03:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,需要特殊工具\NYou need special tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.72,0:03:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,什么特殊工具  拿个螺丝刀不就好了\NWhat kind of special tools? Just take a screwdriver.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.77,0:03:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,他不希望用户能打开机器\NHe didn't want users to be able to open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.88,0:03:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,必须要用特殊工具\NYou need special tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.29,0:03:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,这是真的吗\NIs this for real?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.30,0:03:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这里有上百个工程师\NThere are a hundred engineers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.34,0:03:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,走来走去  难道他们就没人有吗\Nwalking around here. None of them have the tools?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.30,0:03:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,说实话  没有多少人给发了这种工具\NIn fairness, not many of them were issued the tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:03:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你呢\NWhat about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.98,0:04:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我的落在办公室了  那可是凌晨3点...\NI left them at the office. It was 3:00 AM when I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.12,0:04:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我的天\NOh, Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.76,0:04:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,-去掉"你好"吧  -不行\N- Cut "Hello." - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.40,0:04:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,发布会的第一准则是什么\NWhat's the first rule of a launch?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.86,0:04:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,不会崩溃的\NIt's not gonna crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.83,0:04:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,已经崩溃了\NIt just did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.99,0:04:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪\NAndy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.32,0:04:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,哪一个\NWhich one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.41,0:04:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,另一个安迪  你就站这儿我喊什么\NThe other Andy. You're right there. Why would I be calling out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.22,0:04:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,-他有事找你  -好的\N- He needs to talk to you. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.48,0:04:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(87.75,78)}抱歉  发生错误
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.78,0:04:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,把出口的标志灯关掉\NThe exit signs need to be
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.86,0:04:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,不然达不到全黑的效果\Noff or we're not gonna get a full blackout.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.38,0:04:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经跟\NWe've spoken to the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}出口
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.92,0:04:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-物业和消防局谈过了  -然后呢\N- building manager and the fire marshal. - And?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.80,0:04:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,他们绝不同意我们把出口标志灯关掉\NThere's no way they're gonna let us turn the exit signs off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.91,0:04:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,多少罚款我都付\NI'll pay whatever the fine is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.27,0:04:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,罚款就是他们会闯进来赶走所有人\NThe fine is they're gonna come in and tell everyone to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.50,0:04:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你跟消防局说了\NYou explained to the fire marshal
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.66,0:04:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是在这儿改变世界的吗\Nthat we're in here changing the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.96,0:04:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我说了  但是除非我们能\NI did, but unless we can also
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.53,0:04:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,改变火的属性  不然他根本不在乎\Nchange the properties of fire, he doesn't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.60,0:04:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,-史蒂夫  -如果一场火能让大家\N- Steve... - If a fire causes a stampede
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,逃到没标志的出口\Nto the unmarked exits,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.57,0:04:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,对那些幸存者来说也很值了\Nit'll have been well worth it for those who survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.87,0:04:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,对那些没能幸存的\NFor those who don't,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.85,0:04:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,没那么值  但还是很好了\Nless so, but still pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.37,0:04:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-我  -我需要黑暗  全黑\N- Look, I... - I need it to go black. Real black.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.78,0:04:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,把出口标志灯关掉  不管你用什么方法\NGet rid of the exit signs and don't let me know how you did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.04,0:04:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,把语音演示修好\NFix the voice demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.98,0:04:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你真的需要特殊工具来打开Mac吗\NYou need special tools to open the Mac?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.35,0:04:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道它是个封闭系统\NYou knew it was a closed system.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:04:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道这是字面意思  天哪\NI didn't know literally. Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.92,0:05:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你再这样毫无理由地勉强别人\NAnd if you keep alienating people for no reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.15,0:05:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,就没人会留下来听它问好了\Nthere's gonna be no one left for it to say hello to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.47,0:05:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是毫无理由\NIt's not for no reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.03,0:05:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我们搞砸了  IBM就会\NWe blow this and IBM will
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.19,0:05:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,像蝙蝠侠里的反派一样统治接下来的50年\Nown the next 50 years like a Batman villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.30,0:05:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,记得电话公司吗\NRemember the phone company?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.70,0:05:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,那是贝尔公司的叫法  "电话公司"\NThat's what Bell was called, "The phone company."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.07,0:05:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,IBM将成为电脑公司\NIBM will be the computer company.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.11,0:05:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,十年后他们就会成为信息公司\NTen years later they'll be the information company,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.49,0:05:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,对人类来说可是大不幸\Nand that's very bad for the human race.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.16,0:05:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们没时间装绅士谈现实了\NSo we don't have time to be polite or realistic,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,因为如果这样的话\N'cause if we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.56,0:05:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,公司的下一场产品发布会\Nthis company's next product launch
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.18,0:05:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,就只能在26个人\Nwill be held in front of 26 people
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.05,0:05:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,和阿拉梅达县购物指南的兼职记者前开了\Nand a stringer from the Alameda County Shopper's Guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.89,0:05:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我们还没宣传过语音软件\NWe haven't advertised the voice software.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.82,0:05:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以从演示里\NWe could pull it out of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.76,0:05:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,切出来  没人会失望的\Nthe demo and no one would be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.97,0:05:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,你能不能理性一点\NDo you want to try being reasonable,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.02,0:05:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,试试看吧\Njust, you know, see what it feels like?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.66,0:05:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧  切掉语音演示\NOkay. Pull the voice demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.33,0:05:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.34,0:05:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,顺便把发布会也取消\NAnd then cancel the launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.35,0:05:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我懂了  你又耍我\NI see. You just tricked me a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.04,0:05:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以跟我讲它有多不重要\NYou can tell me how unimportant it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果电脑没能问好\Nbut if the computer doesn't say hello,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.36,0:05:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰·斯卡利也不会上台\Nthen neither will John Sculley,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.48,0:05:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我保证他肯定支持我\Nwho I promise you agrees with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.99,0:06:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,斯卡利才不会取消发布会\NSculley's not gonna cancel the launch
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.39,0:06:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他还没疯\N'cause he's not insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.67,0:06:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,他也不是黑客\NHe's also not a hack,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.29,0:06:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,但是为了麦金塔\Nand when it comes to the Macintosh,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.82,0:06:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫他做什么他都愿意\Nhe's gonna do what I ask him to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.65,0:06:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,-盒子里是什么  -不用你操心\N- What's in this box? - Nothing you need to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,别打开\NDon't even open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.50,0:06:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,搞什么\NWhat the fuck?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.80,0:06:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(378,186)}《时代》年度机器
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.80,0:06:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(307.5,205)}计算机时代来临
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.65,0:06:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么这里有一箱...  谁干的\NWhy is there a carton of... Who did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.20,0:06:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,-有人觉得...  -谁\N- Somebody thought... - Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.45,0:06:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,不重要  他觉得\NDoesn't matter. Thought it would
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.77,0:06:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,每人座位上放一份《时代》封面复印件\Nbe a good idea to have copies of that Time cover
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.23,0:06:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,挺好的\Navailable at everyone's seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.47,0:06:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,已经被扼杀在摇篮里了\NIt was nipped in the bud and all
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.91,0:06:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,所有复印件都会被搬出大楼\Nthe copies are being taken out of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.59,0:06:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,问题已经解决了\NSo problem solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.09,0:06:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,-这不是麦金塔  -我明白\N- This isn't a Macintosh. - I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.68,0:06:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,有人觉得在麦金塔的发布会上\NSomebody thought it would be a good idea to, like,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,热情地分发\Nenthusiastically hand over
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.58,0:06:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,印着不是麦金塔的《时代》封面\Ncopies of Time with a not-a-Macintosh on the cover
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.67,0:06:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,是个好主意吗\Nat the launch of the Macintosh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.52,0:06:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,他们要在惠普发什么呢\NWhat are they handing out at Hewlett-Packard?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.30,0:06:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,一堆印着我照片的苹果吗\NA bushel of apples with my face on them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.03,0:06:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信这想法主要是\NI'm sure the thinking was
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.76,0:06:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,考虑到电脑是年度人物\Nthat since the computer is Man of the Year
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.01,0:06:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,会对我们有所帮助\Nthat that's good for our business,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.16,0:06:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,但我说了  我会把它们都扔出大楼的\Nbut like I said, I'm having them removed from the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.70,0:06:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望你做的是\NWhat I'd like you to do
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.44,0:06:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,拿着这全部的2600份复印件\Nwith them is to take them, all 2,600 copies,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.15,0:06:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,堆到科特克的桌上\Nand stack them on Kottke's desk
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:06:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉他史蒂夫祝他新年快乐\Nand tell him Steve says, "Happy New Year to you."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.65,0:07:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,-好  -我给了《时代》杂志完全访问权限\N- Okay. - I gave Time magazine full access.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.01,0:07:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,全部产品  Bandley  Apple Ⅱ  Lisa\NThe whole campus: Bandley, Apple II, Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.90,0:07:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,给了他斯卡利  马库拉\NI gave him Sculley, Markkula.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.30,0:07:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,给了他沃兹  给了他所有人\NI gave him Woz. I gave him everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.68,0:07:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我应该怎么称呼那个\NWhat should I call the person
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.81,0:07:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,想到分发这封面这种好主意的人呢\Nwho thought it'd be a good idea to hand these out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.01,0:07:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会告诉你是谁的\NI'm not telling you who it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.97,0:07:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,这事并没有恶意  也已经妥善解决了\NIt was done without malice. It's been taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.45,0:07:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,而你还有一个半小时  我们有正事要说\NYou have a half hour and we have things to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.25,0:07:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,比如\NLike what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.51,0:07:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,比如初上市九十天的一百万销量\NLike a million in the first 90 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.83,0:07:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,-乔安娜  -之后每个月两万\N- Joanna... - 20,000 a month after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.40,0:07:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,-这都是预测  -我求你了\N- Look. Those are the forecasts. - I'm begging...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.11,0:07:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的专业\NThis is my field.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.88,0:07:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我求你控制好自己的期望\NI'm begging you to manage expectations out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.37,0:07:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是追求高期望\NI'm fanning expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.45,0:07:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我们初上市九十天卖不了一百万台\NWe're not gonna sell a million in the first 90 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.92,0:07:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人  每个人  每个人\NEveryone, everyone, everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.50,0:07:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都在等着Mac\Neveryone is waiting for the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.74,0:07:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,也许吧\NMaybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.97,0:07:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,但是当他们发现定价高达2495美元\NBut what happens when they find out that for 2,495,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.88,0:07:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,而你无可奈可的时候会怎么样呢\Nthere's nothing you can do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.14,0:07:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,定价1500美元我们还是有竞争力的\NWe were competitive at $1,500,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.45,0:07:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦处理器你用摩托罗拉68000取代6809\Nbut once you replaced the Motorola 6809 with the 68000...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.35,0:08:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,那靠什么来支持菜单\NWhich is what supports menus,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.74,0:08:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,窗口  点击  高分辨率图像\Nwindows, point and click, high-res graphics...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.93,0:08:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  因为每个人都需要圆角矩形\NYeah, 'cause everyone needs rectangles with rounded corners.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.07,0:08:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,大巴车跟头等舱同时降落在跑道上\NCoach lands on the runway at the exact same time as first class.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.28,0:08:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你这话我完全听不懂\NI don't have the first fucking idea what that means,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.52,0:08:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,但定价就是这样达到2500美元的\Nbut this is how it got to $2,500,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.86,0:08:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,跟个人电脑的价格差不多\Nwhich is the price point on the PC,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.17,0:08:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,个人电脑还能做更多事\Nwhich can do a lot more!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.17,0:08:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,谁会想要个人电脑  哪个傻瓜会想\NWho's gonna want a PC? What idiot is gonna want...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.34,0:08:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我想告诉你\NIf I wanna tell you there's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你衬衫上有块污渍  我会指着它\Na spot on your shirt, I point to the spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.02,0:08:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,而不说是在领子下方十四厘米\NI don't say there's a spot 14 centimeters down from the collar
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.74,0:08:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,第二个纽扣右边三厘米处\Nand three centimeters to the right of the second button
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.58,0:08:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,同时我还在想苏打水的命令是什么\Nwhile I try to remember what the command is for club soda.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.82,0:08:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是人脑的运行方式\NThat's not how a person's mind works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.85,0:08:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是为了简化使用\NIf the goal was ease of use,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.21,0:08:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,也许你就应该给它一些记忆存储\Nmaybe you should've given it some memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.70,0:08:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以抱怨记忆存储或者是价格\NYou can complain about memory or you can complain about price,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.47,0:08:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,但你不能同时抱怨它们\Nbut you can't do both at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.54,0:08:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,记忆存储就是烧钱\NMemory is what costs money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.68,0:08:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我很高兴你现在告诉我对Mac的看法\NI'm glad you're telling me your feelings about the Mac now
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.07,0:08:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们还有一个半小时\Nbecause we have a half hour left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.60,0:08:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以重新设计\NWe can redesign it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.35,0:09:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是让你控制好自己的期望\NI'm just asking you to manage expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.75,0:09:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,想想看人们见到它的表情\NLook at their faces when they see what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.90,0:09:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他们不会知道看到的是什么\NThey won't know what they're looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.35,0:09:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,或者为什么会喜欢\Nor why they like it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.32,0:09:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们知道自己想要它\Nbut they'll know they want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.80,0:09:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,并不会马上就这样\NNot instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.76,0:09:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,当人们听到《春之祭》的时候\NWhen people heard Rite of Spring,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.81,0:09:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他们把凳子都扔出剧院了\Nthey tore the chairs out of the theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.12,0:09:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,也没有买唱片\NThey didn't buy the record.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.63,0:09:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,《春之祭》恰好是上个世纪最具革命性\NRite of Spring happens to be the most revolutionary
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.38,0:09:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,和刺激性的交响乐\Nand provocative symphony of the last century.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.10,0:09:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,芭蕾  它是芭蕾舞\NBallet. It was a ballet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.22,0:09:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,但是伊戈尔·斯特拉文斯基也没说\NBut Igor Stravinsky didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.55,0:09:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,他一个月要卖两万张\Nsay he was gonna sell 20,000 units a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.69,0:09:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道为什么要说斯特拉温斯基\NI don't know why we're talking about Stravinsky
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.74,0:09:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我关心的是\Nwhen what I care about is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.05,0:09:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,丹·科特克在《时代》杂志上鸡奸了我\NDan Kottke sodomizing me in Time magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.41,0:09:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,很显然...\NLook. Obviously...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.31,0:09:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我这样跟你说吧\NLet me say this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,很显然  丹尼尔根本不觉得自己有错\NObviously, Daniel didn't think he was doing anything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.47,0:09:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,-对《时代》爆这种料吗  -没错\N- By talking to Time about it? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.83,0:09:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我不懂你什么意思\NI don't know what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.01,0:09:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你说  你告诉我这件事的时候\NYou said, when you told me the story...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.70,0:09:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你说你跟丹说\NYou said you said to Dan,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.73,0:09:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"《时代》杂志有没有问你\N"Did Time magazine ask you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.06,0:09:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我是不是有个叫丽萨的女儿"\Nif I had a daughter named Lisa?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.73,0:09:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,丹说"有"\NAnd Dan said, "Yeah."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.86,0:10:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我要说的是他回答你的话干脆又诚实\NMy point was that he answered you simply and honestly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.15,0:10:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他根本不觉得自己做错了什么\Nbecause he didn't think he'd done anything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.51,0:10:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,乔安娜  除了我根本没有一个女儿叫丽萨\NExcept, Joanna... Except I don't have a daughter named Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.62,0:10:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,现在这个故事变成\NAnd this story is now about
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.87,0:10:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我是如何否认父亲身份还去验血的\Nhow I'm denying paternity and took a blood test.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.21,0:10:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,所以这张图是...\NAnd that's why there's a picture of...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.58,0:10:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,不知道他妈的什么鬼东西\NI don't know what the fuck that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.55,0:10:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}《时代》年度机器
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.42,0:10:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(269.25,64)}《时代》年度机器
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.55,0:10:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}计算机时代来临
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.42,0:10:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(224.25,129)}计算机时代来临
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.55,0:10:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,所以封面上是台个人电脑\NThat's why there's a picture of a PC on the cover
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.83,0:10:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是我跟Mac\Ninstead of a picture of me and the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.59,0:10:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道该说什么了\NI don't know what to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.95,0:10:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,本来我应该是《时代》杂志的年度人物\NI was supposed to be Time magazine's Man of the Year.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.42,0:10:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,结果丹·科特克横空出世\NAnd then Dan Kottke was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.16,0:10:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,-那个...  -什么\N- Well... - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.34,0:10:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,-她在等你  -谁\N- She's waiting for you. - Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.23,0:10:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-克里斯安  -布伦南?\N- Chrisann. - Brennan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.27,0:10:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,她们在外面的走廊里\NThey're out in the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.62,0:10:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,她们从早上七点开始\NThey've been sitting in the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.54,0:10:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,就坐在观众席的后面\Nback of the auditorium since 7:00 this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.05,0:10:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在不见克里斯安\NI'm not having a session with Chrisann right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.60,0:10:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我们邀请了335位记者来参加发布会\NWe issued 335 press credentials for the launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.14,0:10:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫  你要是惹怒了克里斯安\NSteve, you piss off Chrisann,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.11,0:11:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,她可以站在大厅接受335家采访\Nshe's gonna stand in the lobby and give 335 interviews,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.44,0:11:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,而你  将会渴望跟丹·科特克的平静生活\Nand you, pal, will be longing for the halcyon days of Dan Kottke.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.35,0:11:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我去把这事解决了\NLet me get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.16,0:11:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,但你别走  待在这儿\NBut don't leave. You're gonna stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.55,0:11:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,什么  不行  我不干\NWhat? No. I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.24,0:11:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,不行  你在这儿\NNo. There's less of a chance
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.37,0:11:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,场面混乱的可能性更小\Nof a scene if you stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.76,0:11:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,她会冷静一些\NShe'll be cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.35,0:11:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这事非常私人...\NI find all this excruciatingly personal and-and...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.62,0:11:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我不要待在这儿\NI-I'm... I'm not staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.47,0:11:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,不行  拜托了\NNo. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.08,0:11:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想跟克里斯安处独处一室\NI don't wanna be in a room alone with Chrisann.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.46,0:11:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你陪我\NThis is me and you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.73,0:11:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\NFine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.91,0:11:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.85,0:11:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,真是意外\NThis is a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.88,0:11:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,进来吧\NWhy don't you come on in?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.57,0:12:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.09,0:12:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你也来吗\NYou coming too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.63,0:12:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,当然  我不会留她在走廊上的\NYes, I'm not gonna leave her in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.44,0:12:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧  这走廊挺安全的  不过算了\NOkay. It's a safe hallway, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.25,0:12:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,还记得乔安娜·霍夫曼吗\NYou remember Joanna Hoffman?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.66,0:12:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,她是Mac的市场部主管\NShe's the head of marketing for the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.35,0:12:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴见到你\NGood to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.14,0:12:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴见到你  丽萨  你好\NNice to see you. Hello, Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.69,0:12:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我们见过  你还告诉我\NWe've met before, and you told me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你喜欢我说话的方式\Nyou like the way I talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.69,0:12:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我听到过的最喜欢的话了\Nand that was my favorite thing anyone's ever said to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.97,0:12:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-你是波兰人吗  -是的\N- You're from Poland. - Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.20,0:12:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-你知道它在哪儿吗  -地球最上面\N- Do you know where that is? - The top of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.37,0:12:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你说的是北极\NI think you're thinking of the North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.96,0:12:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我们时间有点紧\NWell, we're a little pressed for time, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.93,0:12:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,你们慢慢聊  我先走了\NI'll leave you guys alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.11,0:12:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么要走  不是刚说好\NWhy do you wanna leave when you just said...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.89,0:12:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我要去看看赫茨菲尔德\NI'm gonna check in with Hertzfeld.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.02,0:12:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要让一台电脑跟大家问好\NWe're trying to get a computer to say hello,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.31,0:12:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,但它现在太害羞了\Nbut right now it's being very shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.02,0:12:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你能来帮帮我吗  可以吗\NWould you come help me? Is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.50,0:12:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,好\NSure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.57,0:12:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.97,0:12:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我爸爸用我的名字命名了一台电脑\NMy dad named a computer after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.73,0:12:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是你的...\NI'm not your...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.35,0:13:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,其实  你知道这有多巧吗  丽萨\NActually, do you know what a coincidence is, Lisa?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.12,0:13:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,不知道\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.45,0:13:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像你遇到了一个人\NLike if you met someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.37,0:13:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你和她交朋友  发现她也叫丽萨\NYou made a new friend and her name was Lisa too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.60,0:13:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这样的巧合\NThat would be a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.63,0:13:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"丽萨"是"本地集成系统架构"的缩写\N"Lisa" stands for "Local Integrated Systems Architecture."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.57,0:13:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,L-I-S-A\NL-I-S-A.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.75,0:13:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,只是个巧合\NIt's a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.71,0:13:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-你说完了  -对\N- You about done? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.74,0:13:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,好\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.49,0:13:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧  我们去让那台电脑问好\NCome. Let's make that computer say hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.28,0:13:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,去吧  丽萨\NGo ahead, Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,那么  是正相反吗\NSo it was the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.84,0:13:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我是以那台电脑命名的\NI was named after the computer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.47,0:13:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,都不是  只是个巧合\NNothing was named after anybody. It's a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.43,0:13:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,走吧\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.34,0:13:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么回事\NWhat's the matter with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.23,0:13:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么回事  为什么要告诉她这些事\NWhat's the matter with you? Why are you telling her these things?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.42,0:13:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么还跟她说我是她爸爸\NWhy are you still telling her I'm her father?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.38,0:14:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,-是法官告诉她的  -不  不是\N- A judge told her you're her father. - No, he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.39,0:14:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你好大的胆子  竟然跟《时代》杂志说\NWhere the hell do you get off telling Time magazine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.14,0:14:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我和28%的美国男人都睡过\NI've slept with 28 percent of the men in America?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.32,0:14:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-我不是...  -你哪儿来的胆子\N- That's not... - Where do you get off?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.15,0:14:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我根本不是那么说的\NThat's not remotely what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.50,0:14:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,就在这儿\NIt's right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.12,0:14:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,首先  关于《时代》杂志  我要跟你说\NFirst of all, can I tell you something about Time magazine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.29,0:14:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,它就是个训练刺客的机构\NI believe it's a training facility for paid assassins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.51,0:14:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,上面的原话是"乔布斯坚称"\N"Jobs insists"... I am quoting...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.26,0:14:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我没编造数据\NI didn't invent math.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"美国男性人口的\N"...twenty-eight percent
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.26,0:14:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,百分之二十八\Nof the male population of the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.32,0:14:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,都可能是孩子的父亲"\Ncould be the father."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.56,0:14:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是说你跟28%的美国男人睡过\NI wasn't saying you've slept with 28% of American men.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.67,0:14:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我是用一种算法  根据血检结果\NI was using an algorithm based on the blood test
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.81,0:14:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,有94.1%的可能性我是她父亲\Nwhich said there was a 94.1% chance that I'm the father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.30,0:14:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你这是公然地把我描绘成荡妇\NYou're trying to publicly paint me as a slut and a whore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.93,0:14:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,相信我  我不想公然对你做任何事\NBelieve me, I'm not trying to publicly do anything with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.18,0:14:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,《时代》有二百万读者  我怎么...\NTwo million people read Time. How am I supposed...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.43,0:14:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,要是他们让我上封面  读者会更多\NIt would be more if they put me on the cover,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.78,0:14:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,但丹·科特克却狠捅了我一刀\Nbut Dan Kottke decided to kidney-punch me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.33,0:14:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我昨天申请了福利救济\NI applied for welfare yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.25,0:14:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,-你说什么  -你好\N- I'm sorry? - Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.08,0:14:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我说我昨天申请了福利救济\NI said I applied for welfare yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.06,0:14:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,《时代》的文章说\NThe Time article said
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.94,0:15:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你的苹果公司股票价值四亿四千一百万美元\Nyour Apple stock was worth $441 million,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.60,0:15:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我想问问你对此感受如何\Nand I wanted to ask you how you felt about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.64,0:15:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得苹果公司的股票价值被大大低估了\NWell, I feel like Apple stock has been dramatically undervalued.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.03,0:15:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,这时正是入股的好时候\NThis would be a good time to get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.02,0:15:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你的女儿和她母亲...\NYour daughter and her mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.47,0:15:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,-克里斯安...  -正在接受福利救济\N- Chrisann... - are on welfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.41,0:15:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我们住在门罗公园的窝棚里\NWe're living in a hovel in Menlo Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.96,0:15:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我们交不起采暖费\NWe can't pay the heating bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.66,0:15:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,她穿着大衣睡觉\NShe sleeps in a parka.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.07,0:15:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,-你女儿...  -她不是我女儿\N- Your daughter... - She's not my daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.42,0:15:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,因为  据《时代》杂志报道\NBecause, as reported by Time magazine,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.45,0:15:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,-我跟28%的美国男人睡过吗  -不\N- I've slept with 28% of the men in America? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.37,0:15:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,恰好在丽萨出生九个月前  跟他们都睡过\NAll of them, exactly nine months before Lisa was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.44,0:15:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪在等你\NI've got Andy here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.02,0:15:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,失陪一下\NExcuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.82,0:15:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,好了吗\NWe're there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.56,0:16:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,-克里斯  -安迪\N- Hey, Chris. - Hey, Andy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.50,0:16:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-近来如何  -很糟糕\N- How are you doin'? - Terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.30,0:16:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你们叙上旧了\NYou guys caught up now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.57,0:16:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,原谅我  我得和朋友打招呼\NExcuse me for saying hello to my friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.05,0:16:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他觉得你是个混蛋\Nwho thinks you're a dick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.12,0:16:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,-我没觉得你是...  -修好了吗\N- I don't think you're a... - We're there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.34,0:16:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-没有  修好的几率是六分之一  -该死\N- No. It's got a one-in-six chance of working. - God damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.70,0:16:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我们又不是戴顿纳赛车场的维修员\NWell, we're not a pit crew at Daytona.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.83,0:16:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,不可能几秒钟就把它修好\NThis can't be fixed in seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.52,0:16:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,不是几秒钟  你们本有三周时间\NYou didn't have seconds. You had three weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.28,0:16:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,创世才用了一周时间而已\NThe universe was created in a third of that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.45,0:16:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,改天你得告诉我们你是怎么做到的\NWell, someday you'll have to tell us how you did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.15,0:16:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我打算这样做\NHere's what I'm gonna do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.60,0:16:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我会宣布\NI'm gonna announce the names
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.65,0:16:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,发布会演示的每一位设计者的名字\Nof everyone who designed the launch demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.97,0:16:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我要介绍每一个人  让他们起立致意\NI'm gonna introduce everyone and ask them to stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.75,0:16:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,苏珊·凯尔设计了图标\NThe bag was designed by Susan Kare.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.96,0:16:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫·卡普斯设计了\NThe Macintosh font that's scrolling
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.49,0:16:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,在屏幕上滚动的麦金塔字体\Nacross the screen was designed by Steve Capps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.95,0:16:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,布鲁斯·霍恩设计了星夜和空中文字\NThe starry night and skywriting was Bruce Horn.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.95,0:16:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,MacPaint和MacWrite是艾丽斯\NMacPaint, MacWrite, Alice,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.05,0:16:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至计算器也要介绍\Ndown to the calculator.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.78,0:16:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我要介绍安迪·赫茨菲尔德\NAnd then I'm gonna say the voice demo that didn't work
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.99,0:16:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,设计了无效的语音演示\Nwas designed by Andy Hertzfeld.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.74,0:17:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-史蒂夫...  -你有六分之五的几率\N- Steve... - Five-in-six is your chance of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.72,0:17:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,在第一轮俄罗斯轮盘赌中活下来\Nsurviving the first round of Russian roulette,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.39,0:17:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,你却选择了那六分之一\Nand you've reversed those odds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.37,0:17:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,除非你想在朋友\NSo unless you wanna be disgraced in front of your friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.57,0:17:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,家人  同事  股东和媒体面前丢脸\Nfamily, colleagues, stockholders and the press,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.96,0:17:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,换成我  我不会在这儿争辩\NI wouldn't stand here arguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.69,0:17:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我会努力把更多子弹从枪里弄出来\NI'd go try and get some more bullets out of the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.12,0:17:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,快去干  安迪\NDo it, Andy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,等等  你\NStop. You.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.32,0:17:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,-你穿几码的衬衫  -我\N- What size shirt do you wear? - Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.19,0:17:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,有人知道他穿几码的衬衫吗\NDoes anyone know what size shirt he wears?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.47,0:17:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我穿几码的衬衫\NWhat size shirt I wear?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.77,0:17:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,有人知道离得最近的精神病医生在哪儿吗\NDoes anyone know where the closest psychiatrist is?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.96,0:17:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,软盘能装进口袋里\NThe disk fits in your pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.86,0:17:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要件带胸前口袋的衬衫\NI need a shirt with a breast pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.22,0:17:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这样在台上就能把它拿出来\NI can take it out onstage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.56,0:17:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-衬衫  -软盘\N- A shirt? - The disk!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.04,0:17:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要件合身的带胸前口袋的白衬衫\NI need a white shirt in my size with a breast pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.00,0:17:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  哪家商店8点45就营业的\NYes. Which one of the no stores that are open at 8:45
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.22,0:17:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你想让我派人\Ndo you want me to have
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.89,0:17:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,在15分钟之内跑个来回吗\Nsomeone run to and return from in 15 minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.77,0:17:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,去大厅\NGo out in the lobby,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.09,0:17:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,找个跟我身材相当的穿着白衬衫的人\Nfind someone my size who's wearing a white shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.70,0:17:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉他我用台电脑换白衬衫\NTell them I'll trade them for a free computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.83,0:18:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他们可以穿我的衬衫\Nand they get to keep my shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.79,0:18:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,必须是白色的吗  蓝色的行吗\NDoes it have to be a white shirt? Is blue okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.05,0:18:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,不行  Mac是米黄色的  我也是\NNo. The Mac is beige, I'm beige,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.39,0:18:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,软盘是蓝色的  衬衫必须是白色的\Nthe disk is blue, the shirt has to be white.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.12,0:18:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪\NAndy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.08,0:18:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你好  我是麦金塔\NHello, I'm Macintosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.00,0:18:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,把安迪·赫茨菲尔德的脑袋给我拿过来\NBring me the head of Andy Hertzfeld.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.39,0:18:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我努力让它说"你好"  但它太害羞了\NI tried to get it to say hello, but it's shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.32,0:18:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.78,0:18:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,就是它吗\NSo that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.53,0:18:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,就是它\NThat's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.11,0:18:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我不明白\NI don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.15,0:18:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.83,0:18:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,人们用它做什么\NWhat are people going to do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.18,0:18:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨  你多大了\NLisa, how old are you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.22,0:18:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,-你知道她多大了  -你多大了  丽萨\N- You know how old she is. - How old are you, Lisa?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.29,0:18:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,五岁\NFive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.21,0:19:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,来这儿坐会儿\NCome sit here for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.45,0:19:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道这是什么吗\NDo you know what this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.44,0:19:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-是台电脑  -是台电脑\N- It's a computer. - It's a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.48,0:19:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我能不能借用下你的手\NCan I borrow your hand for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.41,0:19:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,对准那个箭头  单击\NPoint that arrow and click.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.01,0:19:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你不必非得跟它玩  但如果你想也可以\NYou don't have to, but if you want, you can play with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.06,0:19:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你不会把它弄坏的\NNothing you can do will break it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.38,0:19:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,所以随便做什么都行\Nso just do whatever you want with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.79,0:19:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你在干什么\NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.45,0:19:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我在还给你法院要求我付给你的钱数\NI'm paying you exactly what the court ordered me to pay you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.59,0:19:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,每月385美元\N$385 a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.61,0:19:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,付这么多可不是我决定的\NI'm not the one who decided on that amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.41,0:19:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我是问你感觉如何\NAnd I'm asking you how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你觉得可以的话\NIf you feel all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.18,0:19:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你觉得给你女儿\NIf it feels all right
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.04,0:19:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,-可以的话... -她不是我...\N- to you that your daughter... - She's not my...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.14,0:19:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你的女儿和她母亲正在接受福利救济\NThat your daughter and her mother are on welfare
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.40,0:19:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,而你因为它  有四亿四千一百万美元身家\Nwhile you're worth $441 million for making that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.26,0:19:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以自豪地说\NI'm proud to say
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.25,0:19:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,苹果公司向预算不足的学校捐赠电脑\NApple donates computers to underfunded schools,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.81,0:19:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,-而且我们会捐更多的Mac  -什么\N- and we'll be doing more of the same with the Mac... - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.69,0:19:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,苹果公司向学校捐赠价值数百万元的电脑\NApple donates millions of dollars' worth of computers to schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.91,0:19:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,那和我们有什么关系\NWhat does that have to do with...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.00,0:20:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,想象一下  一个贫困的孩子\NImagine an underprivileged kid
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.71,0:20:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,24小时都有他最爱的老师的陪伴\Nthat has their favorite teacher with them 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.86,0:20:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我们再过几分钟就能做到了\NWe're minutes away from being able to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.92,0:20:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得  这算是回答了我的问题吗\NIn your head, was that an answer to my question?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.75,0:20:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,再跟我说一遍问题\NTell me the question again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.09,0:20:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我并非唯一一个因子女抚养费起诉你的人\NI wasn't the one who sued you for child support.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.31,0:20:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,不  让...\NNo, let...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.41,0:20:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,圣马提奥县也起诉你了\NSan Mateo County sued you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.62,0:20:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,不  让我解释下发生了什么\NNo, let me explain what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.57,0:20:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我现在有的是时间\N'cause I have plenty of time right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.20,0:20:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉打扰  有人找你\NExcuse me. You have a visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.16,0:20:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,只是想祝你好运  克里斯安\NJust wanted to say good luck. Hey, Chrisann.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.64,0:20:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,-沃兹  -等一下\N- Hello, Woz. - Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,-只是想祝你好运  -谢谢  也祝你好运\N- Just wanted to say good luck. - Thanks. You too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.69,0:20:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,-今早意义重大  -对\N- It's a big morning. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.89,0:20:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该看看外面的观众\NYou should see this crowd out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.75,0:20:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,这群观众  就好像...\NThis crowd, it's like, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.68,0:20:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我不能等你想到合适的比喻了  哥们\NI can't really wait for you to come up with a metaphor, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.49,0:20:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,-我想让你帮个忙  -什么忙\N- Yeah. So, listen, I want to ask you a favor. - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.10,0:20:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你能否在发言时\NCan you acknowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.70,0:20:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,-向Apple Ⅱ团队致谢  -不能\N- the Apple II team in your remarks? - I cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.26,0:20:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,就致个谢而已\NJust an acknowledgement.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.72,0:20:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,让他们站起来\NHave them stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.74,0:20:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要发布的是Mac\NWe're launching the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.01,0:20:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这样会提升士气\NIt'd be a morale booster.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.80,0:20:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,提一下就行  这样他们也能赢得掌声\NJust a mention so they could get a round of applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.24,0:21:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,-提一下吧  -我们能不能等会儿再谈\N- Just a mention. - Can we stick a pin in this for a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.07,0:21:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,-好  -谢谢\N- Sure. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.38,0:21:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,就提一下并向他们致谢就行\NJust talking about an acknowledgement for the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.78,0:21:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,克里斯安在里面等我  我马上回来\NI've got Chrisann in there. I'll see you in a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.19,0:21:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,好\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.08,0:21:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,这样\NThat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.18,0:21:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.24,0:21:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你问我人们用它做什么\NYou asked me what people are gonna do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.90,0:21:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会这样做\NThey're gonna do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.99,0:21:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,是一位工程师的\NOne of the engineers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.07,0:21:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.38,0:21:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你喜欢吗\NDo you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.22,0:21:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你说什么\NI'm sorry?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.40,0:21:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这是抽象画\NIt's an abstract.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.95,0:21:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你用了MacPaint\NYou used MacPaint.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.70,0:21:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,同时按下那个键和S键\NPush that key and the "S" at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.21,0:21:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}保存               取消
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.25,0:21:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}保存文件为
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.25,0:21:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}未命名
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.25,0:21:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,输入你的名字\NNow type your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.67,0:22:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}丽萨
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.84,0:22:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(183,152)}丽萨·布伦南
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.77,0:22:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道哪个按钮是"保存"吗\NDo you know which box says "Save"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.03,0:22:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,对了  单击它吧\NRight. Go ahead and click on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.86,0:22:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我会给你打点钱\NI'll put some money in your account
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.75,0:22:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,给你买个离好学校近的新房子\Nand buy you a new house, someplace near a decent school.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.74,0:22:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.74,0:22:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,沃兹想跟你说句话\NWoz wants a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.73,0:22:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,斯卡利也在找你\NAnd Sculley's asking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.27,0:22:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们说完了\NWe're done?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.12,0:22:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你能不能再教我点别的\NCould you teach me more things?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.35,0:22:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,关于电脑的\NOn the computer?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.61,0:22:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨  到走廊去等我\NLisa, wait for me in the hall, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.92,0:22:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在走廊里把外套穿上\NYou can put your coat on in the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.59,0:22:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,再见  丽萨\NBye, Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.54,0:22:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,-再见  -丽萨  快去走廊\N- Bye. - Lisa, in the hall. Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.65,0:23:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我想知道  你说要给我打些钱\NI wanna know, when you say you're gonna put money in my account,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.92,0:23:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,究竟打多少\Nhow much we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.90,0:23:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,今天是教学日  她得去学校\NIt's a school day. She needs to be in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.44,0:23:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我会满足你的一切需求\NI'm gonna give you whatever you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.83,0:23:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,沃兹想让我对Apple Ⅱ团队致谢\NWoz wants me to acknowledge the Apple II team.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.02,0:23:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你肯定能看出来  她长得像你\NYou must be able to see that she looks like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想冒犯沃兹\NI don't want to insult Woz.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.33,0:23:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,只是觉得这是在错误的时间\NI just think it's backward-looking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.75,0:23:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,回顾过去\Nat exactly the wrong moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.51,0:23:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你听见我说的了\NI know you heard what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.22,0:23:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  乔安娜\NI heard what you said, Joanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.56,0:23:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,只是我们就要做这件事了\NIt's just we're about to do this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.95,0:23:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,9点41分  世界将被永久性地改变\N941, the planet's gonna shift on its axis nigh and forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.07,0:23:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,二十世纪最重要的两件大事\NTwo most significant events of the 20th century:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.57,0:23:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,盟军赢得二战胜利和今天这件事\Nthe Allies win the war and this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.61,0:23:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,这件事\NThis.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.96,0:23:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你现在不应该斥责我不是个好父亲\NSo maybe right now isn't the very best time to scold me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.25,0:24:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,那也不是我孩子\Nfor not being a better father to a kid who's not my kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.32,0:24:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,-检测结果表明我  -我不关心检测结果\N- The test said I... - I don't care what the test said.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.40,0:24:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我不关心94.1%\NI don't care about 94.1%
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.67,0:24:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,或是你用疯狂的算法得出28%的美国男人\Nor the insane algorithm you used to get to 28% of American men.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.47,0:24:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,给她买个新房子  我会给她钱的\NBuying her a new house. I'm giving her money.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.36,0:24:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,有个小女孩相信你是她父亲\NThere's a small girl who believes you're her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.95,0:24:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,就这样  要考虑的只有这些\NThat's all. That's all the math there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.40,0:24:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,她相信  你要怎么办\NShe believes it. What are you gonna do about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.28,0:24:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝派他唯一的儿子去完成自杀任务\NGod sent his only son on a suicide mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.92,0:24:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但无论如何我们都爱他  因为他种了树\Nbut we like him anyway because he made trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.96,0:24:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会在初上市九十天内卖掉一百万台\NWe're gonna sell a million units in the first 90 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.89,0:24:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,之后每个月卖两万台\N20,000 a month after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.73,0:24:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你能不能让我喘口气  霍夫曼女士\NSo maybe you could give me a break, Ms. Hoffman?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.42,0:25:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,沃兹\NWoz.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.24,0:25:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,自动售货机里的东西都是致命的\NThere's nothing in that vending machine that won't kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.83,0:25:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,-看看而已  -我们去散散步吧\N- Just browsing. - Let's take a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.31,0:25:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,-有些事我想告诉你  -说吧\N- Can I tell you something? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.39,0:25:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,在毛伊岛会议之后\NAfter the meeting in Maui,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.52,0:25:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Ⅱ团队生气沮丧又失望\Nthe Apple II team was upset and angry and down.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.65,0:25:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道为什么吗\NDo you know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.56,0:25:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我一次都没提过他们吗\NBecause the Apple II wasn't mentioned even once?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.11,0:25:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Ⅱ一次都没被提到...\NThe Apple II wasn't mentioned ev...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.57,0:25:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,对  就是这样  你说得对\NYes, that's it. You have it. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.43,0:25:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,那可不是粗心大意\NThat wasn't an oversight.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.34,0:25:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他们知道的  他们知道并非粗心大意\NThey know that. They know it wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.91,0:25:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想小题大做...\NI don't wanna make a big deal out of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.51,0:25:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,那完全在你的能力范围之内\NThat's entirely within your power.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.29,0:25:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Ⅱ是...\NThe Apple II is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.64,0:25:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Ⅱ就是从前那样\NThe Apple II is what was, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.10,0:25:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,七年以来\NThe Apple II is what pays
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.15,0:26:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,支撑这儿的都是Apple Ⅱ\Nthe bills around here and has for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.58,0:26:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你让这群人难堪\NAnd if you embarrass these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.95,0:26:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你就会面对公司的人才流失  哥们\Nyou are going to see a brain drain at this company, my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.06,0:26:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,是马库拉让你离开丽萨项目\NMarkkula took you off the Lisa,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.57,0:26:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,不是他们也不是我  所以别怨...\Nnot them and not me, so don't blame...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.42,0:26:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,马库拉让我离开丽萨项目是因为\NMarkkula took me off the Lisa because
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.91,0:26:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,他的宗教信仰不能容忍把它做到完美\Nof his strong religious objection to making it good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.34,0:26:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我满足了你关于Apple Ⅱ的一切要求\NNow I gave you everything you wanted on the Apple II.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.26,0:26:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你不多提点要求吗\NYou don't ask for a lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.78,0:26:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你一次争辩都没输过\NThere wasn't a single fight you lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.04,0:26:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你承认Apple Ⅱ成功\NDo you concede the slots are
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.22,0:26:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,是因为插槽吗\Nthe reason for the success of the Apple II?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.43,0:26:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,-我们别继续讨论插槽了  -我有话说\N- We can't still be talking about the slots. - I have a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.55,0:26:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,都七年了  你还在纠结插槽\NIt's been seven years. You're still doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.00,0:26:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你还在谈插槽\NYou're talking about the slots.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.96,0:26:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你有点不对劲\NThere's something wrong with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.43,0:26:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,这场争论在车库里就开始了\NThis argument started in the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.64,0:26:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你在说什么  为什么只要两个插槽\NWhat are you talking about? Why would you only want two slots?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.58,0:26:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,打印机和调制解调器\NA printer and a modem.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.59,0:26:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有八个插槽  你...\NWith eight slots, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.35,0:26:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,如果能增加到八个插槽  那可真是件大事\NThis is a huge deal that we were able to add eight slots.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.35,0:26:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这种设计  但我们不会这么做\NI appreciate the engineering, but it's not what we're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.03,0:26:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,-谢天谢地我赢得了争论  -沃兹\N- And thank God I won that argument... - Woz.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.09,0:26:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,因为人们就喜欢这台机器的开放系统\NBecause the open system is what people love about the machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.52,0:26:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,所以不管过去还是现在人们都买它\Nand it's why it sold and still sells.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.54,0:26:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,开放性系统  我们不做开放性系统\NAn open system. We're not doing an open system.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.91,0:26:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我们当然要做了  人们就想要开放性系统\NOf course we are. That's what people want,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.39,0:26:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Ⅱ的重大突破就在于...\Nand the breakthrough on the Apple II...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.98,0:26:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,除非你给他们展示\NPeople don't know what they want
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.04,0:26:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,否则人们不知道自己想要什么\Nuntil you show it to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.68,0:27:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,真正的用户想要个性化\NSerious users want to customize.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.42,0:27:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他们想要改变  想要自己鼓捣\NThey wanna modify. They wanna jack it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.51,0:27:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,他们想让像我这样的硬件工程师\NThey want hardware engineers
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.57,0:27:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,提高机器的性能  明白吗\Nlike me to expand its capabilities, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.84,0:27:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,音乐键盘  更好的声卡\NKeyboards for music, better sound board,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.79,0:27:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,更好的显卡  性能更佳的存储\Nbetter display boards, improved memory cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.83,0:27:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,所以现在才有三千人聚集于此\NAnd it's why there are 3,000 people here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.63,0:27:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,插槽让Apple Ⅱ能够运行\NThe slots are what allowed the Apple II to run,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.22,0:27:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,举个例子  VisiCalc这样的软件\Nfor just one example, VisiCalc,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.95,0:27:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,据我估计  光靠这一点\Nwhich from my guess single-handedly
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.33,0:27:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就卖了二十万到三十万台机器\Nsold between 200,000 and 300,000 machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.38,0:27:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,-他们想要更多插槽  -他们没有表决权\N- They want slots. - They don't get a vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.10,0:27:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,迪伦写下《栖身之处》时\NWhen Dylan wrote "Shelter from the Storm,"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.85,0:27:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8} 图为正在拍摄宣传片的鲍勃·迪伦
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.55,0:27:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,也没求大家帮他创作歌词\Nhe didn't ask people to contribute to the lyrics.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.58,0:27:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,话剧也不会为了能让编剧问观众\NPlays don't stop so the playwright can ask the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.79,0:27:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,接下来他们想看什么而停止\Nwhat scene they'd like to see next.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.21,0:27:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,-画家...  -爱好者...\N- Painters... - Hobbyists...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.99,0:27:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在正濒于...  爱好者\NWe're on the verge of a tectonic... Hobbyists?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.70,0:27:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,打印机和调制解调器  两个插槽\NA printer and a modem. Two slots.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.07,0:27:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我欣赏Apple Ⅱ团队\NThe Apple II team has my affection,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.99,0:27:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但我不会在Mac发布会上赞颂七年的旧产品\Nbut I'm not loving up a seven-year-old product at the Mac launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.18,0:27:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-电脑又不是画  -去你的\N- Computers aren't paintings. - Fuck you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.74,0:27:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你每次这么说我都会说\NI'm gonna say "Fuck you"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.72,0:27:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"去你的吧"  一直到你死了或者不说了\Nevery time you say that until you either die or stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.68,0:27:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-史蒂夫...  -你试试\N- Steve... - Try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.93,0:27:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,-史蒂夫  -说\N- Steve. - Say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.81,0:27:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,-电脑不是画  -去你的吧\N- Computers aren't paintings. - Fuck you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.95,0:28:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,它们是画  我想要的就是封闭性系统\NYes, they are, and what I want is a closed system.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.00,0:28:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,端对端控制  与其他完全不兼容\NEnd-to-end control. Completely incompatible with anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.08,0:28:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,电脑不应该有人类的缺陷\NComputers aren't supposed to have human flaws.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.67,0:28:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会按你的想法设计这款电脑的\NI'm not going to build this one with yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.74,0:28:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫\NSteve!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.17,0:28:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你好啊\NHey.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.11,0:28:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,今天属于麦金塔\NToday is about the Macintosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.08,0:28:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,而麦金塔是我的作品\NAnd the Mac is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.46,0:28:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,-我把它归功于你  -谢谢\N- I give you that. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.94,0:28:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,都归功于你\NI give you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.69,0:28:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,只要你公开致谢Apple Ⅱ团队\NJust publicly acknowledge the Apple II team
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.54,0:28:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这是应该做的\N'cause it's the right thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.19,0:28:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,马上我们就能知道\NWe'll know soon enough
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.55,0:28:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是达芬奇般的绝世天才还是自以为是\Nif you are Leonardo da Vinci or just think you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.80,0:28:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,但与此同时  最好...\Nbut in the meantime, it would be great...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.97,0:28:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,与此同时  Apple Ⅱ的时代结束了\NIn the meantime, the Apple II is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.99,0:28:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,七年了  很了不起\NSeven years. It was a great run.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.95,0:28:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该去大厅找你的座位坐下了\NYou should go out in the house and take your seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.58,0:28:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mac是杰夫·拉斯金的\NThe Mac is Jef Raskin's.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.34,0:28:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,说那句话\NSay it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.12,0:28:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-电脑不是...  -去你的\N- Computers aren't... - Fuck you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.47,0:28:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.22,0:29:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,五  六\NFive, six...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.25,0:29:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-好了吗  -我还需要点时间\N- We're there? - I need more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.03,0:29:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,-不行  -只要二十分钟\N- You can't have it. - 20 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.93,0:29:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,已经八点五十八了\NIt's 8:58.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.24,0:29:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以迟些开始\NWe can start late.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.31,0:29:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,听着  我们是电脑公司  不能起步晚了\NHear me. We're a computer company. We can't start late.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.64,0:29:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,-那我还有个主意  -什么\N- Then I have another idea. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.05,0:29:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,是个骗人而且几乎不道德的主意\NIt's deceptive and borderline unethical.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.03,0:29:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-你说  -它可以在512型号上运行\N- I'm listening. - It'll run on the 512.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.99,0:29:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,-你测试了吗  -是的\N- You tested it? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.98,0:29:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,等等  你要用512型号来做\NWait. You're gonna demo
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.90,0:29:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,128型号电脑的演示吗\Na 128 computer on a 512?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.77,0:29:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,没人知道的\NNobody's gonna know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.57,0:29:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,而你只觉得这几乎不道德吗\NAnd you think that's borderline unethical?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.92,0:29:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,那你告诉我还有什么选择\NName my other choices, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.06,0:29:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你得告诉我\NPlease. You have to tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.58,0:29:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么让它说你好如此重要\Nwhy it's so important for it to say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.75,0:29:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,因为好莱坞  他们把电脑妖魔化了\NHollywood. They made computers scary things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.76,0:29:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你看  这会让你想起一张友好的脸\NSee how this reminds you of a friendly face,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.73,0:29:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,那个软盘插口就像是在傻笑\Nthat the disk slot is a goofy grin?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.81,0:29:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,它是暖心而幽默的  它需要说你好\NIt's warm and it's playful and it needs to say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.06,0:29:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,它需要说你好是因为它能做到\NIt needs to say hello because it can.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.58,0:30:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我们没有在进行欺诈\NWe're not committing fraud.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.18,0:30:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,512型号在一年之内就会上市\NThe 512 is gonna ship in under a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.58,0:30:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你能让我别再听到你的东欧式反对了吗\NWill you absolve me of your Eastern European disapproval?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.34,0:30:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,2001年的电脑总是在说你好\NThe computer in 2001 said hello all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.88,0:30:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,但还是把我吓坏了\Nand it still scared the shit out of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.35,0:30:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,赦免我吧\NAbsolve me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.19,0:30:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,仅此一次\NJust for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.98,0:30:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,下不为例\NAnd just for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.54,0:30:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们\NLadies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.07,0:30:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,有请创始董事会成员迈克·马库拉\Nplease welcome founding board member Mike Markkula.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.66,0:30:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,好了  都准备好了\NAll right. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.13,0:30:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,去吸引全世界的注意吧  史蒂夫\NGo make a dent in the universe, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.91,0:30:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,过几小时见\NSee you in a couple hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.72,0:30:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我将为大家带来此次发布会的正式部分\NAnd I'm going to take us through the formal part of the meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.62,0:30:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你们想叫它法律部分也行\Nthe legal part, if you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.78,0:30:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,感谢上帝  骑士终于出现了\NThank merciful God. The cavalry's shown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.05,0:30:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我听说你今早比平时还糟糕\NI hear you've been worse than usual this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.28,0:30:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得不可能\NI didn't think that was possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.57,0:30:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我被派来做"史蒂夫耳语者"\NSo I've been dispatched as the "Steve Whisperer."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.07,0:31:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一瓶55年的玛尔戈红酒\NThis is a '55 Margaux.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.53,0:31:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,现在是早上九点\N9:00 in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.73,0:31:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,这可是55年的玛尔戈啊\NThis is a '55 Margaux.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.58,0:31:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,是我想多了还是你开始学我穿衣服了\NIs it my imagination or have you started to dress like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.66,0:31:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,让马库拉用季度报告开场不是好主意\NIt was a bad idea to have Markkula open with quarterly reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.74,0:31:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我们应该往观众身上浇水\NInstead we should have just dropped water on the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.71,0:31:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,像是从天花板泼下\NYou know, just big 10,000-gallon tanks of cold water,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.39,0:31:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,几箱三四万升的冷水\Ndropped from the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.51,0:31:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,给迈克在提词卡上省点钱\NSave Mike some money on index cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.27,0:31:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,-放轻松就行  -为什么\N- Oh, just relax. - Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.87,0:31:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道  没人问过我这问题\NI don't know. No one's ever asked me that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.44,0:31:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,干杯吧\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.82,0:31:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,你是唯一和我用同样的方式看世界的人\NYou're the only one who sees the world the same way I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.27,0:31:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,没人和你用同样的方式看世界\NNo one sees the world the same way you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.47,0:31:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我就像凯撒一样  约翰\NI'm like Julius Caesar, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.30,0:31:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,-我被强敌环绕  -你才没有\N- I'm surrounded by enemies. - No, you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.11,0:31:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-董事会  -董事会啊  他们支持你\N- The board... - Oh, the board. The board's behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.92,0:31:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,只因为你的关照他们才会这样的\NOnly because you see to it they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.44,0:31:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得这是个不错的董事会\NI think it's a good board,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.66,0:31:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果你想让我把他们一个个挤出去\Nbut if you want me to push them out one by one,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.57,0:31:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以谈谈\Nwe can talk about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.91,0:31:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我想让你一次性把他们都推出去\NI want you to push them out all at once...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.04,0:32:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,如果最近的出口是窗户  就从那儿出去\Nthrough a window, if it's the nearest exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.86,0:32:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我们给他们看广告时他们是那种表情\NThe look on their faces when we showed them the spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.10,0:32:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我看不到他们的脸\NI couldn't see their faces,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.93,0:32:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他们都拿头磕着桌子呢\N'cause they were banging their heads on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.08,0:32:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  在它播出一次后  昨天\NYeah, yeah. Yesterday, the day after it airs once,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.76,0:32:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,《广告周刊》的出版商就说\Nthe publisher of Adweek calls it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.18,0:32:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,这是有史以来最好的广告\Nthe best commercial of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.49,0:32:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,是最好的  它也的确是\NOf all time! And it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.82,0:32:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有谁能做得更好\NAnd if anyone does one better,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.99,0:32:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,只有李岱艾广告公司\Nit's gonna be Chiat/Day,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.24,0:32:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,而董事会想换掉他们\Nwho the board wanted to replace,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.69,0:32:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,也只有李·克洛能胜任\Nand it's gonna be Lee Clow,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.85,0:32:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,可董事会觉得他是个疯子\Nwho the board thought was out of his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.15,0:32:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们  1984\NLadies and gentlemen, "1984."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.23,0:32:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这是信息净化指令的\NThe first glorious anniversary
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.79,0:32:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,光荣的一周年生日\Nof the information purification directives.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.86,0:32:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我们创造了史无前例的\NWe have created for the first time in all history
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.63,0:32:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,纯意识形态的花园\Na garden of pure ideology
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.72,0:32:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,在那里每一位工人都可以有所建树\Nwhere each worker may bloom,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.18,0:32:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,蔽除产生反对与矛盾的害虫\Nsecure from the pests purveying contradictory thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.47,0:32:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我们思想的统一是比地球上\NOur unification of thoughts is more powerful a weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.58,0:32:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,任何舰船或军队都要有力的武器\Nthan any fleet or army on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.15,0:32:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我们合为一体\NWe are one people...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.29,0:32:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我们用了光头党做临时演员吗\NDid we use skinheads as extras?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.10,0:32:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,-有些人跟我说过  -对\N- A couple of people have told me that. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.62,0:32:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我们付光头党工资吗\NWe paid skinheads?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.69,0:32:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,在我的工资名册上有光头党吗\NI've got skinheads on my payroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.96,0:33:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,-他们的样子符合你的要求  -光头党\N- They had a look you wanted. - The skinheads?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.62,0:33:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-对  -好吧  那就别说出去\N- Yeah. - Okay, let's keep that to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.30,0:33:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将获得胜利\NWe shall prevail.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.13,0:33:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,1月24日\NOn January 24th,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.68,0:33:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,苹果电脑将会发布麦金塔\NApple Computer will introduce Macintosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.45,0:33:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-还有谁知道  -知道什么\N- Who else knows? - Who else knows what?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.42,0:33:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-我们付钱让恐怖分子出演广告  -约翰\N- That we paid terrorists to be in our TV commercial. - John...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.33,0:33:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他们在广告上做了错误决策\NThey were wrong about the ad,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.82,0:33:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们是个好董事会  是好人\Nbut they're a good board. Good people.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.62,0:33:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他们唯一的问题  问题是他们是人\NTheir only problem... Their problem is that they're people.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.16,0:33:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,人  而人性是需要克服的东西\NPeople. The very nature of people is something to be overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.81,0:33:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,当我在运营百事可乐的时候\NWhen I was running Pepsi,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.90,0:33:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我们把重点放在18至55岁的年龄层\Nwe had a lot of success focusing on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.40,0:33:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,取得大成功\N18-to-55-year-olds,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.06,0:33:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,而他们不是暴力仇恨团体的成员\Nwho weren't members of violent hate groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.15,0:33:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道\NI get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.65,0:33:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你没有被敌人环绕\NYou're not surrounded by enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.93,0:33:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我们即将大功告成\NWe're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.55,0:33:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我在迪伦的词上摇摆不定\NI'm back and forth on the Dylan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.56,0:33:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我可能会用另一段歌词\NI might quote a different verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.04,0:33:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,有什么选择\NWhat are the choices?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.99,0:33:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,今朝失败者明日会成功\N"For the loser now will be later to win,"
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.63,0:33:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(155.25,82)}明日会成功
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.26,0:33:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,-现在用的是这句  -好  还有呢\N- which is what we have. - Mm-hmm. Or?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.85,0:33:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这片土地上的父亲和母亲\N"Come mothers and fathers throughout the land,"
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.26,0:33:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(159.75,12)}父亲和母亲
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.24,0:33:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,别对你不明白的东西指手画脚\N"and don't criticize what you can't understand."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.55,0:33:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(100.5,49)}别指手画脚
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.68,0:33:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(132,49)}儿子和女儿
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.68,0:33:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你们的儿子和女儿\N"Your sons and your daughters"
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.71,0:34:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,已不再受你们掌控\N"are beyond your command."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.74,0:34:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚输给安迪·赫茨菲尔德一百块\NI just lost a hundred bucks to Andy Hertzfeld.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.75,0:34:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他说你会改用这段歌词\NHe said you'd change it to that verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.15,0:34:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我们还有45秒  我想问你一个问题\NWe got 45 seconds. I want to use it to ask you a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.27,0:34:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么被收养的人\NWhy do people who are adopted
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.34,0:34:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,觉得他们是被拒绝而不是被选中\Nfeel like they were rejected instead of selected?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.33,0:34:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这可无凭无据\NThat came out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.36,0:34:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你们的儿子和女儿已不再受你们掌控\N"Your sons and your daughters are beyond your command.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.37,0:34:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你们的旧路正迅速老化\NYour old road is rapidly aging."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.39,0:34:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,去你的吧  因为我名叫史蒂夫·乔布斯\NSo go fuck yourself, because my name is Steve Jobs,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.25,0:34:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,而时代正在变化\Nand the times, they are a-changin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.34,0:34:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我没觉得被拒绝\NI don't feel rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.05,0:34:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-你确定  -非常确定\N- You're sure? - Very sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.73,0:34:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,因为不是父母生了孩子后\N'Cause it's not like the baby is born
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.26,0:34:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,他们看着孩子  然后说\Nand the parents look and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.66,0:34:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"不  我们对这个不感兴趣"\N"Nah, we're not interested in this one."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.30,0:34:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,换句话说  有人的确选择了你\NOn the other hand, someone did choose you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.06,0:34:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,这无法控制\NIt's having no control.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.36,0:34:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你发现  当生命中最重要的大事\NYou find out you were out of the loop
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.71,0:34:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,开始进行时  你却一无所知\Nwhen the most crucial events in your life were set in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.81,0:34:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,只要你还能控制\NAs long as you have control.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.89,0:35:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我不懂那些放弃的人\NI don't understand people who give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.58,0:35:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,是什么启发赫茨菲尔德打这个赌的\NWhat inspired Hertzfeld to make that bet?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.79,0:35:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他警告我\NHe was warning me that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.50,0:35:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,做为像你父亲般的存在可能会很危险\Nbeing your father figure could be dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.93,0:35:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,收好你的一百块  我就用第一段歌词\NKeep your 100 bucks. I'm sticking with the first verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.95,0:35:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,好\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.66,0:35:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,-他到底是什么意思  -没什么\N- What the hell does he mean? - Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.31,0:35:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我为你骄傲\NI'm proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.03,0:35:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你  头儿\NThank you, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.90,0:35:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴为大家介绍我的朋友\NIt's my pleasure to introduce my friend
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.18,0:35:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,和苹果公司首席执行官\Nand the CEO of Apple,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.41,0:35:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰·斯卡利\NJohn Sculley.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.65,0:35:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰\NJohn?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.00,0:35:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,什么事\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.98,0:35:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨在Mac上画了幅画\NLisa made a painting on the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.86,0:35:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,麦金塔\NThe Macintosh,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.81,0:35:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,苹果公司近乎神话般的家用电脑\NApple's near mythological home computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.08,0:35:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,在与业界大鳄IBM的竞争中\Nhas gotten off to a rocky start
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.55,0:35:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,开局不顺\Nin its battle with industry titan IBM.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.73,0:35:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,在第一季度销售量\NWith sales originally projected to be a million
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.16,0:35:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,会达到一百万的初始期望下\Nin the first quarter,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.09,0:35:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,在发售后  苹果公司几个月里只售出了\NApple has sold only 35,000 of the user-friendly machines in the months
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.98,0:35:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,三万五千台这款易操作的电脑\Nsince it's been available to customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.64,0:35:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫·乔布斯坚持\NThe insistence by Steve Jobs
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.42,0:35:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,使用叫做端到端控制的机制\Nthat it have what's called end-to-end control,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.54,0:35:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(128.25,52)}端
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.71,0:35:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(171.75,52)}到
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.88,0:35:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(212.25,52)}端
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.05,0:35:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(257.25,52)}控制
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.68,0:35:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是说它和大多数\Nwhich is a way of saying that it's not compatible
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.89,0:36:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,外部硬件和软件都不兼容\Nwith most outside hardware or software,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.18,0:36:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这正是此款潜力机型的悲剧缺陷\Nis the Shakespearean flaw in a machine that had potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.44,0:36:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,由于销售不佳  苹果电脑\NApple computers closed two of its factories today
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.18,0:36:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,今天关闭了两家工厂\Nin the wake of disappointing sales.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.02,0:36:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道上个月卖出了多少台Mac吗\NDo you know how many Macs were sold last month?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.56,0:36:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,五百台\N500.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.99,0:36:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,在让华尔街的部分而非全部人\NIn a move that surprised some
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.38,0:36:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,惊讶的一次决策中\Nbut not all on Wall Street,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.01,0:36:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,苹果电脑董事会今日投票\Nthe board of directors of Apple Computers voted today
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.53,0:36:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,解雇它的联合创始人史蒂夫·乔布斯\Nto fire its cofounder Steve Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.86,0:36:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(186.75,63)}被解雇
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.06,0:36:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,是他主动离开还是被排挤出局\NDid he jump or was he pushed?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.08,0:36:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,他的前任上司  苹果电脑首席执行官\NHis ex-boss, Apple CEO John Sculley,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.85,0:36:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰·斯卡利拒绝发表评论\Nrefused to comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.83,0:36:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,但是在一次专访中\NHowever, in an exclusive interview,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.82,0:36:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫·沃兹尼亚克对他的老友\NSteve Wozniak has slammed
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.41,0:36:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫·乔布斯的人品进行了抨击\Nthe integrity of his old friend Steve Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.04,0:36:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他说乔布斯是个无礼而伤人的家伙\NHe calls Jobs an insulting and hurtful guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.98,0:36:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,乔布斯携新公司和新电脑进行反击\NJobs is hitting back with a new company and a new computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.04,0:36:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(283.5,147)}无礼而伤人的家伙
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.35,0:36:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,苹果公司有了新的竞争者\NApple has a new competitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.47,0:36:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫·乔布斯的黑立方客户目标为教育市场\NSteve Jobs's Black Cube is aimed at the education market.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.13,0:36:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(284.25,83)}黑
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.38,0:36:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(285,159)}立方
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.37,0:36:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,很少有人能让世界等待\NFew people have the ability to make the world wait,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.70,0:36:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,除了乔布斯和他的新公司NeXT\Nbut that is just what Jobs is doing with his new company, NeXT.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.67,0:37:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,对焦看上去很准\NFocus seems kind of sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.86,0:37:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,在幻灯片上吗\NOn the slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.33,0:37:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,是整个楼层  聚光灯\NThe floor. The pin spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.87,0:37:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得我们需要精准的对焦\NI think we want a sharp focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.67,0:37:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,不是针对你  只是我不喜欢马戏团审美\NDon't take it personally. Just not a fan of the circus aesthetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.23,0:37:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,好  在这里停下\NAll right, let's hold here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.66,0:37:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我们得上去重新给器材对焦\NWe're gonna have to go up and refocus the instruments.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.21,0:37:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,就一台  30度那个没问题\NJust one. The 30 is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.65,0:37:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,当我们暂停时\NWhile we're holding,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.95,0:37:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,贵宾室里有前来祝贺的人\Nthere are well-wishers in the VIP room.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.36,0:37:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,沃兹来了\NAnd Woz is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.67,0:37:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(219.75,45)}旧金山歌剧团
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.62,0:37:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫·沃兹尼亚克  是  非常感谢\NSteve Wozniak. Yes. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.75,0:37:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,还有安迪·赫茨菲尔德\NAnd Andy Hertzfeld.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.86,0:37:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪·赫茨菲尔德  谢谢\NAndy Hertzfeld. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.44,0:37:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰·斯卡利也来了\NJohn Sculley is here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.57,0:37:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他能来真好\NIt's nice that he's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.40,0:37:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,真的吗  我觉得一点都不好\NReally? I don't think it's very nice at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.60,0:37:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,你得去见他们  他们想表示敬意\NYou have to see them. They wanna pay their respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.16,0:37:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他们尊重人\NIf they were respectful,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.45,0:37:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在应该还在苹果公司\Nwe'd all still be at Apple right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.85,0:37:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,听着\NLook...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.42,0:37:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他们真的希望我好  就不会说出来\NIf they really wished me well, they'd keep to themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.57,0:37:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我能告诉你一件事吗\NCan I tell you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.82,0:37:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得他们口是心非\NI don't think they do wish me well.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.85,0:37:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,但我觉得这没什么  我超越了苹果\NBut I'm all right with that. I'm over Apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.44,0:37:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我超越了麦金塔  沃兹和斯卡利\NI got over the Mac and Woz and Sculley,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.67,0:37:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你从高中恋情里走出来那样\Nthe same way you get over your high school sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.04,0:37:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,重新再来\NBuild a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.94,0:37:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,-我能跟你说件事吗  -说吧\N- Can I tell you something? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.55,0:37:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你说过你不会和他们竞争\NYou said you wouldn't compete with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.46,0:37:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但你设计了一台\Nbut you designed a computer
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.77,0:38:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,专供教育市场的电脑\Nspecifically for the education market,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.77,0:38:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,而这是公认的他们的市场\Nwhich they putatively own.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.80,0:38:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我觉得他们能来挺好\NSo, I think it's cool they're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.76,0:38:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,他们在起诉我\NThey're suing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.83,0:38:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,但还是\NStill...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.50,0:38:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,他们能来很好啊\NIt was nice they came.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.23,0:38:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,他们并不是宽宏大量\NThey're not being magnanimous.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.27,0:38:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,他们只想让这看上去像和平离婚\NThey want it to look like an amicable divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.10,0:38:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,历史对乔·狄马乔甩了玛丽莲梦露\NHistory doesn't remember Joe DiMaggio kindly
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.10,0:38:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}著名棒球运动员
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.28,0:38:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,可是评价不佳\Nfor dumping Marilyn.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.87,0:38:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫\NSteve?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.15,0:38:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么了\NWhat's your problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.74,0:38:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道  但我确定这是因为你\NI don't know, but I'm sure it can be traced back to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.09,0:38:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我是那个需要向别人解释你的人\NYou know, I'm the one who has to explain you to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.65,0:38:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,为了公司商标付给保罗·兰德十万美元\N$100,000 to Paul Rand for a corporate logo
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.56,0:38:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,当时我们甚至都不知道公司是做什么的\Nwhen we didn't even know what our company made.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.33,0:38:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,一套六十五万的模具用来做立方外壳\NA $650,000 mold for the cube,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.96,0:38:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,因为上帝不让角度从九十变成九十点一\Nbecause God forbid the angles be 90.1 instead of 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.19,0:38:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,是我不让角度从九十变成九十点一\NI forbid the angles to be 90.1 instead of 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.27,0:38:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,那个盒子可能会在古根海姆博物馆展出\NThat box could be on display at the Guggenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.36,0:38:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,别让他们有理由在媒体面前说\NDon't give them reason to say to the press
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.92,0:38:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你脾气大\Nyou have a chip on your shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.98,0:38:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你会为了我这么做吗\NWill you do that for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.61,0:38:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我脾气又不大\NI don't have a chip on my shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.17,0:39:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,好\NOkay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.76,0:39:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,但别让他们有理由这么说你\NBut don't give them a reason to say you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.55,0:39:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会的\NI don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.17,0:39:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,-这才是正确的态度  -这才不是态度\N- That's the right attitude. - That's not an attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.50,0:39:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,他们马上就会给我打电话让我去看灯光\NThey're gonna call me back in a minute to look at the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.36,0:39:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-少用一组  -好\N- Get one out of the way. - Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.11,0:39:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,-真的  -真的\N- Yeah? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.27,0:39:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-还有件事  -说\N- One more thing. - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.56,0:39:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,会后不接受媒体提问\NNo questions from the press after.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.81,0:39:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,不  为什么\NNo... Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.35,0:39:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在我有更好的答案之前不做媒体问答\NUntil I have better answers, no press avail.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.36,0:39:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有人问我在哪\NSomebody asks where I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.84,0:39:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你就说刚见到我  我马上就回来\Nyou just saw me, and I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.63,0:39:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,好\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.39,0:39:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}6号化妆间
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.33,0:39:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你想谁先来\NWho do you want first?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.63,0:39:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,把史蒂夫·沃兹尼亚克给我带过来\NBring me the face of Steve Wozniak.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.02,0:39:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,等等\NHang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.48,0:39:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,-我以为你去上学了  -等等\N- I thought you went to school. - Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.26,0:39:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你一小时前就该去学校了\NYou were supposed to go to school an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.75,0:39:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为你已经走了\NI thought you left.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.65,0:40:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我今早没有准时叫醒我妈妈\NI didn't wake up my mom on time this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.12,0:40:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,以前也发生过\NIt's happened before too.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.86,0:40:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我听到闹铃就起床\NI wake up with the alarm
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.01,0:40:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,然后穿衣服吃早饭\Nand then I get dressed and eat breakfast,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.05,0:40:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,但有时吃完饭后我忘了看时间\Nbut sometimes I forget to see what time it is after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.85,0:40:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么你妈妈不自己设闹铃\NWhy doesn't your mom just set her own alarm clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.68,0:40:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的任务之一\NIt's one of my chores.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.78,0:40:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道这和你有什么关系  在你还\NI don't understand what that has to do with why you're still...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.16,0:40:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你妈妈在哪\NWhere's your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.81,0:40:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,她去找公共电话了\NShe went to find a pay phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.47,0:40:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,一小时前  她说\NAn hour ago, she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.44,0:40:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你没必要举手\NYou don't have to raise your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.86,0:40:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-你说它有点不正  -是的\N- You said it was off by a little. - It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.68,0:40:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,-我刚量了  -乔安娜\N- I just measured it. - Joanna...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.83,0:40:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,四面都是三十厘米\NExactly a foot on all four sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.73,0:40:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,一共有六面\NThere are six sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.38,0:40:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,但你现在不该在这里\NBut you're not supposed to be here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.33,0:40:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我们知道如果有四面相等\NWe know if four of the sides are equal to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.47,0:40:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,剩下的两面也一定相等\Nthe other two must be equal as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.65,0:40:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,上下左右四面\NThe top, bottom, right and left
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.84,0:40:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,比前后要短约一毫米\Nare about a millimeter shorter than the front and back.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.60,0:40:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,没有  我量过了\NThey're not. I measured them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.60,0:40:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨  我算是个设计专家\NLisa, I'm kind of an expert in design.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.93,0:40:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,而那只是把二十分的尺子\NAnd that's a 20-cent ruler.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.24,0:40:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,有没有可能它刻度不准\NYou think there's a chance it could be off?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.72,0:40:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我还有把尺子  我会量这把尺子的\NIf I had another ruler, I would measure this ruler,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.52,0:40:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,但我真觉得刻度没问题\Nbut I really doubt it's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.43,0:40:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,等你妈妈回来\NWhen your mother comes back,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.06,0:40:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-你就得去上学了  -因为这是把尺子\N- you have to go to school. - Because it's a ruler!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.49,0:40:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么不准呢\NWhy is it off?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.94,0:41:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,-你听到我刚才说的了吗  -听到了\N- Did you hear what I just said? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.53,0:41:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,因为有时你好像\NBecause sometimes it seems like
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.51,0:41:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,一直在说你想要什么却不听别人说\Nyou just keep saying what you want without listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.35,0:41:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我在听\NI'm listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.29,0:41:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-你需要什么吗  -不需要\N- Is there something you need? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.51,0:41:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么这不是个完美的立方体\NWhy isn't it a perfect cube?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.92,0:41:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-你刚才问过我了  -我忘了为什么\N- You've asked me before. - I forget what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.64,0:41:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,这叫视异常\NIt's an optical anomaly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.06,0:41:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,人眼看来完美立方体不像立方体\NTo the human eye, a perfect cube doesn't look like a cube,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.76,0:41:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,所以就让它两侧面的边长\Nso we made it roughly a millimeter shorter
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.33,0:41:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,比一英尺短大约一毫米\Nthan a foot on two sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.33,0:41:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}NextCube官方尺寸为长宽高均一英尺
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.62,0:41:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,什么是异常\NWhat's an anomaly?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.10,0:41:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这你之前也问过了\NYou've asked me that before too.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.63,0:41:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我不懂你为什么总这样\NI don't know why you keep doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.90,0:41:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,就是例外  不符合规律的东西\NIt's an exception. Something that doesn't fit a pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.41,0:41:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你该去上学了  进\NYou have to go to school. Come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.48,0:41:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你俩见过\NI think you two have met.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.69,0:41:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你好啊  老朋友\NHello, old friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.63,0:41:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,-你看着不错  -你也是  你也是\N- You look well. - So do you. So do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.21,0:41:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,他们告诉我\NAnd they're telling me
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.23,0:41:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,乔治把打光弄好了  你去看看\NGeorge is ready for you to look at the focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.93,0:42:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我一起走\NTake a walk with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.49,0:42:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-这是丽萨吗  -是的\N- Is this Lisa? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.12,0:42:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,-不可能是丽萨  -就是她\N- This can't be Lisa. - It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.79,0:42:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨才那么大\NLisa's this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.60,0:42:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,小孩会长的  走吧\NThey get taller. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.06,0:42:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,-记得我吗  -她不记得\N- Do you remember me? - She doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.49,0:42:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我是你爸的朋友史蒂夫·沃兹尼亚克\NI'm your dad's friend Steve Wozniak.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.49,0:42:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉  我不记得你\NI apologize. I don't remember you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.35,0:42:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你真有礼貌\NYou're very polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.75,0:42:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,-沃兹  -怎么\N- Woz? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.13,0:42:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,克里斯安在打公共电话\NChrisann's at a pay phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.96,0:42:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你能去找她吗\NWould you find her?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.64,0:42:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,好\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.65,0:42:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,来了不少人\NGood turnout.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.29,0:42:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-很多人  -是啊\N- Great turnout. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.01,0:42:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,-"酷毙了"  -酷毙了\N- "Insanely great." - Insanely great.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.12,0:42:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我们第一次在不同团队工作\NThis is the first time we haven't played for the same team.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.47,0:42:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你要发布首张单飞专辑\NIt's like you're releasing your first solo album.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.89,0:42:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我...感谢你邀请我来发布会\NI, uh... I appreciate your inviting me to the launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.85,0:42:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是想重新开始\NI just want to wipe the slate clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.49,0:42:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我也这么想  所以来了后台\NThat's exactly what I want. That's why I came backstage.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.97,0:42:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,希望你知道我会支持你\NI want you to know, um, I'll be out there with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.76,0:42:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你有没有可能代我上去\NAny chance I can get you to go out there instead of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.26,0:42:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱你  史蒂夫\NI love you, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.11,0:42:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我也爱你  沃兹\NI love you too, Woz.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.12,0:42:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,有些风言风语\NYou know, some things were said.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.46,0:42:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  大家公开议论\NThey were. They were said in public.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.79,0:42:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,公开出版  你那么做是被逼的吗\NThey were published. Were you pressured to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.35,0:42:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我是什么\NWas I what?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.24,0:42:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,来看看\NCheck it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.44,0:43:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,这是给旧金山歌剧团的乐池\NIt's the orchestra pit for the San Francisco Opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.99,0:43:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我那么做是被逼的吗\NWas I pressured to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.42,0:43:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,有次我在坦格伍德音乐节上见到小泽征尔\NI once met Seiji Ozawa at Tanglewood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.34,0:43:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,特立独行的指挥\NA thunderous conductor.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.62,0:43:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,对技艺和细节的把握  精准得邪乎\NUngodly artfulness and nuance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.58,0:43:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我问他指挥的工作究竟有哪些\NAnd I asked him what exactly a conductor does
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.02,0:43:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,是节拍器做不了的\Nthat a metronome can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.57,0:43:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,出人意料  他\NSurprisingly, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.20,0:43:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,他没揍死你吗\NHe didn't beat the living shit out of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.41,0:43:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,没有  他说  "音乐家演奏乐器\NThat's right. No, he said, "The musicians play their instruments.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.77,0:43:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,而我摆弄乐团"\NI play the orchestra."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.31,0:43:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,感觉听起来不错\NThat feels like something that sounds good,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.44,0:43:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,但没有任何意义\Nbut doesn't mean anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.07,0:43:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,马库拉  斯卡利\NMarkkula, Sculley...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.45,0:43:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他们有没有让你对媒体说我坏话\NDid they ask you to slag me off in the press?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.61,0:43:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我有理由生气\NI had reason to be angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.14,0:43:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,-他们有吗  -绝对没有\N- Did they? - Absolutely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.61,0:43:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们叫你去讲\NBut they asked you to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.01,0:43:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,当时苹果四面受敌  你又离开公司\NApple was under siege. You'd just left the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.18,0:43:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,该有人接受媒体采访\NSomeone had to talk to the press.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.57,0:43:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我就在这儿  沃兹  是公司抛弃我\NI'm right here, Woz. The company left me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.45,0:43:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我求过你  我求过你的\NI begged you. I begged you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.77,0:43:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Ⅱ占总收入70%\NThe Apple II accounted for 70% of the revenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.17,0:43:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你以为会怎样\NWhat did you think was gonna happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.87,0:43:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你对Apple Ⅱ和Lisa都关心得不够\NYou didn't care enough about the Apple II or the Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.47,0:43:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我明确说吧\NLet's be really clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.88,0:44:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我根本不在乎Apple Ⅱ和Lisa\NI didn't care at all about the Apple II or the Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.12,0:44:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,没人逼我那么做\NI wasn't pressured to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.44,0:44:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我对媒体说的话  可能有被曲解\NWhat I said to the press was an honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.42,0:44:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但都如实表达了我的想法\Nif tempered, reflection of what I believed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.79,0:44:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,-沃兹  -什么事\N- Woz. - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.68,0:44:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你手腕上戴的什么玩意\NWhat the fuck is on your wrist?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.40,0:44:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-想知道吗  -真的等不及了\N- You wanna know? - I literally can't wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.65,0:44:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,十年内所有人都会戴这个\NEveryone's gonna be wearing these in 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.78,0:44:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,这个是数码表  用数码管做的\NIt's a Nixie watch, made using Nixie tubes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.60,0:44:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这项技术已经有40年历史了\NThis is actually 40-year-old technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.17,0:44:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,冷阴极管  140伏电压下运作\NCold cathode tubes. They're operating at 140 volts.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.35,0:44:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,手腕倾斜45度  就出来了\NI tilt my wrist 45 degrees, it's right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.37,0:44:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,小时  分钟和秒数\NHours, minutes and seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.98,0:44:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我们大脑的工作方式一样  看啊\NThe way our minds work. Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.88,0:44:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,帮个忙\NDo me a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.76,0:44:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,把时间往前调  就像在飞机上\NSet the watch ahead like you're on a plane
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.45,0:44:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你要调时区\Nand just changed time zones.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.76,0:44:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,没问题\NNot a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.94,0:44:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,旋下来  只消按这个扭\NUnscrew that. Just hit the button.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.58,0:44:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,不好意思  乘务员\NExcuse me. Flight attendant?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.91,0:44:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我旁边这家伙好像要引爆炸弹\NThe man next to me would appear to be detonating a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.73,0:44:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得它看起来像炸弹\NYou think this looks like a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.33,0:44:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,即使现在我也不能确定它不是\NEven right now, I'm not 100% sure it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.55,0:44:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-我想等大家都习惯了...  -不\N- I think maybe once people get used to it... - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.43,0:45:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我当时很生气\NI was angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.54,0:45:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,关于Apple Ⅱ你当时说的那些话\NYou were saying things about the Apple II,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.36,0:45:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你对团队的态度\Nand the way you were treating the team...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.68,0:45:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,沃兹  给你张免死金牌\NWoz. You get a free pass for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.17,0:45:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我要回台上去了\NI got to get back onstage.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.34,0:45:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,只剩两分钟排练\NWe got two minutes of rehearsal time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.63,0:45:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道刚才那样有多居高临下吗\NDo you understand how condescending that just was?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.29,0:45:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你大概不知道\NMaybe you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.04,0:45:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想看你\NI don't want to see you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.72,0:45:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,双手被铐着拖出飞机\Nget dragged off an airplane in plastic handcuffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.38,0:45:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你给我免死金牌\NI get a free pass for life from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.53,0:45:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你发出免...你给我吗\NYou give out the pass... Y-Y-You give them to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.32,0:45:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你这样会中风的  小伙计\NYou're gonna have a stroke, little buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.98,0:45:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你做了什么  你做了什么\NWhat did you do? What did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.40,0:45:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么丽萨都不知道我\NWhy has Lisa not heard of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.84,0:45:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,见鬼伙计  有几个四年级学生知道你啊\NShit, man, how many fourth-graders have heard of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.79,0:45:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你不会写代码\NYou can't write code.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.34,0:45:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,不是工程师  也不是设计师\NYou're not an engineer. You're not a designer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.91,0:45:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你连钉子都不会钉\NYou can't put a hammer to a nail.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.30,0:45:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,电路板是我搭的\NI built the circuit board.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.83,0:45:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,图形界面是从施乐帕克研究中心偷的\NThe graphical interface was stolen from Xerox PARC.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.46,0:45:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你把杰夫·拉斯金从他自己的项目撤走前\NJef Raskin was the leader of the Mac team
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.01,0:45:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,他是Mac团队的头儿\Nbefore you threw him off his own project.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.43,0:45:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,这一切...机箱是别人设计的\NEverything... Someone else designed the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.09,0:46:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么会我每天看到那么多报道\NSo how come 10 times in a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.36,0:46:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,都说"史蒂夫·乔布斯是个天才"\NI read "Steve Jobs is a genius"?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.91,0:46:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你究竟做了什么\NWhat do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.80,0:46:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我摆弄乐团\NI play the orchestra.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.06,0:46:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,而你是不错的音乐家  就坐那儿\NAnd you're a good musician. You sit right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.86,0:46:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你是那一排最棒的\NYou're the best in your row.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.06,0:46:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我来是澄清误会\NI came here to clear the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.04,0:46:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-你知道我为什么来  -你能直接说吗\N- Do you know why I came here? - Didn't you just answer that?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.81,0:46:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我来是因为你要完蛋了\NI came here because you're gonna get killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.30,0:46:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你这电脑不可能成功\NYour computer's gonna fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.13,0:46:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你找了个高校顾问团\NYou had a college and university advisory board
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.69,0:46:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,他们想要供两三千人使用的大功率工作站\Ntelling you they need a powerful workstation for 2,000 to 3,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.66,0:46:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你给NeXT定价六千五\NYou've priced NeXT at 6,500.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.85,0:46:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,还不包括可选的三千块的硬盘\NAnd that doesn't include the optional $3,000 hard drive,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.53,0:46:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,而大家会发现它是必选的\Nwhich people will discover isn't optional.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.12,0:46:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,因为光盘太弱什么也做不了\NBecause the optical disk is too weak to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.02,0:46:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,再加上两千五的激光打印机就是一万二\NAnd the $2,500 laser printer brings the total to $12,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.56,0:46:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你是这个世界上唯一一个\NAnd in the entire world, you are the only person
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.29,0:46:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,在乎机箱是不是完美立方体的人\Nwho cares that it's housed in a perfect cube.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.94,0:46:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你要完蛋了\NYou're gonna get killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.46,0:46:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,而我来是希望这一切发生时能站在你身边\NAnd I came here to stand next to you while that happens
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.76,0:46:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,因为朋友就该这么做\Nbecause that's what friends do.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.86,0:46:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,男人就该这么做  我不要你的金牌\NThat's what men do. I don't need your pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.90,0:47:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我们像从前那样  别待我像个外人\NWe go back, so don't talk to me like I'm other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.42,0:47:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,只有我知道\NI'm the only one that knows
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.47,0:47:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,现在这个乔布斯是你生造出来的\Nthat this guy here is someone you invented.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.88,0:47:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我陪着你是因为那个没用的完美立方体\NI'm standing by you because that perfect cube that does nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.46,0:47:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,将会是个人电脑史上\Nis about to be the single biggest failure
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.35,0:47:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,最彻底的失败\Nin the history of personal computing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.76,0:47:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,说些我不知道的\NTell me something else I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.97,0:47:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,-继续上台彩排吗  -时间不够\N- Back onstage? - We're out of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.86,0:47:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他们要清理舞台然后放人进来\NThey've got to mop the stage and open the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.56,0:47:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,垮了就垮了  是吧\NIf it crashes, it crashes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.98,0:47:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,可以拿这个开玩笑\NYou'll make a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.60,0:47:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,开玩笑\NI'll make a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.25,0:47:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,垮了就垮了\NIf it crashes, it crashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.75,0:47:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,这广告语不错\NIt's a good slogan.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.80,0:47:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"NeXT  垮了就垮了"\N"NeXT. If it crashes, it crashes."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.41,0:47:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我不单是说演示  史蒂夫\NI'm not just talking about the demo, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.55,0:47:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,就算失败也别切腹\NIf it tanks, we don't swallow cyanide.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.89,0:47:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-我们回去做绘图板  -再别碰那个了\N- We go back to the drawing board. - No more drawing boards.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.82,0:47:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,再发明一次埃德塞尔牌汽车  也别搞绘图板\NInvent the Edsel twice, you don't get any more drawing boards.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.82,0:47:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}1957年出厂时恰值经济衰退而惨败  后成为"失败"的同义词
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.31,0:47:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,说说你的计划\NTell me what the plan is.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.89,0:48:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须告诉我计划  因为我不知道\NYou have to tell me the plan, because I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.92,0:48:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你四处走动好像成竹在胸\NYou're walking around like you've got "Can't Lose" cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.94,0:48:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你准备好的时候自然就知道了\NThe plan will reveal itself to you when you're ready to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.91,0:48:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,需要我嗑药吗\NWill I have to drop acid?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.45,0:48:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,也没坏处\NCouldn't hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.92,0:48:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,有计划吗\NIs there a plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.50,0:48:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我什么时候让你失望过\NHave I ever let you down?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.35,0:48:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,每时每刻\NEvery single goddamn time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.97,0:48:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-那以后不会了  -有吗\N- Then I'm due. - Is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.38,0:48:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,乔安娜  计划是有的\NJoanna, there's a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.13,0:48:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是不想让你\NI just don't wanna put you in a position
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.60,0:48:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,对大家说谎\Nwhere you're lying to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.23,0:48:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,晚15分钟开始\NStart 15 minutes late
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.54,0:48:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,-阿维重新编译  我们也搏一把  -天啊\N- so Avie can recompile and give us a fighting chance. - Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.44,0:48:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要这样谈多少次...\NHow many times are we gonna have this con...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.13,0:48:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,-不能推迟开始  绝不  -好\N- We're not starting late, ever! - Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.24,0:48:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-绝对不能推迟  -推迟\N- We're not ever starting late. - Late.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.52,0:48:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但推迟也是你的原因啊\NBut where do you come down on starting late?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.91,0:48:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨总这样\NLisa's been doing this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.37,0:48:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,她问一些我已经说过的事\Nwhere she asks me about stuff I've already told her.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.50,0:48:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,她问我一些她早知道答案的问题\NShe asks me questions, and I know she already knows the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.99,0:48:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,这什么意思\NWhat's that about?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.69,0:49:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,怕家长心情不好的时候\NKids do that when they're scared
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.88,0:49:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,小孩都那么做\None of their parents is in a bad mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.84,0:49:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他们想引你谈些你感兴趣的话题\NThey try to get you talking about something you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.39,0:49:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,很常见\NIt's very common
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.15,0:49:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你也可以说些她感兴趣的\Nand can be treated by talking to her about things she likes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.42,0:49:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你在这方面有经验或受过培训吗\NDo you have any experience or training in this field?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.43,0:49:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,没有\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.83,0:49:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,叫他们开门放人\NTell them to open the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.73,0:49:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨在哪\NWhere's Lisa?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.84,0:49:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,就在附近\NShe's around.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.83,0:49:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-什么意思  -她在楼里跑来跑去\N- What does that mean? - She's running around the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.85,0:49:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,一小时前  你说要送她去学校\NAn hour ago, you said you were taking her to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.32,0:49:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,她求我让她留下\NShe begged me to let her stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.38,0:49:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,有些父亲很爱...\NThere are fathers who would so love...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.78,0:49:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这样不对好吧\NIt is wrong, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.17,0:49:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,太堕落了  家长不能这么当\NIt is morally wrong, it's parentally wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.18,0:49:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你利用丽萨来找我要钱\NIt is wrong for you to use Lisa
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.93,0:49:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,这么做不对\Nas a way of getting money from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.60,0:49:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,即使现在不懂  总有一天她会明白\NShe will know, if she doesn't already,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.02,0:49:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,在你眼中她就起这作用\Nthat that is your primary use for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.97,0:49:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,-你到死都遭她恨  -即使现在不懂\N- She will hate you for the rest of your life. - She will see,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.57,0:49:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,总有一天她会明白\Nif she doesn't already,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.85,0:49:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,她的母亲敢于直面男性\Nthat her mother is a woman who stands up to men.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.34,0:49:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,方法是靠他们养活\NBy living off of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.74,0:50:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,方法是不让他们禁锢我  贬低我\NBy not letting myself be imprisoned and degraded by them.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.28,0:50:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,禁锢  我想甩都甩不掉\NImprisoned? I can't get rid of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.67,0:50:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我要看医生  还有牙医\NI need a doctor and I need a dentist.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.06,0:50:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然我上了一学期就从大学退学\NI dropped out of college after a semester,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.59,0:50:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但好吧  我来看看\Nbut, okay, let's have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.25,0:50:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须资助自己的女儿及她的母亲\NYou will support your daughter and her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.86,0:50:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你有没有花一千五百块来给家宅赐福\NDid you pay someone $1,500 to bless your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.05,0:50:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,-听见我说的了吗  -有吗\N- Did you hear what I said? - Did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.89,0:50:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我不记得多少钱了  史蒂夫\NI don't remember how much it was, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.75,0:50:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,-一千五  -好吧  他们也不能白干\N- It was $1,500. - Well, they don't do it for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.07,0:50:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,是不能  他们要价一千五\NThey don't. They charge $1,500.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.01,0:50:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎么花...操  我甚至不...\NHow I spend... Fuck. You know, I'm not even gonna...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.67,0:50:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你是不是想说\NWere you about to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.26,0:50:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"我怎么花钱不关你的事"\N"How I spend my money is none of your business"?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.49,0:50:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我鼻窦发炎而且我需要看牙医\NI have a sinus infection and I need to see a dentist too.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.61,0:50:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你也知道那笔赐福费\NSo you can see how your blessing budget
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.45,0:50:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,本该花得更明智\Ncould have been better spent.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.40,0:50:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,比如花在完美的立方体上\NLike on a perfect cube?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.80,0:50:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-看着我  克里斯安  -怎么了\N- Look at me, Chrisann. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.87,0:50:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-你知道我是谁吧  -知道\N- You know who I am, right? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.33,0:50:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,-你知道我认识些人  -你说什么呢\N- And you know I know people. - What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.29,0:50:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,看着我  你知道我认识的人也认识些人\NLook at me. And you know the people I know, they know people.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.39,0:50:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,这是干吗\NWhat is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.08,0:50:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,如果再让我听到\NIf I ever hear again
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.69,0:50:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你往丽萨头上扔早餐碗\Nthat you've thrown a cereal bowl at Lisa's head...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.78,0:51:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-什么  -会有人打我的私人专线\N- What? - My private line's gonna ring,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.70,0:51:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,电话线另一端会说  "办好了"\Nand a voice on the other end is gonna say, "We're all set."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.71,0:51:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,这样我就知道你死了\NThat's how I'll learn that you're dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.11,0:51:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你是不是疯...\NAre you cra...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.32,0:51:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我是冲地上摔碗\NI threw the bowl on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.19,0:51:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我没往她头上扔\NI didn't throw it at her head.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.98,0:51:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,她甚至都不在房里\NShe wasn't even in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.46,0:51:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,她不在...我是冲地上摔碗\NShe was nowhere... I threw the bowl on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.06,0:51:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,她是个小姑娘  你在吓她\NShe's a little girl. You're scaring her.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.62,0:51:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我是个成年人  你在吓我\NI'm a grown man. You're scaring me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.15,0:51:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,扔垃圾是小事\NTaking out the garbage is a chore.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.39,0:51:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,擦桌子是小事\NClearing the table is a chore.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.39,0:51:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,早上叫你起床真他妈可怕\NWaking you up in the morning is just fucking creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.69,0:51:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,请你多教教我\NPlease teach me more
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.74,0:51:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,-怎么当爹妈  -到此为止\N- about being a parent. - We're all done here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.22,0:51:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你都不承认自己是爹肯定能让我受益匪浅\NIt means so much coming from someone who won't admit he is one.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.10,0:51:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-别再冲丽萨吼了  -我对她负责\N- Stop screaming at Lisa. - I give her responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.74,0:51:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-明白了  -总有一天她会感谢我\N- Got it. - One day she's gonna thank me for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.80,0:51:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-你死了以后吧  -滚蛋\N- Probably in your sleep. - Fuck off!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.46,0:51:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,好\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.77,0:51:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我从没...我从没往她头上扔过东西\NI never... I never threw anything at her head.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.68,0:51:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.83,0:51:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我也绝不会那么做\NI never would.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.37,0:51:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不管你说什么  事实就是事实\NThings don't become so because you say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.44,0:51:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我忙完再给你账户打些钱\NThere'll be more money in your account by the end of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.28,0:52:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,-你态度好吗  -好\N- Were you being nice? - Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.72,0:52:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,下一个是安迪\NAndy's next.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.42,0:52:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,赫茨菲尔德还是坎宁安\NHertzfeld or Cunningham?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.34,0:52:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,赫茨菲尔德  他和阿维·特瓦尼安\NHertzfeld. He's playing with Avie Tevanian
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.00,0:52:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,在后台弄电脑\Non the computer backstage.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.80,0:52:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们  音乐厅现在开放\NLadies and gentlemen, the house is now open.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.85,0:52:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,-在上千人面前玩  -史蒂夫\N- ...playing in front of thousands of people. - Steve!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.79,0:52:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,能等会儿吗  乔尔\NCan he do it later, Joel?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.08,0:52:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我们八分钟内就要进去\NWe go in eight minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.57,0:52:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,今早我们能来个快问快答的采访吗\NCan I get a quick reaction to the press this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.68,0:52:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,什么内容\NWhat about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.52,0:52:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-它的大小体积  -来后台我告诉你\N- The size of it, the volume. - I'll tell you on background...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.80,0:52:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要史蒂夫的原话\NI was hoping for a quote from Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.85,0:52:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,来后台我告诉你\NI'll tell you on background
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.47,0:53:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,在科技业我还没见过这样的东西\Nthat I've never seen anything like it in the tech industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.07,0:53:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我联系《华尔街日报》\NI called the "Wall Street Journal"
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.17,0:53:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,想给今天打个整版广告\Nto take out a full-page ad for today,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.96,0:53:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你猜他们的销售怎么说吗\Nand do you know what their sales guy said?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.10,0:53:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"费什么事呀  这就像是\N"Why bother? It'd be like
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.12,0:53:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,提醒梅西百货明天是圣诞节"\Nnotifying Macy's that tomorrow is Christmas."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.66,0:53:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你看斯图尔特·奥尔索普的简讯没\NYou saw the Stewart Alsop newsletter?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.17,0:53:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,看了\NI did.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.66,0:53:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}《财富》杂志的信息技术专栏作家
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.78,0:53:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉  乔安娜  我要录史蒂夫的话\NI'm sorry, Joanna, I need to get Steve on the record.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.04,0:53:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,标题是\NThe headline was
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.31,0:53:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,"亲爱的NeXT  我何时能拿到"\N"Dear NeXT, when can I get my machine?"
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.50,0:53:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,什么时候\NWhen can he?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.59,0:53:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,八到十周内我们就宣布发行日期\NWe'll announce the ship date in the next eight to 10 weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.93,0:53:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,奥尔索普说的不是发行日期\NAlsop's not talking about the ship date.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.24,0:53:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他想知道什么时候能给他一个\NHe wants to know when he can get one to play with.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.42,0:53:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我们对斯图尔特·奥尔索普充满敬意\NWe have a lot of respect for Stewart Alsop,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.95,0:53:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我们也想送一台到他手上\Nand we want to get a machine into his hands
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.49,0:53:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,这样他就能跟订阅用户介绍介绍\Nso he can tell his subscribers about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.21,0:53:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-那是什么时候  -很快\N- And when will that be? - Very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.09,0:53:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,几天还是一周\NCouple of days? A week?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.14,0:53:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我不录音\NOff the record.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.75,0:53:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,-不录音  -完全不录\N- Off the record? - Completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.26,0:53:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,-我们认为  -等做好了就给他\N- We think... - He'll get it when it's finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.33,0:53:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,还没做好吗\NIt's not finished?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.01,0:53:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,快做好了\NIt's almost finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.40,0:53:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,演示你都排练了三周\NI've been watching you rehearse the demo for three weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.39,0:53:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,-是的  -还剩什么\N- Yeah. - What's left?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.31,0:53:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-一些细节  -什么\N- A little thing. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.66,0:53:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-已经说得够多了  -我们没有录音\N- I think that's enough. - We're off the record,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.47,0:54:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,而且乔尔总能充分理解细微差异\Nand Joel's always been good at understanding nuance.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.78,0:54:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,还剩什么没做\NWhat's left to finish?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.95,0:54:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我想用外行的说法\NI guess, in layman's terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.22,0:54:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该说  我们还没有OS\Nyou'd have to say we don't have an OS.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.87,0:54:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,-操作系统吗  -是的\N- An operating system? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.71,0:54:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,什么意思\NWhat do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.73,0:54:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,操作系统负责电脑的运行\NWell, the OS is what runs the computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.25,0:54:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,可以说  有操作系统才有电脑\NIn fact, it sort of is the computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.20,0:54:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,之前怎么运行的  今天早上要怎么运行\NHow has it been running? How's it gonna run this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.33,0:54:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你说没有操作系统究竟什么意思\NWhat do you mean, you don't have an OS?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.11,0:54:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,是这样  阿维·特瓦尼安是首席软件工程师\NIt's like this. Avie Tevanian is our chief software designer,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.64,0:54:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他编了个演示程序\Nand he wrote a demo program.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.12,0:54:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,类似于造了辆好车  但引擎还没弄好\NIt's like we built a great car, but we haven't built the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.94,0:54:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,于是用高尔夫球车的电池组去撑一会儿\NSo we put a golf cart battery in there to make it go for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.81,0:54:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,现在这电脑\NAll this computer knows
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.71,0:54:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,只知道怎么做演示\Nhow to do right now is demonstrate itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.70,0:54:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你是说你只建了个黑立方\NYou're telling me the only thing you've built is a black cube?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.28,0:54:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\NYes. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.41,0:54:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,但你见过比这更酷的黑立方吗\NBut isn't it the coolest black cube you've ever seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.44,0:54:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这是...我没有录音\NIs this... We're off the record.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.12,0:54:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,这是策略还是出了问题  如果是出了问题\NIs this a strategy or a problem? If it's a problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.35,0:54:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,别跟那家伙说我们的专利知识\NDo not share proprietary knowledge with that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.58,0:54:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,没出问题\NIt's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.64,0:54:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,反正我也理解不了\NI wouldn't understand it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.55,0:54:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我也不理解  而专利上有我的名字\NI don't understand it either, and my name's on the patents.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.38,0:55:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,还能发邮件啊\NIt's got e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.41,0:55:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,邮件不再仅为技术专家服务\NWell, e-mail's not just for tech specialists anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.89,0:55:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,现在如此  但将来不是了\NWell, it is, but it won't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.12,0:55:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜NeXT电脑发出的邮件\NAnd I assume an e-mail sent on a NeXT computer
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.97,0:55:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,只有NeXT电脑才能收到吧\Ncan only be received by a NeXT computer?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.30,0:55:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,封闭结构  端到端\NClosed, end-to-end.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.61,0:55:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,新的废纸篓不好\NThe new trash can is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.68,0:55:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我很想感谢你为此付出的每分每秒\NI wanna tell you I appreciate all the hours you put into it,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.96,0:55:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,但我说不出口  因为实在是太差了\Nbut I can't because of how terrible it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.39,0:55:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,那就换回另一个\NGo back to the other one.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.96,0:55:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么我们还是提供了三种时钟选择\NWhy are we still giving three options on the clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.47,0:55:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,-那你想给几种  -两种  买或不买\N- How many options do you want to give? - Two. Buy it or don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.14,0:55:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,能跟你说几句吗\NCan I talk to you for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.46,0:55:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,当了个然\NAbso-fruitly.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.64,0:55:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,听着  阿维在重新编译了\NUh, look, man. Avie's been recompiling,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.78,0:55:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,但他说今早可能会出些小状况\Nbut he says there may be some glitches this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.27,0:55:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,如果只是有一些状况的话\NIf all there are are some glitches,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.85,0:55:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,那就已经是奇迹般的巨大胜利了\Nit'll be a triumph of miraculous magnitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.57,0:55:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么要为阿维传话\NWhy are you translating for Avie?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.74,0:55:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想他看到\NI-I didn't want him to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.22,0:55:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你对系统演示出了状况的严厉态度\Nthe hard way your position on glitches in a demo,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.86,0:55:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,但你似乎变成熟了\Nbut it sounds like you've mellowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.78,0:55:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我在成长  安迪  我学着爱自己\NI've been growing, Andy. I've been learning to love myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.80,0:55:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我做梦都没想过你还会不爱自己\NI wouldn't have ever dreamed that was a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.50,0:55:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,讽刺得好啊\NFantastic burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.82,0:55:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你得去你座位上了\NYou need to go to your seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.38,0:55:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨呢  进了专为天才小孩开的学校吗\NHow about Lisa, getting into a school for gifted kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.38,0:55:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  经过测试发现她能飞\NYeah, she was tested and it turns out she can fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.56,0:56:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,-说真的  这很了不起  -我知道\N- Seriously, it's a big deal. - I know it's a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.94,0:56:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我才给那学校建了栋楼\NThat's why I built the school a building.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.45,0:56:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-她应该不是靠这楼进去的吧  -是吗\N- Well, I'm sure that's not why she got in. - Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.68,0:56:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,给你看个《Macworld》上有趣的文章\NUh, can I show you something funny from Macworld?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.64,0:56:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在还真是有这么多闲工夫\NI can't think of anything I have to do right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.32,0:56:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你会开心的\NIt'll make you feel good.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.39,0:56:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,乔安娜  看看这个\NJoanna! Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.69,0:56:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪  他只剩几分钟了\NAndy, he's only got a couple of minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.35,0:56:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,《Macworld》上盖伊·川崎的文章\NIt's Guy Kawasaki writing in Macworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.69,0:56:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你会喜欢的\NYou're gonna like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.28,0:56:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我们能等发布会结束再拜读吗\NWell, can we all enjoy it later?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.97,0:56:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他写了篇模仿新闻稿的文章\NHe wrote a parody press release
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.47,0:56:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,说苹果为了你们的操作系统收购NeXT\Nabout Apple buying NeXT for your OS.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.09,0:56:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,他设想不远的将来  苹果需要你的系统\NHe imagines a near future where Apple needs your OS
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.24,0:56:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不得不收购NeXT\Nand has to buy NeXT,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.24,0:56:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你则会回来担任CEO\Nand-and you come back as CEO.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.06,0:56:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,他写道盖茨说\NHe has Gates saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.31,0:56:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"现在乔布斯会想出更多的创新点子\N"There would now be more innovations from Jobs
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.78,0:56:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,能让微软抄袭"\Nthat Microsoft could copy."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.58,0:56:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}史蒂夫·乔布斯重回苹果担任CEO
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.87,0:56:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以待会儿再看\NYou can read it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.70,0:56:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.73,0:56:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你没捐楼  她也会被录取的\NShe would've gotten in without you donating a building.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.65,0:56:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,但捐了楼  接受访谈时就有得说了\NStill, it's something to talk about in the interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.56,0:57:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,好的  好运\NAll right. Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.55,0:57:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.82,0:57:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,给我吧  我帮你扔了\NGive that to me. I'll throw it out for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.36,0:57:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我要留着\NI'm gonna hang on to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.63,0:57:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.27,0:57:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.72,0:57:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你准备好见斯卡利了吗\NYou ready for Sculley?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.99,0:57:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么回事\NExcuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.69,0:57:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨\NLisa!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.99,0:57:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,能不能别嚷\NYou can't shout!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.67,0:57:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨\NLisa?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.84,0:57:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你得走了\NYou have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.51,0:57:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,这上面危险  所以我让别人来做\NIt's dangerous up here. That's why I make other people do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.02,0:57:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你在躲谁  我还是你妈妈\NWho are you hiding from, me or your mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.51,0:57:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有躲谁\NI'm not hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.95,0:57:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,走吧\NLet's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.63,0:58:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你刚在听什么\NWhat were you listening to?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.20,0:58:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我在听同一首歌的两个版本\NI'm listening to two versions of the same song.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.52,0:58:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,等我听完了  我就倒带再听一遍\NThen when I get to the ends, I rewind to listen to them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.37,0:58:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,同一首歌  但版本不一样\NIt's the same song, but the versions are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.33,0:58:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,-什么歌  -好吧\N- What's the song? - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.23,0:58:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,是首挺老的歌  名字是《双面人生》\NSo it's a really old song, and it's called "Both Sides, Now."
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.28,0:58:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,-《双面人生》  -是\N- "Both Sides, Now"? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.71,0:58:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,唱了些什么\NWhat's it about?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.82,0:58:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,关于...\NIt's about...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.15,0:58:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,共有三段  云  爱和生活\NThere are three verses: Clouds, love and life.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.11,0:58:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,唱歌的人唱的是他们曾经的思考\NAnd the person singing is singing that they used to think of...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.83,0:58:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,他们曾思考\NThat they used to think about...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.64,0:58:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,-云  爱和生活  -对\N- Clouds, love and life? - Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.00,0:58:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,思考了一个角度\NOne way, yeah, but now
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.00,0:58:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,但现在他们换了种角度去看  然后\Nthey look at them another way, and they...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.02,0:58:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他们最终发现\NThey've come to the conclusion that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.18,0:58:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他们其实完全不了解云  爱和生活\Nthey really don't know clouds, love or life at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.76,0:58:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,歌词跟你说的一模一样\NThose are the exact words.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.33,0:58:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  琼妮·米切尔的歌\NYeah, Joni Mitchell.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.85,0:59:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这不算是首老歌  除非我也老了\N'Cause it's not a really old song, unless I'm a really old guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.99,0:59:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在得去上学了\NYou have to go to school now.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.32,0:59:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你想我告诉你\NDo you want me to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.31,0:59:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,两个版本的区别吗\Nthe differences between the two versions?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.33,0:59:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,马上\NRight now.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.10,0:59:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,第一个版本是那种\NThe first version is the kind of thing
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.45,0:59:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你会称之为少女的感觉\Nthat you would call girlish.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.46,0:59:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是说我马上想知道区别\NI didn't mean I want to know the difference right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.71,0:59:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说你要马上去上学\NI meant you have to go to school right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.21,0:59:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以留下来看\NI can stay and watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.90,0:59:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你逃课  你是在犯罪\NYou are truant. You're committing a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.36,0:59:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会落下什么重要的课程的\NI'm not gonna miss anything important.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.82,0:59:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-你怎么知道  -我预习了\N- How do you know? - I read ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.11,0:59:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,清教徒来到了新大陆\NThe Pilgrims make it to the New World.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.01,0:59:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,然后就是独立宣言\NThen the Declaration of Independence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.79,0:59:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,是  你跳了几个世纪\NYeah, you skipped a couple centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.87,0:59:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫  克里斯安在外面\NSteve? Chrisann's out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.68,0:59:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,走吧\NLet's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.53,0:59:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我能说说我能留下来的理由吗\NCan I make my case for staying?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.32,0:59:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,不行\NNope.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.72,1:00:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,她刚跟我在一起\NShe was with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.95,1:00:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,来  你爸爸不想我们待这\NCome on. Your dad doesn't want us to stay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.89,1:00:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有  我没\NThat's not true. That's not...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.78,1:00:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须去学校  仅此而已\NYou have to be in school is all.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.23,1:00:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在在犯罪\NI'm committing a crime right now,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.94,1:00:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想惹麻烦\Nand I don't wanna get in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.91,1:00:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你没惹麻烦  我开玩笑的\NYou're not in trouble. I was kidding.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.55,1:00:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.46,1:00:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,第二个版本是什么\NHey. What was the second version?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.71,1:00:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你说第一个版本很少女\NYou said the first version was girlish.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.25,1:00:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,第二个版本呢\NWhat was the second version?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.35,1:00:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我一下子还真想不到合适的词\NI can't really think of the word.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.37,1:00:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,-好  开心去上学吧  -遗憾\N- Okay. Well, have a good day at school. - Regretful.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.24,1:00:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.05,1:00:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你想重新活一次  改变些什么\NLike wishing you could go back and do things different.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.98,1:00:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你太小了  说什么遗憾\NYou're too young to be regretful.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.06,1:00:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,不是我\NNot me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.68,1:00:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,是唱歌的人\NThe person singing the song.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.53,1:00:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,懂了  遗憾  挺有道理的因为\NGot it. Regretful. That makes sense because...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.41,1:00:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我想跟你住\NI wanna live with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.18,1:01:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,六分钟\NSix minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.14,1:01:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,-你想见斯卡利吗  -不想\N- You want to see Sculley? - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.60,1:01:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我说过多少回了  你需要保安\NYou know all those times I told you you needed security?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.77,1:01:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是原因\NHere's why.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.17,1:01:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我真不明白  我都老了  你却没见老\NI don't know how it is I've gotten older and you haven't.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.48,1:01:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,是不是跟恶魔做了什么我没做的交易\NSome deal with the devil I was never offered.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.56,1:01:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我过去四年在想什么吗\NSo you know what I've been thinking for the last four years?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.43,1:01:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,其实  约翰\NAs it turns out, John,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.39,1:01:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我从来不知道你在想什么\NI've never known what you were thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.67,1:01:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,新生儿都没有控制权\NNo newborn baby has control.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.60,1:01:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你懂我在说什么吗\NDo you know what I'm talking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.32,1:01:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-84年Mac发布之前你说  -知道\N- In '84, before the Mac launch. You said... - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.58,1:01:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你说被领养意味着你没有控制权\NYou said that being adopted meant you didn't have control.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.04,1:01:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我们马上要开始了  所以...\NWe're starting in a minute, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.61,1:02:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么人们认为是我开除了你\NWhy do people think I fired you?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.74,1:02:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,没关系  约翰  都过去了\NIt's fine, John. It's all behind us.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.74,1:02:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,是吗\NIs it?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.09,1:02:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,少装傻了  你骗不了我\NDon't play stupid. You can't pull it off.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.73,1:02:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你来这问我为什么人们认为你开除了我\NYou came here to ask me why people think you fired me?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.68,1:02:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么人们认为是我开除了你\NWhy do people think I fired you?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.13,1:02:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我们来确认几件事  好吗\NJust confirm something for me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.83,1:02:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你喜欢那广告  是吧\NYou liked the ad, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.84,1:02:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,那个广告《1984》  你是喜欢的吧\NThe commercial... "1984." You liked it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.66,1:02:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,-你什么时候买家具  -太麻烦了\N- When are you gonna get furniture? - It's not an easy process.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.14,1:02:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,不麻烦  你先买沙发  一件件就齐了\NIt is. You buy a couch, take it from there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.21,1:02:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我实在是想不到\NI'd be really surprised if
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.38,1:02:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你过来跟是我讨论室内装潢的\Nyou came here to talk about interior decorating.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.67,1:02:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我很喜欢那广告\NI liked the ad very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.05,1:02:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你喜欢\NYou did?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.55,1:02:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我喜欢的  现在请回答我的问题\NYou know I did. Now please answer my question.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.51,1:02:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你他妈就是个骗子  你想扼杀了它\NYou're a lying son of a bitch. You tried to kill it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.38,1:02:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,是时候仔细审视一下Mac了\NIt's time to take a hard look at the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.15,1:02:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,已经落后时代了\NIt's past time.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.40,1:02:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,定价过高  我们要降价到1995元\NIt's overpriced. We need to drop it to 1,995.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.53,1:02:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要把营销预算翻一倍\NWe need to double the marketing budget,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.35,1:02:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,分配更多人手去做内置硬盘\Nput more bodies on an internal hard drive
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.51,1:02:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,在文件服务器上投资\Nand invest in FileServer.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.93,1:02:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你到底从哪得知\NWhere the hell did you get the idea
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.03,1:02:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,-我要撤掉...  -李·克罗\N- that I tried to kill... - Lee Clow.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.32,1:02:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,-李错了  -他说谎吗\N- Lee's wrong. - He's lying?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.62,1:02:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-他  弄错了  -钱从哪来\N- He's... mistaken. - Where would the money come from?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.97,1:03:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,把早该扔掉的Apple Ⅱ扔了就有了\NIt would come from finally getting rid of the Apple II.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.25,1:03:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Ⅱ是唯一在赚钱的产品\NThe Apple II is the only thing making money.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.37,1:03:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你跟董事会站在了一边\NYou agreed with the board.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.37,1:03:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我明白董事会的顾虑  但我\NI understood the board's concerns, but I...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.35,1:03:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,董事会的顾虑是我们没展示出产品吗\NThe board's concerns that we didn't show the product?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.39,1:03:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,还有其他原因  问题在于\NAmong other things, but my question was...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.84,1:03:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,什么原因\NWhat other things honestly?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.99,1:03:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是好奇  你说"还有其他原因"\NI'm asking because I'm curious. You said "Among other things."
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.67,1:03:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,还有就是它的背景设定在反乌托邦星系\NAmong other things, it was set in a dystopian galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.30,1:03:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,发生在一个不是地球的星球上\NIt took place on a planet where we don't live.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.30,1:03:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这很黑暗  而且跟我们品牌相违背\NIt was dark and the opposite of our brand.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.45,1:03:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,再加上我们没展示产品\NAnd we didn't show the product.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.53,1:03:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,人们谈论那则广告\NPeople talked about the ad but
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.54,1:03:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,但没什么人知道我们在卖什么\Nmost of them didn't know what we were selling.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.13,1:03:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mac需要卖1995块\NThe Mac needs to sell for 1,995.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.57,1:03:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,没有任何市场调查告诉我们说\NThere is no market research telling us
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.34,1:03:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mac会因为定价过高而失败\Nthe Mac is failing because it's overpriced.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.57,1:03:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,调查表明人们不喜欢\NIt's telling us that people don't like it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.30,1:03:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,是因为他们认为它没什么用\Nbecause they think it doesn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.35,1:03:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个封闭结构  端到端\NIt's closed, end-to-end.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.85,1:03:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我们之前不知道人们不想买这个\NWe didn't know it wasn't what people wanted,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.72,1:03:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们确实不想\Nbut it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.34,1:03:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,他们想要插槽  想要选择  想要空间\NThey want slots, they want choices, they want options.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.46,1:03:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我们买音响一样  配件自由组合\NThe way we buy stereos... mix and match components.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.83,1:03:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰  听我说\NJohn, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.01,1:03:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我敢保证跟你说顾客永远正确的人\NWhoever said the customer is always right was,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.79,1:03:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,他自己就是顾客\NI promise you, a customer.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.04,1:03:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,-那里面有光头党  -她解放了他们\N- It had skinheads in it. - She was liberating them.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.43,1:03:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,解放光头党\NLiberating the skinheads.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.32,1:03:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,那广告跟什么鬼光头党一点关系都没有\NThe ad didn't have anything to do with fucking skinheads.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.70,1:03:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就他妈把他们当临时演员用\NWe used them as fucking extras.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.27,1:03:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,根本没人知道他们是光头党\NNobody even knows they were skinheads.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.66,1:04:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是说董事会有顾虑\NI'm just saying the board had concerns...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.23,1:04:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你发明了生活模式营销\NYou invented lifestyle advertising.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.84,1:04:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的品牌就是我的品牌\NAnd our brand was my brand.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.91,1:04:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我的职责是给董事会提建议\NMy job is to make a recommendation to the board.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.48,1:04:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我们展现的是很多人开心地喝着百事\NWe showed a lot of happy people drinking Pepsi.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.42,1:04:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可没说\NWe didn't say
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.05,1:04:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你不买百事世界就灭亡了\Nthe world was going to end if you bought a Dr. Pepper.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.35,1:04:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,去建议他们降低价格和增加营销售预算吧\NRecommend that we drop the price and double the marketing budget.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.98,1:04:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-我做不到  -而且我们展示了产品\N- I can't. - And we showed the product.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.80,1:04:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我们展现了它被打开\NWe showed it being opened,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.02,1:04:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们展现了它被倒出来  被喝掉\Nwe showed it being poured, being consumed.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.32,1:04:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那你怎么打算  建议我们取消Mac吗\NWhat are you gonna do, recommend that we kill the Mac?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.76,1:04:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经建议了  史蒂夫\NI already have, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.12,1:04:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,什么  什么时候\NWhat? When?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.84,1:04:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得你成功的秘诀在于\NYou think the secret to your success
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.60,1:04:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,是假定人们知道怎么享受一罐汽水吗\Nwas not assuming people knew what to do with a can of soda?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.89,1:04:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有取消那广告  史蒂夫\NI didn't kill the ad, Steve!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.48,1:04:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,正是因为我它才能播出来\NI'm the only reason it made it on the air.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.82,1:04:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,就刚才  一小时前\NJust now. An hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.59,1:04:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我从马库拉家出来的时候\NI'm coming from Markkula's house.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.01,1:04:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他说什么\NWhat did he say?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.29,1:04:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,-他说什么  -创造点新东西\N- What did he say? - Invent something new.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.23,1:04:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我会给你个团队  你待在毛伊岛都行\NI'll give you a team. You can sit in Maui.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.14,1:04:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不光度假  还送你沙发\NThe resorts come with couches.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.67,1:04:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,等等  你是说你提议终结Mac项目\NWait a minute. Are you saying you recommended terminating the Mac
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.84,1:04:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,还是你提议让我退出Mac团队\Nor you recommended taking me off the Mac team?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.81,1:04:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在超级碗买了三个广告时段\NWe bought three spots in the Super Bowl.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.56,1:05:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,两个30秒  一个60秒\NTwo 30's and a 60.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.85,1:05:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,放过广告之后  董事会希望收回那笔钱\NAfter we screened it, the board wanted that money back
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.74,1:05:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他们要我抛售这些广告时段\Nand they asked me to sell off the spots.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.62,1:05:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,李岱艾广告公司把两个30秒的卖了\NChiat/Day sold off the two 30's
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.11,1:05:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,但60秒的没有\Nbut not the 60,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.84,1:05:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我对李·克罗说得清清楚楚\Nand I let it be known to Lee Clow
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.26,1:05:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,就算他不努力把最后那个时段卖掉\Nthat if he didn't try very hard to sell the last spot,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.12,1:05:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我也不会不开心\NI wouldn't be unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.38,1:05:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们降价再加倍预算\NIf we drop the price and double the budget...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.84,1:05:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,降价或加倍预算\NDrop the price or double the budget.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.64,1:05:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,唯一的方法是从Apple Ⅱ那里拿钱\NThe only way to do that is to take money out of the Apple II.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.65,1:05:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Ⅱ都丢你的人  它让我丢人\NThe Apple II should embarrass you. It embarrasses me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.72,1:05:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,股东没觉得丢人\NIt doesn't embarrass the shareholders.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.00,1:05:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,股东关我屁事\NI don't give a shit about the shareholders.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.70,1:05:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我才雇了你\NThat's why I hired you,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.72,1:05:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我就不用听股东啰嗦了\Nso I don't have to hear about shareholders.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.79,1:05:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,股东是我的问题所在\NThe shareholders are my problem,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.32,1:05:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,董事会代表的就是股东\Nand the board represents the shareholders.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.95,1:05:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是规矩\NThat's how it works.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.55,1:05:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定不是李·克罗故意拖着不卖60秒时段\NYou sure it wasn't Lee Clow who dragged his feet selling the 60?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.24,1:05:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,是我让他拖着的  史蒂夫\NAt my direction, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.16,1:05:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得他自己有这个胆子拍板\NYou think he would have done that on his own,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.13,1:05:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,自己担这个责任吗\Ntaken it on himself?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.17,1:05:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,是  我觉得他会拼命从你那救下60秒\NYeah. I think he would've done what it took to save it from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.22,1:05:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,想留住那60秒的只有我\NI was the only thing protecting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.97,1:05:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你不想要那广告\NYou didn't want the ad
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.68,1:05:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你想要\Nbecause you were trying to
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.45,1:05:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,在Mac上市两个月前停了Mac项目\Nkill the Mac two months before it launched.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.98,1:05:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你他妈就是一妄想狂\NYou are fucking delusional.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.92,1:05:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-我能说个事吗  -说\N- Can I mention something to you? - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.52,1:05:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我完全不明白你为什么在这里\NI have no earthly idea why you're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.88,1:06:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你离开苹果的原因和过程\NThe story of why and how you left Apple,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.09,1:06:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,转眼就传疯了  但那都是假的\Nwhich is quickly becoming mythologized, isn't true.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.98,1:06:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,-我要亲自去跟董事会说  -别那样做\N- I'm gonna take this to the board myself. - Don't do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.24,1:06:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,-我就要去  -不能去\N- I am doing that. - You can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.25,1:06:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.86,1:06:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他们认为这家公司不再需要你了\NThey believe you're no longer necessary to this company.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.33,1:06:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我收到恐吓信  死亡威胁\NI get hate mail, death threats.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.66,1:06:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,有人威胁要杀我\NI get death threats.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.96,1:06:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我的孩子被人嘲弄\NMy kids are getting taunted.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.34,1:06:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么人们认为是我开除了你\NWhy do people think I fired you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.26,1:06:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,乔安娜马上要宣布我的名字了\NJoanna's gonna call my name in a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.70,1:06:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-史蒂夫  -我们可没排练过\N- Steve? - That was unrehearsed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.76,1:06:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,好  我马上过去\NYeah, I'll be there in just a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.35,1:06:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我给了你申诉的机会\NI gave you your day in court.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.80,1:06:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-你给我  -我给了董事会明确的选择\N- You gave me? - I gave the board a clear choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.70,1:06:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我说"你们想投资给Apple Ⅱ\NI said, "Do you want to invest in the Apple II
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.38,1:06:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,还是Mac"  他们选了Apple Ⅱ\Nor the Mac?" They chose the Apple II.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.93,1:06:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,他们就是想放弃超级碗广告时段的那群人\NThe same people who wanted to dump the Super Bowl spot.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.82,1:06:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我就上了去中国的飞机\NAnd then I got on a plane to China.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.12,1:06:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,斯卡利先生  一号线有您电话\NMr. Sculley. There's a call for you on Line One.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.66,1:06:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,或者说我差点上了飞机\NOr I almost got on a plane,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.33,1:06:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我在候机室接了通电话\Nbecause I got a call in the lounge.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.64,1:07:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-谁的电话  -不重要\N- Who made that call? - Doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.15,1:07:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,对我来说很重要  谁的电话\NIt matters to me. Who made the call?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.27,1:07:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰·斯卡利\NJohn Sculley.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.07,1:07:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰  如果你上了飞机\NJohn? If you get on that plane,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.04,1:07:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,落地时你就被解雇了\Nyou'll have lost your job by the time it lands.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.10,1:07:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫要求召开董事会  他想要你离开\NSteve's been calling the board. He wants you out.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.55,1:07:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我的行李都留在飞机上了\NI left my bags on the plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.80,1:07:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我那堆东西现在还在北京的某个角落\NMy shit's still somewhere in Beijing.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.21,1:07:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,大晚上的\NI took a car back to
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.21,1:07:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我搭了辆车回到库比蒂诺\NCupertino in the middle of the fucking night.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.44,1:07:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道现在几点\NI know what time it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.35,1:07:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,一小时内我需要法定人数到场\NI need a quorum here in one hour
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.90,1:07:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我还要史蒂夫出席\Nand I want Steve here too.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.40,1:07:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你让我离开Mac团队  是错误的决定\NYou took me off the Mac, and it was bad business.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.23,1:07:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-召集法定人数就是谋杀  -就是这个\N- The quorum call was a homicide. - Right there! Right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.78,1:07:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这个部分胡说八道  朋友\NThat's the part that's bullshit, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.39,1:07:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,这是自杀\NIt was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.96,1:07:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你知道自己的牌  而我亮了牌\NBecause you knew your cards and I showed you mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.73,1:07:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我亮了牌  你还是这么做了\NI showed you mine, and you did it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.60,1:07:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得我要做什么\NWhat did you think I was gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.86,1:07:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我出局没关系  但我不会束手就擒\NI'm okay losing, but I'm not gonna forfeit.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.02,1:07:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,但我不想输\NI'm not okay losing.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.26,1:07:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我们损失了市场份额  Mac在亏损\NWe're losing market share, and the Mac is losing money.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.01,1:07:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我们唯一的希望是Apple Ⅱ\NOur only hope is the Apple II,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.54,1:07:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,它现在停滞不前\Nwhich is stagnating
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.45,1:07:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,因为用的是快要过时了的DOS操作系统\Nbecause of its soon-to-be-obsolete DOS.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.76,1:07:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,用户已经在改装自己的电脑\NUsers are already rigging their machines
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.53,1:07:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,以运行CP/M操作系统\Nto run with a CP/M operating system
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.22,1:07:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,这系统就是基于英特尔处理器的\Nthat's been built to run on Intel.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.42,1:07:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我尽可能简洁地总结一下\NI can't put it more simply than this.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.93,1:08:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要集中资源升级Apple Ⅱ\NWe need to put our resources into updating the Apple II.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.19,1:08:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,但这会从Mac那里抢走资源\NBy taking resources from the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.50,1:08:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mac要失败了  这是事实\NIt's failing. That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.01,1:08:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-它定价过高了  -没有任何证据表明\N- It's overpriced. - There's no evidence that it's...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.05,1:08:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是证据\NI'm the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.87,1:08:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我是世界顶尖的Mac专家  约翰\NI'm the world's leading expert on the Mac,John.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.83,1:08:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你又有什么资格\NWhat's your resume?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.80,1:08:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你总是下达相互矛盾的指令\NYou're issuing contradictory instructions,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.54,1:08:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你还拒不服从  你让人痛苦不堪\Nyou're insubordinate, you make people miserable.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.82,1:08:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的顶尖工程师\NOur top engineers
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.96,1:08:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,都逃去了太阳  戴尔和惠普\Nare fleeing to Sun, Dell, HP.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.82,1:08:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,华尔街不知道谁是老大\NWall Street doesn't know who's driving the bus.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.24,1:08:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的损失数以亿计\NWe've lost hundreds of millions in value.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.10,1:08:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,以及我是苹果的CEO  史蒂夫\NAnd I'm the CEO of Apple, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.09,1:08:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我的资格\NThat's my resume.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.08,1:08:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,但之前你就是个卖汽水的  对吗\NBut before that, you sold carbonated sugar water, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.64,1:08:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我跟沃兹尼亚克在个破车库里开创了未来\NI sat in a fucking garage with Wozniak and invented the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.36,1:08:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,因为艺术家才能引领\NBecause artists lead
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.62,1:08:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,而二流权棍只会要求投票\Nand hacks ask for a show of hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.31,1:08:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,那好\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.89,1:08:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,这个家伙疯了\NWell, this guy's out of control.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.79,1:08:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我一点都不介意今晚就递交辞呈\NI'm perfectly willing to hand in my resignation tonight,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.37,1:08:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果你们要我留下  史蒂夫就得走\Nbut if you want me to stay, you can't have Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.36,1:08:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,把他弄走\NSettle him out.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.96,1:08:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他可以留点股票  好收到公司的简报\NHe can keep a share of stock so he gets our newsletter.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.85,1:08:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,他必须跟苹果公司一刀两断\NHe'll have to sever his connection to Apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.46,1:08:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我是认真的  我请秘书长发起投票\NI'm dead serious. I want the secretary to call for a vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.29,1:09:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你他妈敢\NI fucking dare you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.36,1:09:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你这些年来把这些个媒体\NYou have done an outstanding job
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.93,1:09:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,调教得很听话\Nover the years of cultivating the press.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.80,1:09:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我指的就是操纵媒体\NAnd by that, I mean manipulating them.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.49,1:09:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,因为直到今天  也没有一个编辑\NBecause none of them, none of their editors,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.80,1:09:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,也没有一个出版社\Nnone of their editors' publishers
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.91,1:09:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,知道正是你自己作的\Nto this day know that you forced it,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.49,1:09:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,是你逼着董事会解雇了你\Nthat you forced the board.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.30,1:09:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我甚至提前警告过你他们会解雇你\NEven after I told you exactly what they'd do,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.28,1:09:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,而他们也正是这样做的\Nwhich is exactly what they did.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.49,1:09:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,全票同意解雇你\NUnanimously.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.89,1:09:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,当时的一切我都记得很清楚  约翰\NI don't have any trouble remembering that, John,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.35,1:09:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,因为那是我这辈子最糟糕的一个晚上\Nbecause of it being the worst night of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.08,1:09:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我强行发起投票是因为我坚信自己没有错\NAnd I forced the vote because I believed I was right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.18,1:09:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我仍然相信自己是对的  我就是对的\NI still believe I'm right. And I'm right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.81,1:09:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,那晚我的心里在流血\NNow I bled that night.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.53,1:09:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,现在血不流了\NAnd I don't bleed.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.64,1:09:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但是时间已经治愈了一切\NBut time's done its thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.30,1:09:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经好久没仔细考虑过那些事了\Nand I really haven't thought about it in a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.59,1:09:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我非常理解你为什么不开心\NNow, I absolutely understand why you're upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.70,1:09:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我也想让公众知道事情的真相\NAnd I want people to know the truth too.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.86,1:09:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,该上场了\NIt's time.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.22,1:09:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,好的\NGot it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.70,1:09:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你会把我毁了  对吗\NYou're gonna end me, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.57,1:10:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,别傻了\NYou're being ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.24,1:10:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我就静静地看着你自己把自己毁掉\NI'm gonna sit center court and watch you do it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.36,1:10:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我会点一桌好菜\NThen I'm gonna order a nice
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.35,1:10:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,加一瓶55年的玛歌酒  再签几个名\Nmeal with a '55 Margaux and sign some autographs.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.21,1:10:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝啊\NJesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.94,1:10:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你需要点建议吗  汽水大师\NYou want some advice, Pepsi Generation?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.82,1:10:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,别把沃兹推到媒体面前说我的坏话\NDon't send Woz out to slap me around in the press.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.37,1:10:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,其他人都可以\NAnybody else...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.10,1:10:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你  马库拉或者亚瑟·洛克\Nyou, Markkula, Arthur Rock.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.28,1:10:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,就是我那天才哥们不行\NAnyone but Rain Man.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.90,1:10:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,别那样操纵他\NDon't manipulate him like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.39,1:10:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,不管你怎么想  我会永远保护他的\NWhatever you may think, I'm always gonna protect him.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.32,1:10:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧  史蒂夫\NCome on, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.73,1:10:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这才是男人做的事\NThat's what men do.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.25,1:10:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不能再迟了\NWe can't start late.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.06,1:10:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我不觉得我在翻旧账\NI don't think there was any way to detect a chip on my shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.77,1:10:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗  以前在苹果的时候\NDid you know, back at Bandley,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.23,1:10:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Mac团队每年都会\Nthe Mac team gave an award
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.04,1:10:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,给敢于反抗你的人颁奖\Nevery year to the person who could stand up to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.88,1:10:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.05,1:11:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,-我连赢了三年  -不错啊\N- I won. Three years in a row. - Cool.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.31,1:11:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,这个人\NThis.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.78,1:11:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,这个《Macworld》的盖伊·川崎\NThis... This Guy Kawasaki in Macworld.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.88,1:11:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,他碰巧猜对了  对不对\NHe accidentally got it right, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.46,1:11:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你一直在拖延NeXT系统的进度\NYou've been dragging your feet on the NeXT OS
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.33,1:11:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,是为了搞清楚苹果公司的需求\Ntill you can figure out what Apple's gonna need.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.22,1:11:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,就算他猜对了  对我来说也没那么邪恶\NEven if that were true, it doesn't sound that diabolical to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.75,1:11:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我们准备好了\NHey. We're ready for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.25,1:11:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我是你的朋友  你的知己\NI'm your closest confidante, your... your best friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.27,1:11:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,用你的话叫什么来着\NYour thing... What do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.32,1:11:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,工作上的爱人  一直都是\NYour work wife. The whole time.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.96,1:11:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,过去三年都是\NThe last three years.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.01,1:11:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你是什么时候改了主意\NWhen did you change your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.14,1:11:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,开始密谋"史蒂夫·乔布斯复仇计划"的\Nand start building the Steve Jobs Revenge Machine?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.75,1:11:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,会场已经坐满一半了\NHouse to half.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.33,1:12:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你记得"天空实验室"吗\NYou remember Skylab?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.21,1:12:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,美国宇航局在70年代发射的\NIt was an unmanned satellite NASA
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.98,1:12:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,一颗用来收集情报的无人卫星\Nsent up in the early '70s on a data gathering mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.94,1:12:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但事实上  在发射的时候\NThe thing is, when they sent it up,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.62,1:12:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他们并不知道怎么回收它\Nthey didn't know yet how they were gonna get it back.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.36,1:12:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但是他们认为有充分的可能\NBut they felt like they were close enough
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.04,1:12:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,会在卫星上天执行任务的八年里\Nthat in the eight years it was gonna be up there,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.40,1:12:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,把回收方式搞清楚\Nthey'd figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.51,1:12:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,他们快到了\NThey're on their way now.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.43,1:12:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,他们终究没搞清楚\NThey didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.63,1:12:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,所以八年后  那颗卫星\NSo after eight years, it came crashing down
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.84,1:12:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,在印度洋上空划着数千英里的轨迹坠毁了\Nin a thousand-mile swath across the Indian Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.11,1:12:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,稍微有一点偏差\NA little to the left, a little to the right,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.08,1:12:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,就可能伤及无辜\Nsomebody could have gotten hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.22,1:12:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我真心想为大学设计一部电脑\NI really wanted to build a computer for colleges.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.10,1:12:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,只是技术的发展跟不上我的需求\NThe technology just didn't catch up as fast as I needed it to.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.27,1:12:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我们的资金用完了\NYou know we're out of money.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.35,1:12:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们\NLadies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.96,1:12:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,发布会马上开始\Nthe program will be starting momentarily.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.10,1:12:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,但当苹果公司不再创新\NBut then Apple stopped innovating,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.28,1:12:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我看到了新的机遇\Nand I saw something better.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.63,1:12:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,乔安娜  我知道学校不会去花一万三千美元\NJoanna, I know schools aren't gonna buy a $13,000
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.11,1:12:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,买一台音响不错的电子词典的\Ndictionary with good speakers.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.70,1:12:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我很清楚这一点\NYou know I know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.46,1:12:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,但是苹果公司会来买\NBut Apple will.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.25,1:13:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,因为阿维·特瓦尼安正在开发\N'Cause Avie Tevanian is
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.32,1:13:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,一个正合他们需要的操作系统\Ngonna build them exactly the OS they need.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.69,1:13:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这样他们也得把我买回去\NThey're gonna have to buy me too.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.16,1:13:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,并给我五亿美元的股票\NFor half a billion dollars in stock
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.55,1:13:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,和每个产品上端到端的控制\Nand end-to-end control on every product.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.86,1:13:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们  让我们欢迎\NLadies and gentlemen, please welcome...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.01,1:13:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,在业内人士\NMore than a year
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.65,1:13:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,面前亮相一年之后\Nafter it was first unveiled to industry insiders,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.41,1:13:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,NeXT电脑终于上架销售了\Nthe NeXT Computer is finally available in stores.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.97,1:14:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,但这似乎是对史蒂夫·乔布斯的连续打击\NAnd it appears to be two strikes in a row for Steve Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.56,1:14:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,学生和老师们\NStudents and educators
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.15,1:14:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,对这台电脑的高价无法理解\Nare finding it difficult to justify the machine's high cost.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.35,1:14:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,真是黑立方的多事之秋\NSo much for the black cube.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.13,1:14:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,NeXT刚刚把工厂卖给了佳能\NNeXT just sold its factory to Canon
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.48,1:14:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,并且裁掉了半数的员工\Nand laid off half its employees.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.02,1:14:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,在电脑的世界里  不是你死就是我死\NIn the world of computers, it's kill or be killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.08,1:14:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,苹果电脑公司处境艰难\NApple Computer has fallen on hard times.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.40,1:14:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,公司正在裁员2500人\NIt is laying off about 2,500 people.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.94,1:14:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,苹果公司进一步丢失市场份额\NApple is continuing to lose market share,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.37,1:14:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,除了CEO 约翰·斯卡利的"小玩具"牛顿\Nwith no new innovations in the pipeline except the Newton,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.20,1:14:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,它的产品线毫无创新\Na pet project of CEO John Sculley.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.49,1:14:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,移动生活  你需要一台牛顿掌上电脑\NIf you really want to be mobile, you want a Newton PDA.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.07,1:14:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,可能你并不需要\NBut then again, maybe you don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.42,1:14:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,它可以把手写文字变成电脑字符\NIt turns handwriting into computer text.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.72,1:14:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,多尔夫  在你的牛顿记下这句话\NHey, Dolph, take a memo on your Newton.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.10,1:14:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"打败马丁"\N"Beat up Martin."
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.45,1:14:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}打败马丁
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.66,1:14:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}吃掉Martha
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.16,1:14:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,1980年  苹果拥有三成的市场份额\NIn 1980, Apple had 30% of the market.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.96,1:14:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,现在只剩下可怜的3.2%了\NToday, Apple has only 3.2 percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.66,1:14:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,结束了\NThat's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.67,1:14:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰·斯卡利被苹果公司解雇了\NJohn Sculley has been fired from Apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.84,1:14:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}被解雇
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.67,1:14:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}被解雇
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.09,1:14:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}被解雇
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.33,1:14:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你对互联网有什么看法\NWhat about this Internet thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.34,1:14:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你对它了解多少\NDo you know anything about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.88,1:14:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,它是个全新的概念\NIt is the big new thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.55,1:15:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,关于谁将执掌苹果电脑公司的传言\NRumors are flying around Apple Computer once again
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.99,1:15:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,甚嚣尘上\Nover who will take over the helm.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.66,1:15:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这是高科技界意义非凡的重聚\NIn the news at this hour, a remarkable high-tech reunion.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.40,1:15:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,事情确实发生了\NWell, it's happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.57,1:15:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,在一笔数十亿美元的交易中\NIn a billion-dollar shakeup,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.99,1:15:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,苹果收购了NeXT操作系统\NApple is purchasing NeXT Computer's operating system,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.94,1:15:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,这可能导致...\Nwhich may mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.59,1:15:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,浪子回头吗\NIs the prodigal son returning?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.02,1:15:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我打赌是的\NBet on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.57,1:15:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你猜怎么着  Mac回来了\NGuess what. Mac is back.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.47,1:15:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,苹果公司联合创始人史蒂夫·乔布斯\NApple cofounder Steven Jobs...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.84,1:15:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,-史蒂夫·乔布斯  -史蒂夫·乔布斯\N- Steve Jobs... - Steve Jobs...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.64,1:15:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,-史蒂夫·乔布斯  -史蒂夫·乔布斯\N- Steve Jobs... - Steve Jobs...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.28,1:15:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫·乔布斯回归苹果公司\NSteve Jobs is returning to Apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.20,1:15:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(300,104)}旧金山
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.63,1:15:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想从数码相机\NIf you want to beam your
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.79,1:15:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(311.25,188)}交响乐厅
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.29,1:15:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,里面传送数码照片\Ndigital photographs from your digital camera,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.39,1:15:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,每个设备都有这样的功能\Nit's built into every product.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.22,1:15:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我们选用了新一代输入/输出系统\NWe're going to the new generation of I/O.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.58,1:15:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,两个12兆的USB接口\NTwelve megabyte USB. Two ports.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.12,1:15:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我们放弃了陈旧的苹果输入/输出设备\NWe're leaving the old Apple I/O behind.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.74,1:15:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,每种产品都内置立体环绕声\NStereo surround sound built into every product,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.22,1:15:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}12兆USB(2个)
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.22,1:15:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}环绕立体声
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.22,1:15:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}键盘与鼠标
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.36,1:15:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,优秀的键盘和最酷的鼠标\Na great keyboard and the coolest mouse you've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.08,1:15:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这次我们用的是真的老鼠\NThis time, we used actual mice.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.63,1:15:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我们十分钟后开门放人  史蒂文\NWe're opening the house in 10 minutes. Steven?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.70,1:15:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以别再胡闹了吗\NDo you want to stop horsing around?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.67,1:15:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我看到的是真的吗\NBless my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.09,1:15:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,坐在那里的是史蒂夫·沃兹尼亚克\NThat's Steve Wozniak sitting out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.85,1:16:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你们过去碰碰运气\NGive yourselves a treat and
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.84,1:16:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,问沃兹知不知道时间吧\Nask Woz if he happens to have the correct time.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.38,1:16:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道时间  而且我们就快没时间了\NI have the correct time, and we're running out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.33,1:16:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"优秀的键盘"\N"A great keyboard"...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.19,1:16:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,优秀的键盘和最酷的鼠标\NA great keyboard and the coolest mouse you've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.70,1:16:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,那些东西现在是这个样子的\NThis is what those things look like today.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.84,1:16:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,现在  我想让你们看看它们未来的样子\NNow, I'd like to show you what they're gonna look like tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.14,1:16:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是iMac\NThis is the iMac.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.24,1:16:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(188.25,37)}你好
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.28,1:16:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(188.25,37)}你好
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.82,1:16:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(189,110)}(再一次)
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.86,1:16:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(189,110)}(再一次)
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.08,1:16:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这次不错啊\NThat was cool.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.69,1:16:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么我觉得这次效果格外好呢\NWhy did I like that better than I usually do?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.59,1:16:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-我不知道  -肯定有什么不一样了\N- I don't know. - Something was different.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.57,1:16:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,笨蛋\NHey, stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.33,1:17:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得她在跟你们说话呢\NI think she's talking to one of you guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.64,1:17:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,-注意到区别了吗  -这正是我...\N- Did you notice a difference? - That's what I'm...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.31,1:17:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,应急出口的灯灭了\NThe exit signs were off.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.41,1:17:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,-完全的黑暗  -你做到了\N- Full blackout. - You did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.76,1:17:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,所有出口的灯都连到我们的控制台了\NWe wired all the exit lights to our board.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.35,1:17:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,它们在演示期间熄灭7秒钟后会再次亮起\NThey go out with the cue for seven seconds then come back on again.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.82,1:17:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,理论上是这样\NIn theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.47,1:17:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,这样做合法吗\NWe think that's legal?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.58,1:17:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我们很确定这并不合法\NNo, we're very certain it's not.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.04,1:17:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,-你想看些评论吗  -先不用了\N- You want to see some quotes? - Let's hold off on those.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.64,1:17:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他会喜欢这个的\NNo, he'll like 'em.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.40,1:17:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-我等下再给你看  -我现在就要看\N- I'll show 'em to you later. - I'll take 'em now.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.93,1:17:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-抱歉  -请从那里重新开始\N- I'm sorry. - Pick it up from there, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.04,1:17:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只有几分钟了  做360度展示吧\NWe only have a couple of minutes, so let's just do the 360.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.91,1:17:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要使用一个从松下偷来的无线摄像机\NWe're gonna bring out a wireless camera we stole from Panasonic.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.41,1:17:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我会给你们展示它的样子\NI'll show you what this looks like.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.58,1:17:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,整个机器是半透明的  可以看到里面\NThe whole thing is translucent. You can see into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.53,1:17:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得我的折中办法怎么样  沃兹\NHow's that for a compromise, Woz?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.15,1:17:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你还是没法打开它\NYou still can't get into it,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.52,1:17:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-但是你可以看到内部  -还不错\N- but you can see into it. - Fair enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.97,1:17:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我们把扬声器放在前面  红外线在上面\NWe put stereo speakers in front, infrared right up here,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.42,1:17:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,CD驱动器在中间\NCD-ROM drive in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.10,1:17:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,-太棒了  -双立体声耳机插孔\N- Nice. - Dual stereo headphone jacks.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.96,1:17:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的接口都藏在这个漂亮的小门里面\NAll the connectors are inside one beautiful little door here.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.49,1:18:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,网络接口  USB接口\NEthernet. USB.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.95,1:18:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管这是台纯正的麦金塔电脑\NEven though this is a full-blooded Macintosh,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.94,1:18:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的目标是满足消费者\Nwe're targeting it for the number one use
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.78,1:18:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,对电脑的最迫切的需求  那就是\Nthe consumers tell us they want a computer for, which is...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.58,1:18:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,等一下  暂停一下\NLet's hold it, please. Hold it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.10,1:18:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,答案是"互联网"\NThe answer was "The Internet."
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.66,1:18:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,-乔安娜 -来了\N- Joanna? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.20,1:18:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,站到我面前来\NStand in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.93,1:18:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我想看看这些评论\NI want to look at these quotes,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.99,1:18:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我不想让乔尔知道\Nbut I don't want Joel to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.20,1:18:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,评论都很正面\NThey're all great.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.26,1:18:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"这不仅仅是近几年上市的电脑中\N"It is not only the coolest-looking computer introduced in years
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.06,1:18:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,难得一见的绝美电脑\Nbut a chest-thumping statement
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.68,1:18:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,更是一个硅谷梦想公司\Nthat Silicon Valley's original dream company
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.34,1:18:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不再迷症下去的许诺"\Nis no longer somnambulant."
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.49,1:18:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,迷症是个名词  意思是"梦游"\NIt's a word. It means "sleepwalking."
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.03,1:18:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫  不好意思\NSteve? I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.48,1:18:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要想准时开始的话现在就要清场\NWe have to clear the house if we're gonna start on time.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.38,1:18:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,-我们会准时开始的  -绝对准时\N- We're gonna start on time. - We're absolutely starting on time.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.28,1:18:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,拿着这个\NHere. Take this.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.28,1:18:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,大家到此为止吧\NEverybody, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.43,1:18:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,他们要清理舞台和座位  准备开放剧场\NThey've got to mop the stage, reset and open the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.34,1:18:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱大家\NI love you guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.70,1:19:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪  过来一下\NAndy, come on back a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.46,1:19:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,-哪个安迪 -赫茨菲尔德\N- Which one? - Hertzfeld.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.41,1:19:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,《福布斯》称之为"改变产业的成功"\NForbes calls it an "Industry-altering success."
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.93,1:19:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,看这个\NLook here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.01,1:19:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我们怎么还没睡在一起\NWhy haven't we ever slept together?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.37,1:19:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们没有相爱  看\NWe're not in love. Look.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.39,1:19:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,-斯卡利 -看他说的\N- Sculley. - Look what he said.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.91,1:19:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"他用了十五年前让苹果取得成功的\N"He has implemented the same simple
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.46,1:19:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,相同策略  那就是推出杀手级产品\Nstrategy that made Apple so successful 15 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.22,1:19:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,然后用出色的营销把它推向市场"\Nmake hit products and promote them with terrific marketing."
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.65,1:19:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,-他挺够意思的  -是的\N- It was nice of him. - It was.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.23,1:19:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说真的\NI meant it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.55,1:19:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,J·D·萨林格的看法\NSightings of J.D. Salinger
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.23,1:19:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,都不如约翰·斯卡利的认真\Nare more common than John Sculley.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.12,1:19:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有说反话  他真的很厚道\NI wasn't being sarcastic. It was nice of him.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.96,1:19:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,-你跟他有联系吗  -没有\N- Do you talk to him? - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.03,1:19:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,1988年后你就没跟他说过话\NYou haven't talked to him since '88?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.12,1:19:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有的话我就告诉你了\NI'd have told you if I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.75,1:19:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,没关系\NDoesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.98,1:19:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想让别人认为他们可以背着我做什么\NI don't want people thinking they can cross me
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.57,1:20:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,又指望若干年后能得到我谅解\Nand then, boom, 15 years later, I'm cool with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.87,1:20:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我开玩笑呢\NI was kidding.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.09,1:20:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你今天早上哪里不对劲啊\NWhat's wrong with you this morning?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.97,1:20:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我们去后台说\NLet's get off the stage.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.83,1:20:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"苹果引领的就只有颜色了"\N"The only thing Apple's providing now is leadership in colors."
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.80,1:20:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,别担心那个\NDon't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.42,1:20:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,比尔·盖茨为什么对我不满\NWhat does Bill Gates have against me?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.08,1:20:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我不清楚\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.60,1:20:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你们两个都疯了  听我说\NYou're both out of your minds. Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.64,1:20:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他辍学离开的学校比我离开的那所更好\NHe dropped out of a better school than I dropped out of.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.41,1:20:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,但他是个没用的混蛋  我来告诉你原因\NBut he's a tool bag. I'll tell you why.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.08,1:20:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,去和丽萨和好\NMake everything all right with Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.12,1:20:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我跟你说  乔安娜  注意界限\NYou know, Joanna? Boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.23,1:20:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你在凌晨一点闯进我的公寓打扫卫生\NYou've come to my apartment at 1:00 AM and cleaned it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.36,1:20:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你来跟我说说什么是界限\NSo tell me where the boundary is.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.71,1:20:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,那里  假设界限在那里\NThere. Let's say it's there.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.21,1:20:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我告诉你一些真实的预测\NIf I give you some real projections,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.78,1:20:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你能保证不在台上说出来吗\Nwill you promise not to repeat them from the stage?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.60,1:20:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"真实的预测"是什么意思\NWhat do you mean, "Real projections"?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.51,1:20:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,-你以前给我的都是什么  -保守预测\N- What have you been giving me? - Conservative projections.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.81,1:20:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,市场部在对我说谎吗\NMarketing's been lying to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.25,1:20:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我们一直在控制预期好让你不用期望太高\NWe've been managing expectations so that you don't not.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.42,1:21:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,那真实的预测是什么\NWhat are the real projections?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.33,1:21:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在90天内能卖掉100万台\NWe're gonna sell a million units in the first 90 days.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.75,1:21:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,之后每个月20000台\N20,000 a month after that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.27,1:21:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-我的天啊  -没错\N- Holy shit. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.47,1:21:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,看到了吧  这么久的等待终于...\NYou see? You wait long enough and...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.10,1:21:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,另外  32%的购买者\NWhat's more, 32% of the sales
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.62,1:21:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,将会是第一次购买电脑\Nare going to go to people buying a computer for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.64,1:21:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,而12%的购买者\NAnd 12% are going to people
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.94,1:21:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,以前用的是安装了Windows的电脑\Nusing some kind of Windows machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.49,1:21:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是比尔·盖茨对你不满的原因\NThat's what Bill Gates has against you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.71,1:21:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,而且它将会是史上销售最快的电脑\NAnd it'll be the fastest-selling computer in history.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.61,1:21:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,在经历了裁员3000人\NYou brought the company back from life support
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.67,1:21:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,和放弃了70%的产品线的痛苦后\Nafter going through the misery of laying off 3,000 people
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.47,1:21:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你终于让这家公司起死回生了\Nand cutting 70% of the product line.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.65,1:21:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,所以  史蒂文  都结束了\NSo, Steven, it's over.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.78,1:21:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你赢定了\NYou're gonna win.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.36,1:21:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,不享受这种时刻\NIt would be criminal
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.49,1:21:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-简直是一种罪过  -我很享受\N- not to enjoy this moment. - I'm enjoying it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.52,1:21:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,那就去和丽萨和好吧\NMake things all right with Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.44,1:21:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,-你知道吗  -快去吧\N- You know... - Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.65,1:21:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我不喜欢缺少隐私的感觉\NI don't like having less privacy than other people have.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.36,1:21:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,成为一个亿万富翁\NDoes being a multi-billionaire
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.14,1:22:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,-会让你感觉好一点吗  -不\N- take some of the sting off that? - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.08,1:22:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-丽萨只是... -丽萨只是点了头\N- All Lisa did... - All Lisa did was give her blessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.27,1:22:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,克里斯安就把房子卖了\NChrisann sold the house and...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.95,1:22:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那丽萨有什么办法呢\NAnd Lisa could have done what?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.40,1:22:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,她要怎么阻止她母亲\NHow was she supposed to
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.52,1:22:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,卖掉她自己的房子\Nstop her mother from selling her own house?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.09,1:22:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我给她们两个买的\NThat I bought for the two of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.53,1:22:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,她为什么要阻止她母亲\NHow was she supposed to stop her?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.47,1:22:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,她只要提醒她妈一句\NVoicing an objection would
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.66,1:22:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,可能就能阻止她犯错\Nhave been a step in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.04,1:22:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,对于一个19岁女孩没能阻止妈妈卖房子\NYou don't think you're having a bizarre overreaction
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.21,1:22:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你不觉得你有点反应过激了吗\Nto a 19-year-old girl allowing her mother to list her own house?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.28,1:22:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,她至少该试试\NShe could've tried.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.12,1:22:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,难道她应该去阻止自己的母亲吗\NWas she supposed to stop her mother, that particular mother...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.77,1:22:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,她同意她母亲卖掉房子\NShe gave Chrisann her blessing to sell the house
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.97,1:22:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,就是为了向我甩脸色\Nand she did it to spite me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.82,1:22:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,她就算在热水器里放炸弹我都不在乎\NI don't care if she put a pipe bomb in the water heater.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.86,1:22:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在要跟她和好\NYou're going to fix it, now.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.59,1:22:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,她这几个月一直怪怪的  她跟我杠上了\NShe's been acting weird for months. She's turned on me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.36,1:22:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,-去跟她道歉  -你搞什么...\N- Fix it. - What the...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.32,1:22:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,去跟她道歉  史蒂夫\NFix it, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.11,1:22:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,-别紧张  -要不我就辞职\N- Take it easy. - Fix it or I quit.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.09,1:22:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么样  我走人  你再也见不到我了\NHow about that? I quit, and you never see me again.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.02,1:22:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你看怎样\NHow about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.52,1:22:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你今天早上是怎么了\NTell me what's wrong with you this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.43,1:22:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,19年来我一直这样\NWhat's been wrong with me for 19 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.95,1:23:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我是见证者  甚至是你的同谋\NI've been a witness, and I tell you, I've been complicit.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.24,1:23:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我有多爱你  史蒂夫\NI love you, Steve. You know how much.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.16,1:23:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱你不关心一个人挣钱的能力\NI love that you don't care how much money a person makes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.95,1:23:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你在意的是他们的创造力\NYou care what they make.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.29,1:23:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,但是创造力并不应该是你最好的一面\NBut what you make isn't supposed to be the best part of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.99,1:23:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,当你成为人父\NWhen you're a father,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.85,1:23:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,父亲应该是你最好的一面\Nthat's what's supposed to be the best part of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.32,1:23:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,正是这一点给造成了你20年的苦恼挣扎\NAnd it's caused me two decades of agony,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.46,1:23:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫  这对你来说\NSteve, that it is for you
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.92,1:23:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,是最坏的一面\Nthe worst.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.15,1:23:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是什么大事  对你来说微不足道\NIt's a little thing. It's a very small thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.20,1:23:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,和她和好\NFix it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.59,1:23:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,现在就去\NFix it now,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.66,1:23:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,不然你就只能去我的新工作处找我\NOr you can contact me at my new job...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.85,1:23:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我想上哪工作就上哪\Nworking anywhere I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.72,1:23:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我恰恰觉得这不是件小事  她明知道\NI don't happen to think it is a little deal. She knew that...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.12,1:23:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,-不  -我这房子是给她们两个人买的\N- No. - I bought the house for the two of...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.21,1:23:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,-不  -你说不是什么意思\N- No. - What do you mean, "No"?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.83,1:23:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,不就是不  这栋房子\NI mean no. The house has
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.38,1:24:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,根本就不是你生丽萨的气的原因\Nnothing to do with why you're angry at Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.83,1:24:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我向你保证  这房子正是\NI assure you, the house has
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.03,1:24:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我这么生丽萨气的原因\Neverything to do with why I'm angry at Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.82,1:24:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你可曾听过一个词  "现实扭曲力场"\NHave you ever heard the phrase "Reality distortion field"?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.18,1:24:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,听过\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.73,1:24:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,完整版是"史蒂夫的现实扭曲力场"\NAs in "Steve's reality distortion field"?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.68,1:24:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道  我看到过\NI've heard it. I've read it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.63,1:24:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这词都变成乔尔·拜茨的流行歌曲了\NIt's been sung to me by Joan Baez.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.53,1:24:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你说的这个现实扭曲力场\NWhat you call a reality distortion field,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.30,1:24:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,而且我很确定这个词就是你传开的\Nand I'm pretty sure you're the one who coined the phrase,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.82,1:24:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-是我们能走到今天的原因  -我知道\N- is the reason we're here. - I know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.82,1:24:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,如果每一次别人都说我不可能做到\NIf I traded in my bank account for a dollar
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.82,1:24:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我银行就入账一块钱的话\Nevery time somebody told me
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.86,1:24:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,那我早就发达了\Nsomething was impossible, I'd come out ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.01,1:24:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-这我也清楚  -那你还有什么问题\N- I know that too. - What's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.88,1:24:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,-问题肯定不是房子  -乔  我\N- My problem? It sure isn't the house.  - Jo, I...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.63,1:24:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,问题是你告诉她你拒付她上哈佛的学费\NIt's that you told her you weren't going to pay for Harvard.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.49,1:24:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,那孩子\NThat child.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.37,1:24:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,是个认真上进  性格开朗的孩子\NThat earnest, unironic kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.78,1:24:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,她告诉你我没给她付学费吗\NShe told you I wasn't paying her tuition?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.78,1:24:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我老早该拿什么重东西砸你了\NI should have hit you with something heavy a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.31,1:24:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨跟你说我没给她付学费吗\NLisa told you I wasn't paying her tuition?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.02,1:24:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,-是安迪说的  -哪个安迪\N- Andy told me that. - Which one?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.15,1:24:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,姓赫茨菲尔德的那个\NHertzfeld.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.25,1:24:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,赫茨菲尔德又是怎么知道的\NHow would Hertzfeld know?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.79,1:25:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他给哈佛开了张两万五的支票支付学杂费\NHe wrote Harvard a check for 25,000 to cover the semester.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.12,1:25:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你他妈开什么玩笑  是他付的钱吗\NAre you fucking... He paid her tuition?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.52,1:25:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你把他叫来不就是想说这个吗\NIsn't that why you just asked to see him?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.80,1:25:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,不  我叫他是为了别的同样重要...\NNo, I asked to see him about something equally...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.84,1:25:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,是你告诉她你不愿意给她付学费的吗\NDid you tell her you weren't going to pay for college?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.09,1:25:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-是的  因为  -你怎么能说这种话\N- Yes, because... - How could you do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.66,1:25:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,因为她妈妈  同时也是她房东\NBecause her mother, who is also her landlord...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.91,1:25:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,居然是赫茨菲尔德  我当时在咆哮\NHertzfeld? I was ranting.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.01,1:25:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你懂的  当时话说重了  你觉得我会\NI was just, you know... I was talking. You think I would...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.33,1:25:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,乔安娜  我当时气坏了因为丽萨一直激我\NI was pissed off because Lisa was trying to piss me off, Joanna.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.51,1:25:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,她是故意的  我不知道会变成这样\NThat was her intent. I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.22,1:25:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你肯定把她吓坏了\NYou obviously scared the hell out of her.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.47,1:25:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,赫茨菲尔德给哈佛开了支票  付了钱\NHertzfeld wrote a check to Harvard, pay for...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.13,1:25:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-她来了吗  -她应该到了\N- Is she here yet? - I'm sure she is.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.30,1:25:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你能让人把她叫来吗\NCan you have someone bring her back?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.24,1:25:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,可以\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.25,1:25:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.78,1:25:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.18,1:25:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我祖母常跟我说...\Nmy grandmother always used to say to me...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.56,1:25:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我懒得听你灌鸡汤\NI don't give a shit, Yentl.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.80,1:25:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,-我找人把丽萨带来  -谢谢\N- I'll have someone get Lisa. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.22,1:25:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你见到赫茨菲尔德\NAnd if you see Hertzfeld...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.23,1:26:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我是安迪\NIt's Andy.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.27,1:26:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,说曹操  曹操的总工程师就到了\NSpeak of the devil's chief engineer.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.76,1:26:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,去吧\NGo.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.41,1:26:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,进来吧\NCome on in.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.34,1:26:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你今天很漂亮\NYou look great today.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.37,1:26:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-谢谢  -不是吗\N- Thank you. - Doesn't she?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.99,1:26:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,美若天仙  一直都很美  赶紧出去\NShe looks fantastic. Always does. Get out.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.33,1:26:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,-我知道你为何把我叫来  -是吗\N- Well, I think I know why I'm here. - Do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.23,1:26:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫\NSteve...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.81,1:26:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,-你把支票寄出去了吗  -寄了\N- Did you send the check yet? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.58,1:26:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,所以哈佛已经收到\NSo Harvard got a tuition
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.69,1:26:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,由安迪·赫茨菲尔德给丽萨开的学费支票\Ncheck from Andy Hertzfeld to pay for Lisa?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.17,1:26:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得他们应该不会看得这么仔细\NI don't think they look that carefully.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.78,1:26:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,也不会留意到付款人不是你\NI don't think they'd notice the check didn't come from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.58,1:26:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,真险  要不丢人丢大发了\NClose one. This was almost embarrassing for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.80,1:26:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我理解你\NI understand how...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.40,1:26:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我今天就把钱汇给你\NI'll wire you the money today.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.65,1:26:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我理解你的心情  我很抱歉  真的\NI-I understand how you feel. And I do apologize. I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.73,1:26:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,但请你听完我的想法\NBut let me tell you my thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.86,1:26:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我简直找不到合适的语言\NI can't even think of an appropriate analogy
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.91,1:26:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,来描述你所做的一切\Nto describe what you did.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.73,1:26:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你们会和好的  总会和好的\NI knew you guys would fix things. You always do.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.05,1:26:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,但同时如果钱没及时到账\NBut in the meantime, if the money wasn't there,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.07,1:26:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,她就会错过整整一学期的课\Nshe'd miss a semester of school.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.05,1:26:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-没错  -而她还得告诉朋友缺课原因\N- Yeah. - And she'd have to tell her friends why.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.83,1:27:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,她需要很多东西  她需要买袜子\NAnd she needed things. She needed socks.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.29,1:27:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.15,1:27:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,剑桥市很冷  她需要保暖的袜子\NIt's cold in Cambridge. She needed warm socks.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.09,1:27:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-你给她袜子  -我给她买袜子的钱\N- You gave her socks? - Well, I gave her money for socks.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.35,1:27:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,就算她在过渡期你也没资格自命监护人\NYou don't get to deputize yourself as her interim.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.46,1:27:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你也没资格推翻我的决定  懂吗\NYou don't get to override my decisions. Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.00,1:27:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你更没资格扮演她的父亲\NYou don't get to act like you're her father.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.24,1:27:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,总得有人去吧\NSomebody had to.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.68,1:27:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你他妈这话是什么意思\NWhat the fuck did you just say to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.83,1:27:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我从她六岁时就认识她了\NI've known her since she was six.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.65,1:27:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我同时也认为\NI also consider...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.96,1:27:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,克里斯安是我朋友  不管你和我\NChrisann's my friend, outside of what you and I...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.74,1:27:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,撇开我们俩的关系不谈\Noutside of our relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.16,1:27:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你像个家庭咨询师\NSo you're like a family adviser.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.57,1:27:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我是家庭朋友\NI'm a family friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.72,1:27:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,那你可能也知道丽萨一直在看心理医生\NThen you probably know that Lisa's been seeing a therapist.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.55,1:27:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,-是啊  -看了很多年\N- Yeah. - For many years.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.22,1:27:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,-我知道  -还不让我知情\N- Yeah. - Without my knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.20,1:27:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,这真的不关我的事\NThat really wasn't my business.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.14,1:27:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你对于关不关你的事的理解真是有趣\NI'm fascinated by what you think is and isn't your business.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.12,1:27:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨一直在做心理咨询  她也很喜欢\NLisa's been going to a therapist and she likes it
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.27,1:27:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,她更希望你和克里斯安能陪她一起\Nand would love for you and Chrisann to go with her.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.19,1:28:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你之所以知道这么多\NAnd the reason you know that is
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.19,1:28:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,是因为正是你给她推荐的心理医生\Nbecause you're the one that recommended the therapist.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.50,1:28:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我正好认识这么一个人很擅长\NWell, I know a guy. He specialize in...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.65,1:28:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,不  我意思是  是你\NNo, I mean you're the one
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.05,1:28:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,推荐她去看心理医生\Nwho recommended that she see a therapist.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.49,1:28:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗  不久以前\NYou know what? It was a while ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.28,1:28:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我虽然记不太清楚了\Nand I don't remember how the whole...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.04,1:28:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,是你告诉克里斯安  丽萨应该看心理医生\NYou told Chrisann that Lisa should see a therapist.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.92,1:28:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫你是在让我背锅  看医生很正常\NSteve, you're stigmatizing. It's a perfectly norm...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.58,1:28:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这又不是什么\NIt's not...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.54,1:28:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我的意思是  看医生能有什么坏处呢\NMy thing was, how can it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.64,1:28:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,那就等着瞧\NLet's find out.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.80,1:28:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,克里斯安是我的朋友\NChrisann is my friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.35,1:28:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,-你当初用的是什么理由  -什么意思\N- What was the reason you gave? - You mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.22,1:28:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你当初向克里斯安建议\NWhat was the reason you gave Chrisann
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.58,1:28:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,让丽萨去看心理医生的理由是什么\Nwhy Lisa should see a therapist?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.29,1:28:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我不记得了  当时我们在闲聊  而我\NI don't remember. We were talking and I said...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.82,1:28:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,说的话和刚才告诉你的差不多\NIt's pretty much what I just said,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.05,1:28:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,就是看心理医生没什么坏处\Nthat it certainly couldn't hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.67,1:28:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你没说丽萨需要一个强有力的男性模范吗\NYou didn't say that Lisa needed a strong male role model?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.32,1:28:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我说了\NI did.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.32,1:29:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得她成长到现在\NI think it's a miracle she's not
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.46,1:29:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,没和恐怖分子一起抢银行就已经是奇迹了\Nrobbing banks with the Symbionese Liberation Army.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.54,1:29:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这世界根本没给她善良的理由\NThere's no reason in the world why she should be nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.36,1:29:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,但她真的很善良\NBut she is.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.96,1:29:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我帮了忙  因为总得有人这么做\NSo I helped, because somebody had to.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.52,1:29:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我今天下午就把钱汇给你\NI'll wire the money to you this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.20,1:29:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你很久以前也这么威胁过我\NYou threatened me a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.16,1:29:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你说什么\NSorry?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.73,1:29:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,很久以前  你也威胁过我一次\NA long time ago... You threatened me once.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.84,1:29:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,人总是会被有才的人所吸引\NPeople are attracted to people with talent.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.94,1:29:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,而庸者则会觉得这是威胁\NPeople without it find that threatening.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.67,1:30:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,也许你才应该看心理医生\NMaybe you should see a therapist.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.78,1:30:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,反正没什么坏处\NCertainly couldn't hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.80,1:30:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我意思是你的的确确威胁过我\NI meant you literally threatened me.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.28,1:30:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,在弗林特  Mac发布会之前\NAt Flint, right before the Mac launch.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.59,1:30:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我当时在重新编译  在给语音系统纠错\NI was recompiling. I was trying to debug the voice demo.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.22,1:30:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你说如果我不能找到解决方案\NYou said if I couldn't find a solution,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.20,1:30:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你就会在所有观众面前宣布我的名字\Nyou'd call me out in front of the audience.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.04,1:30:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,-电脑说出"你好"了吗  -说了\N- Did it say "Hello"? - It did.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.81,1:30:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,不用谢\NNo need to thank me.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.32,1:30:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么你总希望别人讨厌你\NWhy do you want people to dislike you?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.17,1:30:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是故意让别人讨厌我\NI don't want people to dislike me.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.42,1:30:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是不在乎别人是否喜欢我\NI'm indifferent to whether they dislike me.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.84,1:30:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,既然你不在乎  我一直都不喜欢你\NSince it doesn't matter, I always have.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.01,1:30:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,真的吗\NReally?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.48,1:30:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我倒是一直很欣赏你  真是不巧\NI've always liked you a lot. That's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.68,1:30:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,-预祝发布会能惊艳全场  -谢谢\N- Knock 'em dead. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.41,1:31:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,非常厉害  难以理解但无比真实的一点\NWhat is remarkable, what's hard to fathom but true,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.06,1:31:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,就是在同一时钟频率下\Nis that for a given clock rate,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.66,1:31:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,PowerPC芯片速度是奔腾2的两倍\Na PowerPC chip is twice as fast as a Pentium II chip.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.37,1:31:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,换句话说\NIn other words,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.51,1:31:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,一个266MHz的G3核心的速度\Na 266 megahertz G3 chip
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.29,1:31:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,是同样266MHz的\Nis twice as fast as a
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.30,1:31:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,奔腾2核心运行速度的两倍\N266 megahertz Pentium II.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.73,1:31:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,或者说  266MHz的G3\NOr... A 266 G3
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.21,1:31:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,相当于一个500MHz的核心\Nis equal to about 500 megahertz.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.47,1:32:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道什么是巧合吗  丽萨\NDo you know what a coincidence is, Lisa?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.21,1:32:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,看看《Byte》杂志的评分吧\NTake a look at Byte magazine's Byte Marks,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.77,1:32:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,这是最权威的评测...\Nthe gold standard for any...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.55,1:32:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,进来\NCome in.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.47,1:32:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我让别人去大堂看了\NI sent someone into the lobby.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.20,1:32:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-他们找到她了  而且她  -她在那\N- They found her, and she... - Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.87,1:32:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,她说她不想到这儿来\NShe said she'd rather not come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.99,1:32:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,-为什么  -她只说了这么多\N- Why? - That was it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.34,1:32:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,-我亲自去找她  -不行  你不能去\N- I'm going out there myself. - You can't. You can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.11,1:32:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}《艰难时光》  甲壳虫乐队著名电影配乐
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.11,1:32:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,那就真的成了《艰难时光》了\NIt'll be a scene out of Hard Day's Night.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.69,1:32:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-抱歉打扰了  -你好  乔尔\N- Excuse me. - Hey, Joel.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.04,1:32:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪说我可以到后台来看看\NAndy said it was okay to come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.77,1:32:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,-哪个安迪  -安迪·卡宁汉\N- Which one? - Andy Cunningham.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.73,1:32:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,受不了了  他俩有一个得把名字改了\NI can't do this forever. I need one of them to change their name.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.53,1:32:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以管安迪·卡宁汉叫安德里亚\NYou call Andy Cunningham "Andrea."
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.69,1:32:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎么称呼他们没关系\NIt doesn't matter what I call them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.86,1:32:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,和他们说话的时候  我分得清楚谁是谁\NI know who I'm talking about when I'm talking.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.86,1:32:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要别人给他们不同的称呼\NI need everyone else to call them different names.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.52,1:32:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,稍等我一会\NGive me one second.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.16,1:33:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托你  帮我把她叫过来好吗\NCan you go get her for me, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.53,1:33:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚刚和安迪谈了谈\NI just talked to Andy.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.42,1:33:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,姓赫茨菲尔德的那个\NHertzfeld.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.93,1:33:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我都想用清洁剂把我脑子清一清\NI'm just trying to scrub this out of my brain with Drano.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.47,1:33:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,但我真的想和丽萨谈谈\NBut I do want to talk to Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.71,1:33:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,好的  你就...\NOkay. Just...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.35,1:33:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,-保持冷静  -好的\N- Stay cool. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.91,1:33:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.50,1:33:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你好  史蒂夫\NHey, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.48,1:33:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在感觉怎么样\NHow are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.57,1:33:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我感觉很好  乔尔  你呢\NI'm feeling good, Joel. How about you?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.48,1:33:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得我快在你们这行干不下去了\NI don't think I could be in your business.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.10,1:33:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,更新换代太快了\NIt changes too quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.30,1:33:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我能挺住\NWell, I'd hang on, 'cause yours
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.88,1:33:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,而你也要开始跟上这个节奏了\Nis about to start changing pretty quickly too.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.85,1:33:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我14年以来第三次采访你\NThis is the third time in 14 years I'm writing about you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.55,1:33:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你目前有什么看法\NWhat do you think so far?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.41,1:34:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉  阿维找你  说有新的鲨鱼图片\NExcuse me. Avie's looking for you. He has a new shark.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.68,1:34:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,-你想去后台参观下吗  -当然\N- You wanna come backstage for a second? - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.60,1:34:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-这是谁  -阿兰·图灵\N- Who's this one? - Alan Turing.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.11,1:34:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,赢得世界第二次大战他功劳最大\NSingle-handedly won World War II and,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.61,1:34:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,因为公认是他发明了电脑\Nfor an encore, invented the computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.69,1:34:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-但他不会出现在发布会上  -为何\N- He won't be part of the campaign though. - Why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.82,1:34:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你还得问我这是哪位\N'Cause you just had to ask me who he was.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.85,1:34:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我能看看新的鲨鱼图片吗\NCan I see new shark?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.57,1:34:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,比上一只鲨鱼好多了\NI like it better than the old shark.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.98,1:34:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-是很多只鲨鱼  -很多只\N- Sharks. - Sharks.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.72,1:34:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-你看了多少鲨鱼  -就几个\N- How many sharks did you go through? - A couple.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.72,1:34:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-这是第39只  -我们正在接受采访\N- This is the 39th. - We're on the record.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.80,1:34:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,-39只鲨鱼  -好的\N- Thirty-nine sharks. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.45,1:34:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-你知道这只特别在哪吗  -在哪\N- You know what's special about this shark? - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.42,1:34:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,其实我也在问\NNo, I'm really asking,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.88,1:34:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,因为在我看来和其他38只完全一样\Nbecause it looks exactly like the other 38 sharks to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.12,1:34:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,把它和解说词一起放出去\NLet me see it with the cue,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.31,1:34:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,就从外观那里\Nfrom the profile.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.17,1:34:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,这是92-B号幻灯片\NThis is cue 92-B.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.07,1:34:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,这是电脑外观\NThis is a profile here,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.89,1:34:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这个是电脑的背面图\Nand this is what it looks like from the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.00,1:34:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,另外  正面效果图\NAnd one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.11,1:34:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,奔腾笔记本只配给它塞牙缝\NIt eats Pentium notebooks as a light snack.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.21,1:34:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这只鲨鱼了\NThis is the shark.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.43,1:35:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我很满意\NI really like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.16,1:35:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人第一次就能成功\NNobody gets it right the first time,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.49,1:35:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,但这条早该在15或20条之前给我看了\Nbut I should have been shown this shark 15, 20 fish ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.53,1:35:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-可能吧  -把画面锁定\N- You probably were. - Lock it in.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.08,1:35:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-倒计时十分钟  -他吃了一口毒苹果\N- Ten minutes. - He killed himself by taking
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.98,1:35:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,自杀了  我说的是阿兰·图灵\Na bite of a poison apple... Alan Turing.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.82,1:35:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.72,1:35:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,应该给他立一尊雕像\NThere should be statues of that man.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.79,1:35:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他的名字应该家喻户晓  妇孺皆知\NHis name should be on the lips of schoolchildren.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.71,1:35:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,被咬了一口的彩虹色苹果\NThe rainbow flag apple with a bite taken out...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.02,1:35:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,原来标志灵感出自这里吗\NThat's where it came from?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.73,1:35:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,不  其实我们找了很多听着不错的名字\NNo, we picked it off a list of friendly-sounding words.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.42,1:35:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,但找一个有故事的名字不是更好吗\NBut wouldn't it be great if that had been the story behind it?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.51,1:35:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫  我还是喜欢上一只鲨鱼\NSteve. Kinda liked the last shark.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.92,1:35:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,滚丫的\NFuck you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.94,1:35:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我想请你帮个忙\NI wanted to ask you a favor.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.14,1:35:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我的朋友  很早以前\NMy friend, a long time ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.86,1:35:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你在发布会前要求我帮个忙  我拒绝了\Nyou asked me a favor before a product launch, and I said no.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.66,1:35:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,-你想让我承认...  -等等\N- You wanted me to acknowledge... - Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.78,1:35:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想说承认你错了\NIf you're about to say you were wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.21,1:35:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要让这个记者记下来\NI want to prepare this journalist.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.13,1:35:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我百分百是对的  而你错得离谱\NI was 100% right, and you were spectacularly wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.91,1:35:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,但我还是欠你个人情  所以说吧\NBut I still owe you a favor, so name it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.27,1:35:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,-史蒂夫  -除了感谢Apple Ⅱ研发组\N- Steve... - It can't be acknowledging the Apple II team.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.32,1:35:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,感谢Apple Ⅱ研发组\NAcknowledge the Apple II team.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.62,1:36:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,-能不能私下谈这个  -不行\N- How about in private? - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.86,1:36:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,-这是恶作剧吗  -不是\N- Is this a prank? - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.09,1:36:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我正努力回想300MHz的G3芯片的事\NI'm trying to remember that a 300 megahertz G3 chip...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.03,1:36:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,只感谢核心成员就好\NJust the top guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.47,1:36:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.06,1:36:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-稍等一下可以吗  -好\N- Excuse me, okay? - Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.30,1:36:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,给我一会\NOne second.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.83,1:36:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,-她说还是算了  -什么意思\N- She said she'd rather not. - What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.97,1:36:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,她和她的朋友坐在一起\NShe's sitting with her friends,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.27,1:36:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,她还说了她不想到这里\Nand she said she'd rather not come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.42,1:36:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,那好  告诉她  先把她叫到一边\NOkay. Tell her... Take her aside.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.34,1:36:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我可不想让她在朋友面前丢脸\NI don't want to embarrass her in front of her friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.20,1:36:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,但告诉她  我刚刚把安迪吓尿了\NBut tell her I just scared the shit out of Andy,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.62,1:36:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,而且这次谁都不能帮她付那该死的...\Nand this time, nobody's paying her fucking...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.49,1:36:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧  别说这个\NAll right. Don't say that.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.53,1:36:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,不过你可以搬出你那套成熟又睿智的腔调\NBut do your thing where you sound old and wise
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.02,1:36:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像你的人生就是一幅欧洲悲情油画\Nbecause of the broad, tragic European canvas of your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.18,1:36:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我不是生在19世纪的犹太小村吧\NYou know I wasn't born in a 19th-century shtetl, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.13,1:36:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,请转告她这很重要\NPlease tell her it's important.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.47,1:36:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,-一切都还好吗  -都好\N- Everything all right? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.02,1:36:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,-这大庭广众的...  -我知道\N- There are people around here, man... - I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.25,1:36:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,-还有一位媒体记者  -我看到了\N- Including a member of the press. - I see him.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.14,1:37:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,沃兹\NWoz.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.78,1:37:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,只需感谢那些被解雇的核心成员们\NJust the top guys, the ones who are getting laid off.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.28,1:37:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,听我说  好吗\NListen, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.28,1:37:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,去年  苹果损失了十亿美元\NLast year, Apple lost one billion dollars.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.22,1:37:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我都不知道这是怎么办到的\NI don't even know how that's possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.07,1:37:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你们可能撑不到90天就要破产了\NYou were less than 90 days from being insolvent.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.71,1:37:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我让三个不同的会计师来跟我解释\NI had three different accountants try to explain it to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.73,1:37:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,整个公司都需要精简\NThe whole place has to be streamlined.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.33,1:37:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,-先从开除那俩会计开始  -我会从\N- Start with two of the accountants. - I started with the...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.35,1:37:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,乔尔  你可以先从台上下来吗\NJoel, could you come offstage?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.07,1:37:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-我们去后台吧  -让他留下\N- We're gonna go backstage. - Leave him right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.27,1:37:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我先把Apple Ⅱ研发组裁掉\NI started with the Apple II team
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.52,1:37:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们不再生产Apple Ⅱ了\Nbecause we don't make that anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.45,1:37:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,只答谢核心成员\NJust acknowledge the top guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.30,1:37:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,喝杯饮料放松下吧\NHave a mimosa and relax.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.14,1:37:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你这次休想再拒绝我  史蒂夫\NYou will not blow me off right now, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.78,1:37:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,核心成员有资格...\NThe top guys deserve...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.01,1:37:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,根本没什么核心成员\NThere are no top guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.37,1:37:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,明白吗  苹果二团队里没什么核心成员\NAll right? On the Apple II team, there are no top guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.09,1:37:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,他们是二流货  只会拖顶尖选手的后腿\NThey're "B" Players, and "B" Players discourage the "A" Players.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.44,1:37:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我要顶尖人才留在苹果  而不是去戴尔\NI want "A" Players at Apple and not Dell.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.56,1:37:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,他们才不是二流  我比你清楚得多\NThey're not "B" Players, and I'm a better judge of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.32,1:37:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,距离破产只剩下不到90天了\NLess than 90 days from insolvency,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.85,1:37:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,某种程度上来说  正因为某些人还认为\Nin part because somebody thought
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.70,1:37:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,牛顿掌上电脑不是一个垃圾产品\Nthe Newton wasn't a box of garbage.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.41,1:38:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-乔尔  请你来一下好吗  -他留下\N- Joel, could you come offstage, please? - Leave him.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.20,1:38:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我说的是\NI'm talking about...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.72,1:38:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我不在的这段时候  你们设计并发售了\NYou guys designed and shipped a little box of garbage
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.15,1:38:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-这个垃圾玩意  -我说的是Apple Ⅱ\N- while I was gone. - I'm talking about the Apple II,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.56,1:38:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,它不仅是这个公司重要历史成就之一\Nwhich is not just a crucial part of this company's history,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.24,1:38:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,更是个人电脑史上的意义重大的里程碑\Nit is a crucial part of the history of personal computing.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.95,1:38:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,曾经是\NFor a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.39,1:38:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想裁掉这些员工  你至少应该\NThe least you can do, if you're going to downsize these people...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.13,1:38:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,他们也能住上失业者能拥有的\NThey're gonna live in the biggest houses
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.79,1:38:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,最大的房子了\Nof anyone on the unemployment line.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.06,1:38:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...对他们表示感谢\N...is to acknowledge them.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.60,1:38:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,在发布会上感谢他们  还有Apple Ⅱ\NAcknowledge them and the Apple II during this launch.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.56,1:38:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一款新的拳头产品\NThis is a new animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.23,1:38:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,整个公司都是Apple Ⅱ的成功发展来的\NThis whole place was built by the Apple II.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.48,1:38:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你的成功更是托Apple Ⅱ的福\NYou were built by the Apple II.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.89,1:38:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,事实上\NAs a matter of fact,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.65,1:38:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,正是Apple Ⅱ和它的开放系统毁了我\NI was destroyed by the Apple II and its open system
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.94,1:38:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,所以各路黑客和闲人\Nso that hackers and hobbyists
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.83,1:38:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,才能鼓捣出那些无线电之类的破玩意儿\Ncould build ham radios or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.58,1:38:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,并且它还差点把苹果公司毁了\NAnd then it nearly destroyed Apple
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.18,1:38:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你们把全部身家都投在了上面\Nwhen you spent all your money on it
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.18,1:38:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,然后一直老调重弹  毫无创新\Nand developed a grand total of no new products.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.86,1:38:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-牛顿掌上电脑  -就是一个垃圾盒子\N- The Newton. - The little box of garbage.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.49,1:38:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你们发明了牛顿  还嫌不够丢人吗\NYou guys came up with the Newton. You want people to know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.65,1:38:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是新品发布会  不是什么感恩餐会\NThis is a product launch, not a luncheon.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.09,1:38:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我最不愿意做的就是把iMac和...\NThe last thing I want to do is connect the iMac to...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.13,1:39:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,和这个公司史上唯一成功的产品联系起来\NTo the only successful product that this company has ever made.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.11,1:39:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,别怨我说话直  但这就是事实\NI'm sorry to be blunt, but that happens to be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.44,1:39:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,丽萨是个失败品  麦金塔也是\NThe Lisa was a failure. The Macintosh was a failure.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.68,1:39:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我也不想说重话\NI don't like talking like this,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.62,1:39:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我受够了明知自己是约翰[甲壳虫主唱]\Nbut I am tired of being Ringo
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.70,1:39:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,却被当成林戈[甲壳虫鼓手]\Nwhen I know I was John.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.45,1:39:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,大家挺喜欢林戈的\NEverybody loves Ringo.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.57,1:39:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我也受够了你高人一等地对待我\NAnd I'm tired of being patronized by you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.76,1:39:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得约翰是靠运气才出的名吗  沃兹\NYou think John became John by winning a raffle, Woz?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.24,1:39:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得他是耍了某个人\NYou think he tricked somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.55,1:39:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,还是揍了乔治·哈里森的脑袋才出的名吗\Nor hit George Harrison over the head?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.23,1:39:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,他出名是因为他是约翰\NHe was John because he was John.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.90,1:39:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,他出名是因为他创作了《旅行票》\NHe was John 'cause he wrote "Ticket to Ride".
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.92,1:39:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,而我创造了Apple Ⅱ\NAnd I wrote the Apple II.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.47,1:39:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-各位  得清场了  -都不许走\N- Everybody? I want to clear the auditorium. - Nobody moves.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.71,1:39:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你是创造了完美的主板\NYou made a beautiful board,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.12,1:39:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,顺提一句  你居然愿意将其免费赠送\Nwhich, by the way, you were willing to give out for free,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.98,1:39:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,所以别跟我说什么你是怎么创造苹果的\Nso don't tell me how you built Apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.34,1:39:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,要不是因为我\NIf it weren't for me,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.11,1:39:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你也就只能在霍姆斯泰德高中当优等生了\Nyou'd be the easiest "A" at Homestead High School.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.76,1:39:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,你的称赞掌控着这些人的生死\NThese people live and die by your praise,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.03,1:39:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,给你个机会\Nso here's your chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.28,1:39:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,承认就算你不在\NAcknowledge that something good happened
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.80,1:39:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我们也能成功\Nthat you weren't in the room for.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.65,1:40:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,-不  -史蒂夫\N- No. - Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.68,1:40:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,承认吧  这是事实  这...\NDo it. It's right. It's...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.03,1:40:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,这是事实\NIt's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.79,1:40:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉  我不认\NSorry, but no.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.81,1:40:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,那我这么说吧\NThen let me put it another way.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.92,1:40:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得没有人在个人计算设备\NI don't think there's a man who's done more to advance
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.74,1:40:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,大众化普及方面的贡献\Nthe democratization that comes with
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.30,1:40:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,比我更大了\Npersonal computing than I have,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.63,1:40:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,可你从来就没尊重过我\Nbut you've never had any respect for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.36,1:40:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么\NNow why is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.06,1:40:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,至少我会考虑下有可能\NI'd at least consider the possibility
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.44,1:40:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,是因为你也从来没尊重过我\Nthat it's because you've never had any for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.96,1:40:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你俩这是在唱哪出\NWhat the hell is going on here?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.26,1:40:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,没事  感谢你抽出时间见我\NNothing. Thank you for your time.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.68,1:40:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,搞定了  把她叫过来了\NIt's done. She's coming back.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.18,1:40:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你差点就让整家公司破产了\NYou came a half-inch from putting this company out of business.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.90,1:40:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这事我去找谁说理呢\NNow who do I see about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.19,1:40:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我让你保住了工作\NI'm letting you keep your job.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.86,1:40:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我给了你豁免\NYou get a pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.36,1:41:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,人们以前常问我\NYou know, when people used to ask me
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.75,1:41:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我和史蒂夫·乔布斯有何不同\Nwhat the difference was between me and Steve Jobs,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.89,1:41:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我会回答  史蒂夫一般掌控大局\NI would say Steve was the big-picture guy
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.25,1:41:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,而我就只管埋头研发\Nand I liked a solid workbench.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.12,1:41:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,如果现在别人再问起我有何不同\NWhen people ask me what the difference is now,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.13,1:41:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我会回答  史蒂夫是个混蛋\NI say "Steve's an asshole".
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.83,1:41:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你的产品远远好过你的人品  兄弟\NYour products are better than you are, brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.85,1:41:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,那就对了  兄弟\NThat's the idea, brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.25,1:41:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,清楚这点  就是我俩的不同\NAnd knowing that, that's the difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.43,1:41:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是非黑即白的事\NIt's not binary.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.25,1:41:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以既为人谦逊又才华横溢\NYou can be decent and gifted at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.82,1:41:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(51.75,110)}不同凡想
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.70,1:41:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他不是那个意思\NHe didn't mean it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.68,1:41:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,他就是\NYeah, he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.32,1:41:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,他是个容易情绪化的人\NHe's a temperamental guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.60,1:42:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他不是\NNo, he's not.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.19,1:42:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像每场发布会开场前五分钟\NIt's like five minutes before every launch,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.24,1:42:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,大家都会去酒吧\Neveryone goes to a bar,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.36,1:42:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,喝醉后跑来向我倒苦水\Ngets drunk and tells me what they really think.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.34,1:42:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,她去你更衣室了\NShe's coming to your dressing room.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.84,1:42:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我是让你和丽萨和好\NI told you to make things all right with Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.25,1:42:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是让你去把所有矛盾一口气解决了\NI didn't say you had to settle every blood feud you have.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.60,1:42:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,上回矛盾没处理好\NLast time blood feuds weren't settled,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.71,1:42:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,结果我没上成《时代》封面\NI lost the cover of Time.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.80,1:42:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我思前想后\NThough for the life of me,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.92,1:42:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,也没搞懂为什么丹·科特克对我不满\NI still don't know what the hell Dan Kottke was mad at me about.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.13,1:42:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,-你没上封面又不怪科特克  -就怪他\N- Kottke didn't lose you the cover of Time. - Of course he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.05,1:42:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,需要我向你证明你说你肯定对的时候\NWould you like me to demonstrate your capacity to be wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.86,1:42:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,其实都是错的吗\Nwhen you're certain you're right?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.09,1:42:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,丹·科特克告诉《时代》我否认...\NDan Kottke told Time magazine that I was denying...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.78,1:42:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你还记得那个封面吗\NDo you remember the cover?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.52,1:42:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,-《时代》的吗  -对\N- Of Time? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.00,1:42:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-记得  -是什么封面\N- Yes. - What was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.88,1:42:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,-你在说什么  -封面上有什么\N- What are you talking about? - What was on the cover?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.29,1:42:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,-计算机  -不对\N- A computer. - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.36,1:43:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,是一台计算机的塑像\NIt was a sculpture of a computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.73,1:43:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}计算机时代来临
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.86,1:43:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}计算机时代来临
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.89,1:43:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,是一台塑像\NIt was a sculpture.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.56,1:43:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,《时代》应该在发刊前几个月\NTime would have had to have commissioned it
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.07,1:43:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,就定下这封面了\Nmonths in advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.74,1:43:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你根本就没进"年度风云人物"候选名单\NYou were never in the conversation for Man of the Year.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.01,1:43:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,没人害你失去任何东西\NNobody lost you anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.69,1:43:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,...我和Mac的照片\N...picture of me and the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.29,1:43:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,所以还有什么是你自认对的\NSo what else are you sure about?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.49,1:43:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎么会没想到这点\NI don't know how I could've missed that.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.54,1:43:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-现实扭曲  -不  我说真的\N- Reality distortion. - No, seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.74,1:43:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我也说真的\NSeriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.91,1:43:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,别想着吵赢丽萨\NDon't try to win an argument with Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.29,1:43:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,承认你错了吧\NJust say you were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.05,1:43:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,进来吧  宝贝\NCome on in, honey.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.00,1:43:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-我不是你"宝贝"  -约翰\N- It's not "honey". - John.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.30,1:43:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,进来  快进来  别站在走廊了\NGet in. Get in. Get out of the hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.62,1:43:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我是从侧门进来的\NI was taken in a side entrance.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.06,1:43:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,一会我原路返回  没人会看到我的\NI'll go out the same way. No one will see me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.66,1:43:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,-你好吗  乔安娜  -我很好  约翰\N- How are you, Joanna? - I'm good, John.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.41,1:43:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,只是没想到会见到你\NI'm just surprised to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.56,1:43:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,大家都很感激你在《福布斯》上说的话\NEveryone here really appreciates the quote you gave to Forbes.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.50,1:43:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,-其实你不必这样  -不必客气\N- You didn't have to do that. - My pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.97,1:43:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你愿意的话  等熄灯的时候\NIf you want, I can slip you in the back
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.15,1:43:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我带你去后台看看\Nonce the house lights go out.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.42,1:43:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-我只是来祝好运的  -好吧\N- I'm just here to say "Good luck." - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.87,1:44:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你只有几分钟时间\NYou just have a couple of minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.72,1:44:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,-麻烦你去找下...  -好\N- Would you try to find... - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.34,1:44:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你是个好人  约翰\NYou're a good man, John.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.96,1:44:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我给你带了个礼物\NSo I brought you a present.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.07,1:44:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,一台牛顿掌上电脑\NA Newton.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.20,1:44:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,如果不开箱  你还能转手卖掉\NDon't take it out of the box, you'll be able to sell it,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.48,1:44:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,那样就更好了\Nwhich is more than I can say.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.41,1:44:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你没事吧\NEverything all right there?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.30,1:44:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,没\NUh, no...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.60,1:44:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,就只是乔安娜指出了一点问题\NJust something Joanna pointed out to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.61,1:44:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,有些显而易见的事我却漏掉了\NI missed something so obvious about...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.14,1:44:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,没什么大不了\NDoesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.54,1:44:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,华尔街都坐等着观察你CEO当得怎么样\NLook, Wall Street's gonna sit back and wait to see how you do as CEO,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.94,1:44:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,所以第一年里不要为股价波动费心了\Nso don't let any fluctuation bother you for the first 12 months.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.01,1:44:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,短线交易者会作出反应的\NDay traders are gonna respond.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.38,1:44:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,不必我来教你\NI don't need to school you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.59,1:45:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你是想告诉我不应该停产牛顿吗\NThis your way of telling me I shouldn't have killed the Newton?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.59,1:45:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上最有效率的动物是秃鹫\NThe most efficient animal on the planet is the condor.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.37,1:45:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上最没效率的动物是人类\NThe most inefficient animals on the planet are humans.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.88,1:45:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,至少不该因为个人恩怨而停产\NWell, you shouldn't have killed it for spite.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.80,1:45:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,对公司不好  别这么做\NThat's bad business. Don't do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.31,1:45:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,可有了自行车\NBut a human with a bicycle
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.20,1:45:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,人类就成了最有效率的动物了\Nbecomes the most efficient animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.53,1:45:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,而完美的计算机\NAnd the right computer...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.59,1:45:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,友好且易操作的计算机\Na friendly, easy computer that
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.54,1:45:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,不应当难看突兀  而应当像台灯一样\Nisn't an eyesore but rather sits on your desk
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.02,1:45:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,静美地摆在你的桌上\Nwith the beauty of a Tensor lamp...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.04,1:45:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,完美的计算机就像是思维的自行车\NThe right computer will be a bicycle for the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.21,1:45:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你喜欢吗\NDo you like it?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.59,1:45:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我被送回去过\NI was giving back.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.06,1:45:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,如果不是只有配得上的人才有\NAnd what if instead of it being in the right hands,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.21,1:45:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,而是人人都有呢\Nit was in everyone's hands?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.33,1:45:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,全世界所有人\NEveryone in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.90,1:45:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你说的电脑对现有的市场结构\NWe'd be talking about the most tectonic shift
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.80,1:45:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,所造成的影响将会是...\Nin the status quo since...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.23,1:45:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,史无前例的\NEver.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.58,1:45:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道你为什么一直\NI don't know why you've always been
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.76,1:45:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,对我的被收养史感兴趣\Ninterested in my adoption history,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.06,1:45:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,可你说过这不像是别人看了我一眼\Nbut you said it's not like someone looked at me
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.72,1:46:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,就把我送回去了那样\Nand gave me back.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.70,1:46:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,可实际上就是这样\NBut that is what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.73,1:46:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你是说你有完美的计算机吗\NAnd you're telling me you have the right computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.71,1:46:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,它叫麦金塔\NIt's called Macintosh.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.88,1:46:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,先是一对律师夫妇收养了我\NA lawyer couple adopted me first,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.37,1:46:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,一个月后就把我送回去了\Nthen gave me back after a month.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.18,1:46:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他们改变主意了\NThey changed their mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.10,1:46:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我的父母收养了我\NThen my parents adopted me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.53,1:46:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我的生母要求  收养我的人\NMy biological mother had stipulated that whoever took me
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.26,1:46:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,必须受过大学教育  有钱而且信天主教\Nhad to be college-educated, wealthy and Catholic.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.01,1:46:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,保罗和克拉拉夫妇一条都不符合\NPaul and Clara Jobs were none of those things,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.24,1:46:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我的生母不肯签收养协议\Nso my biological mother wouldn't sign the adoption papers.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.79,1:46:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,后来呢\NWhat happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.93,1:46:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,打了挺长一阵官司\NThere was a legal battle that went on for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.48,1:46:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我妈说最开始一年她拒绝爱我\NMy mother said she refused to love me for the first year.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.13,1:46:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,以防他们得把我送回去\NYou know, in case they had to give me back.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.21,1:46:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你没法没法拒绝爱一个人  史蒂夫\NYou can't refuse to love someone, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.46,1:46:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  但其实是有办法的\NYeah, it turns out you can.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.14,1:46:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,一个月大的婴儿到底犯了什么大错\NWhat the hell can a one-month-old do that's
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.87,1:46:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,会烦到让他父母把他送回去\Nso bad his parents give him back?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.55,1:46:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,没有  一个月大的婴儿什么都干不了\NNothing. There's nothing a one-month-old can do...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.69,1:46:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你有没有想过去找你的生父\NHave you ever thought about trying to find your biological father?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.05,1:47:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经见过他了\NI've met my biological father.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.72,1:47:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,说起来其实你也见过\NFor that matter, so have you.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.42,1:47:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,它叫麦金塔\NIt's called Macintosh.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.75,1:47:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,-史蒂夫·乔布斯先生  -詹达利\N- Mr. Steve Jobs. - Jandali.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.46,1:47:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,这位是约翰·斯卡利\NSay hello to John Sculley.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.20,1:47:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,詹达利是这儿的老板\NJandali owns the place,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.79,1:47:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰是百事公司的CEO\Nand John's the CEO of Pepsi,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.77,1:47:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我正在说服他搬来库比蒂诺\Nbut I'm trying to get him to move to Cupertino,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.17,1:47:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,干一番大事业\Nput a dent in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.88,1:47:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,您也吃素吗\NYou eat vegan as well?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.95,1:47:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你在逗我吧\NYou're kidding me.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.71,1:47:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,不  我什么都吃\NNo, I'll eat anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.11,1:47:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,要不你试试这道前菜\NWhy don't you start off with
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.14,1:47:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,地中海生菜色拉配马齿苋和薄荷\Nthe Mediterranean lettuce salad with purslane, mint...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.38,1:47:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我妹妹找到的他\NMy sister found him.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.27,1:47:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,-他知道吗  -不知道\N- Does he know? - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.31,1:47:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,相反  他还向莫纳炫耀\NIn fact, he bragged to Mona that
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.73,1:47:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫·乔布斯一直光临他的餐厅\NSteve Jobs comes in the restaurant all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.88,1:47:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-难道你不想...  -不想\N- You don't want to... - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.39,1:47:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你不觉得你该告诉他吗\NDon't you think you should talk to him?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.31,1:47:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,那他可能会随便找个理由告我来要钱吧\NHe'd probably find a reason to sue me.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.65,1:47:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫\NOh, Steve...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:49.64,1:47:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰  如果你是来为你的业绩讨说法\NJohn, if you're here about your legacy,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.42,1:47:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,那你得排在沃兹尼亚克之后了\Nyou need to form a line behind Wozniak.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.20,1:47:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,沃兹尼亚克会没事的\NWozniak's gonna be fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.42,1:47:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我可是炒了史蒂夫·乔布斯的人\NI'm the guy who fired Steve Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.80,1:48:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,有钱  受过大学教育  信天主教\NRich, college-educated and Catholic.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.42,1:48:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫  到时间了\NSteve? It's time.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.06,1:48:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我得上台了\NI've gotta go.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.65,1:48:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,是我搞砸了这一切吗\NDid I do this? Screw it up?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.22,1:48:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,现在就忘了这些吧\NLet's let it go now.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.23,1:48:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,也是时候了\NHas to be time.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.03,1:48:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,来当我们的CEO吧\NCome be our CEO.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.16,1:48:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,行\NYeah. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.63,1:48:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,是因为手写笔  约翰\NIt was the stylus, John.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.93,1:48:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,-什么  -我是因为手写笔才停产牛顿\N- What? - I killed the Newton because of the stylus.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:53.78,1:48:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,要是手拿着手写笔\NIf you're holding a stylus, you can't use
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.45,1:48:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,就腾不出那五支天然的手写笔了\Nthe other five that are attached to your wrist.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.59,1:49:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,本来我们能干出一番大事业\NThings we could have done together.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.53,1:49:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,那得是多么惊天动地的事业啊\NGod, the things we could've done.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.47,1:49:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我会给你交学费的\NI'm paying your tuition.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.03,1:49:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你傻了吗  我当然会给你交学费\NAre you crazy? Of course I'm paying your tuition.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.19,1:49:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,那你当时说你不会给我交学费\NI must have misunderstood you when you said
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.81,1:49:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,一定是我理解错了\Nyou weren't paying my tuition.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.12,1:49:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你和你妈要卖房子就是跟我过不去\NYou and your mom selling the house was a hostile thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.52,1:49:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,她急需钱\NShe needed the money.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.65,1:49:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,她一直都急需钱\NShe always needs the money.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.37,1:49:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,她需要看医生  她得了鼻窦炎\NShe needs a doctor. She has a sinus infection.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:44.92,1:49:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,她1988年开始就得了这鼻窦炎了\NShe's had the same sinus infection since 1988.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.18,1:49:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我得照顾我妈妈\NI'm gonna take care of my mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.22,1:49:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,要是惹你不爽那就对不起了\NI'm sorry if that angers you.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.07,1:49:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我确实不爽  因为你还是个孩子\NIt does anger me, because you're a kid
Dialogue: 0,1:49:53.81,1:49:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,照顾你妈妈并不是你的责任\Nand it's not your job to take care of your mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.24,1:49:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你妈妈才死了吗\NIs that how yours died?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.30,1:50:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,各位都走开吧  给他们点私人空间\NGuys, step away, please, and give them some room.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.51,1:50:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,等到你妈90岁  没法养活自己了\NWhen your mom is 90 and can't feed herself,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:05.32,1:50:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以去照顾她\Nyou can take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.82,1:50:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,可现在  她才45岁\NBut right now, she's 45,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.87,1:50:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,非常健康  却养不活自己\Nperfectly healthy and can't feed herself.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.14,1:50:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该在学校里努力学习\NYou're supposed to work hard at school and
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.75,1:50:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,过着19岁学生的生活才对\Nbe 19, and that's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.16,1:50:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,-我来照顾你妈  -照顾得可真好啊\N- I'll take care of your mother. - Keep up the good work.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.67,1:50:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-你到底想让我怎么样  -你叫我回来\N- What the hell do you want from me? - I was sent for.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.03,1:50:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我给她买了栋四十万的房子\NI bought her a house for $400,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.52,1:50:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,现在房价翻了一倍\NIt's worth twice that much today.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.54,1:50:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,就为了两块神石和一碗魔汤把它卖了\NShe sold it for two magic rocks and a bowl of soup.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:27.99,1:50:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,那是她的房子\NIt was her house.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.26,1:50:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,她用卖房子的钱去环欧洲旅游了\NShe used that money to travel through Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.11,1:50:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,这笔钱还是她苦苦求来的\NMoney which you make her beg for.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:32.50,1:50:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-史蒂夫  -别跟我扯这个\N- Steve... - Don't even start with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.19,1:50:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,居然还敢去找安迪要钱\NGoing to Andy and asking for the money?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.35,1:50:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-简直太过分了  -不是我去找他\N- That was so off-the-charts over the line... - I did not do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.66,1:50:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,是安迪找的我\NAndy came to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.67,1:50:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你们要不要一起聊聊\NEverybody have an opinion on this?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.53,1:50:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉各位  还有三十秒  你要迟到了\NI'm sorry, guys. In 30 seconds, you're going to be late.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.30,1:50:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,她花钱买古董\NShe spends the money on antiques
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.27,1:50:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,然后卖出去的价格还不到买价的零头\Nand then sells them for a fraction of what she paid,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.76,1:50:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,而我给她这笔钱是让她照顾你的\Nand she does it with money I gave to her for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.25,1:50:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫\NSteve...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.29,1:50:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你13岁的时候歇斯底里地跑来求我\NYou came to me hysterical when you were 13,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.42,1:50:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,想要和我一起过\Nasking if you could live with me...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.36,1:51:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,-我没有歇斯底里  -因为你妈\N- I was not hysterical. - because your mom
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.38,1:51:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,每天都对你大吼大叫\Nwas screaming at you every day.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.39,1:51:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-13岁那回  -还时不时一连几个星期\N-Thirteen was the second time - Her not speaking to you
Dialogue: 0,1:51:02.99,1:51:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,-是我第二次求你  -不跟你说话\N- I asked you. - for weeks at a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.18,1:51:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,因为她当个神棍压力太大\NThe stress of her life as a spiritual healer.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:05.61,1:51:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我没说过你不好\NI don't believe I said you're a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:07.91,1:51:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,可要是我说了  我道歉\NBut if I did, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:14.04,1:51:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你在学校是不是遇到了什么麻烦\NSomething happened to you at school,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.60,1:51:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,是不是第一学期哪门\Nsome first semester core class
Dialogue: 0,1:51:18.63,1:51:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,新生必修的核心课程挂了还是...\Nthat all freshmen are required to take...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.57,1:51:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,-我看了那期《时代》  -什么\N- I read Time. - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.82,1:51:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我们学校可以上网\NI have Internet access at school.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:26.27,1:51:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我看了《时代》的一本过刊\NI read an old copy of Time,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.55,1:51:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我问了我妈有关我们家史的事情\Nand I asked my mom some questions about my family history.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.18,1:51:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,那是...\NThat was...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.07,1:51:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,《时代》那文章曲解我的话\NTime wrote a mangled piece of journal.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.69,1:51:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你就不该看到\NYou were never supposed to read that.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.63,1:51:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我找了两位哈佛的统计学家\NI had two different Harvard statisticians
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.96,1:51:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,想要反推你所编出来的  能证明\Ntry to reverse-engineer the equation that you came up with
Dialogue: 0,1:51:41.65,1:51:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,全美28%的男人都可能是我爸的算式\Nto prove that 28% of American men could be my father.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.78,1:51:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,宝贝  我...\NHoney, I...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.89,1:51:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,也许我妈确实有各种毛病\NYou know, my mother might be a troubled woman,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.70,1:51:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,可你又是什么原因\Nbut what's your excuse?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:51.37,1:51:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我没被你的说辞打动  爸\NThat's why I'm not impressed with your story, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:53.99,1:51:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你明知道我过得很惨\NIt's that you knew what I was going through,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:56.18,1:51:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,却只袖手旁观\Nand you didn't do anything about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.01,1:52:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你就是个没良心的懦夫\Nand that makes you an unconscionable coward.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.71,1:52:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,而且非要说起来  "想"是个动词好吗\NAnd not for nothing, but "think" is a verb, all right,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:05.28,1:52:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,还把"不同"弄成副词了\Nmaking "different" an adverb.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.47,1:52:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你不就是想让大家换个角度思考吗\NYou're asking people to think differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.68,1:52:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以谈包豪斯运动\NAnd you can talk about the Bauhaus movement
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.85,1:52:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,谈博朗  谈"至繁归于至简"\Nand Braun and "simplicity is sophistication"
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.08,1:52:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,谈三宅一生服饰  谈鲍勃·迪伦的歌词\Nand Issey Miyake uniforms and Bob Dylan lyrics all you want,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.30,1:52:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,可这玩意儿  就像动画片里的烤炉\Nbut that thing looks like Judy Jetson's Easy-Bake oven.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.75,1:52:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你的发布会要迟了\NYou're gonna start late.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.16,1:52:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,-你知道丽萨代表什么吗  -什么\N- You know what Lisa stood for? - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.13,1:52:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那台电脑  丽萨\NThe computer. The Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.40,1:52:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道这名字代表什么吗\NYou know what it stood for?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.27,1:52:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我为我对iMac的评价道歉\NI'm sorry I said that about the iMac.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:50.59,1:52:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是真这么想的\NIt's not what I really think.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.43,1:52:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,办公室我身后那台  你知道代表什么吗\NBehind my back, at the office, you know what it stood for?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.81,1:52:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,局部集成系统体系结构  我当时才五岁\NLocal Integrated System Architecture. I was five.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.46,1:53:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,-你就不能说个谎吗  -我说了\N- Why couldn't you just lie? - I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.91,1:53:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,那当然是以你的名字命名的\NOf course it was named after you.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.23,1:53:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"局部集成系统体系结构"就是瞎编的\NLocal Integrated System Architecture doesn't even mean anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.94,1:53:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,那你为什么这么多年都说不是\NWhy'd you say it wasn't all those years?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.15,1:53:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,说真的  我也不知道\NI honestly don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.16,1:53:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么说你不是我爸\NWhy'd you say you weren't my father?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.01,1:53:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我不配\NI'm poorly made.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:34.44,1:53:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,-九点多了  你要迟到了  -无所谓\N- It's after 9:00. You're gonna be late. - I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.47,1:53:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-你在为哈佛校报写稿  -什么\N- You're writing for the Crimson. - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.33,1:53:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,哈佛校友会有个苹果分会\NThe Apple chapter of the Harvard Alumni Association
Dialogue: 0,1:53:47.63,1:53:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我你在为校报写稿\Ntells me you're writing for the Crimson.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.76,1:53:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  杂文什么的\NYeah, a little bit. Essays.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:52.81,1:53:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,-我想看看  -好\N- I'd like to read one. - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.85,1:53:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说现在  我想看看你写的文章\NNo, I mean now. I'd like to read one of your essays now.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.96,1:53:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托  你现在得上台了\NCome on. You've got to go on stage.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.37,1:54:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你不给我看你写的\NThe iMac will not be launched
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.50,1:54:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,iMac就不发布\Nuntil you give me one of your essays,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.10,1:54:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,所以全世界都在等你\Nso the world is waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.80,1:54:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,非常抱歉打扰两位\NI'm really sorry, guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:18.78,1:54:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,祝你好运\NGood luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.29,1:54:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我要把音乐装进你的口袋\NI'm gonna put music in your pocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:34.92,1:54:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:38.64,1:54:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,一百首歌  一千首歌  好吧五百首歌\NHundred songs. A thousand songs. 500 songs.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:42.71,1:54:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,总之五百到一千首左右的歌装进你的口袋\NSomewhere between 500 and a thousand songs right in your pocket,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:46.87,1:54:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我实在受不了看着你\N'cause I can't stand looking at
Dialogue: 0,1:54:48.43,1:54:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,一直挂着这奇丑无比的随身听了\Nthat inexplicable Walkman anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.59,1:54:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是一块能放磁带的板砖\NYou're carrying around a brick playing cassette tape.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:53.04,1:54:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不是原始人\NWe're not savages.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:54.46,1:54:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我要把一千首歌装进你的口袋\NSo I'm gonna put a thousand songs in your pocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:57.76,1:54:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你能做到吗\NYou can do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.07,1:55:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你想在后台看着吗\NYou want to watch from backstage?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.88,1:55:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,行\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.01,1:55:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,进第一条\NGo cue one.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.08,1:56:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你还记得你在初代Mac上画的画吗\NYou remember that painting you did on the original Mac?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:37.66,1:56:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得\NI do.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:41.02,1:56:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们\NLadies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:44.88,1:56:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,有请史蒂夫·乔布斯\NSteve Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:27.37,1:57:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,沃兹\NWoz.

